title: layer salad
directions: Layer first 7 ingredients in order given.
Combine mayonnaise and sugar.
Spread evenly over top of salad.
Sprinkle on dressing.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate 8 to 12 hours.
Toss before serving.

title: 5 flavor pound cake
directions: You may substitute flavorings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Put croutons in bottom of casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese; add sausage and beaten eggs.
Mix milk, dry mustard and soup; pour over previous layers.
Sprinkle mushrooms over soup mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: bonnie's potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets.
Leave in refrigerator overnight. Peel and grate the potatoes the next day.
Melt margarine.
Add half and half and salt.
Mix all ingredients into the grated potatoes.
Add grated cheese.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle additional cheese on top the last 15 minutes of baking time.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: In 3-quart baking dish, combine soup, milk, thyme and pepper. Stir in vegetables and chicken.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes until bubbly.
Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Remove dish from oven, stir.
Arrange biscuit pieces over hot chicken mixture.
Bake 15 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.
(I like to sprinkle Parmesan cheese on biscuits before baking.)
Makes 5 servings.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown ground chuck with onion flakes and drain.
Stir in flour.
Mix in corned beef, broken up.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Peel and slice 4 cups of apples.
Place in a baking pan.
Sprinkle with water, cinnamon and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Blend together sugar, flour and melted butter or margarine, then spread over the top. Bake, uncovered, approximately 40 minutes.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: espresso chocolate sauce
directions: In a saucepan over low heat, cook and stir coffee and chocolate until chocolate is melted. Add sugar and butter; cook and stir until sugar is dissolved and the butter is melted. Remove from heat; stir in vanilla. Serve over ice cream. Makes 1 cup.

title: kentucky hot brown
directions: In a 4-quart, heavy sauce pan, melt butter.
Mix in flour until mixture is smooth.
Add milk in small amounts at a time; cook until sauce is thick.
Add Tabasco sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Remove from heat.
Take out 1/2 cup sauce and add to beaten egg yolks. Mix well and return to the remainder, stirring constantly.
Add all cheeses.
Remove from heat.
Toast six slices of bread on both sides.
Slice each piece in half and place on a heat-resistant plate.
Layer with chicken or turkey, ham of your choice, sauce, tomato, and 2 slices of bacon.
Top with paprika.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: pie crust to freeze
directions: Cut Crisco into flour.
Mix egg and vinegar in cup.
Finish filling with water.
Mix into flour.
Makes 5 crusts.
Freeze until ready to use.

title: light 'n crisp waffles
directions: Preheat waffle maker.
Put all ingredients, except egg whites in a large mixer bowl.
Beat on low until moistened.
Increase to medium; mix until smooth.
By hand, gently fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour 1/2 cup (125 mL) batter in center of grid.
Close waffle maker; bake until golden, 3 to 3 1/2 minutes.
Repeat. Serve hot with your favorite topping.
Yield: ten 6 1/2-inch (16.25 cm) waffles.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cheese, slowly adding sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time until mixed thoroughly. Combine flour and salt; add to mixture, a small amount at a time until thoroughly mixed.
Add vanilla.
Cook in tube pan, greased and floured, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan 10 minutes, then remove.

title: phil's famous pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni in a 5-quart pan.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Chop chestnuts and pepperoni.
Add ingredients and season to taste.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Using blender, mix cake mix, margarine, vanilla and 1 egg. Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 2 eggs and pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Topping forms crust on cake.

title: shortbread
directions: Mix all ingredients until they form a dough.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thick; cut into squares.
Cook at 350° for 15 minutes. Leave in pan to cool for a few minutes before moving to a cooling tray.
Dust with extra fine sugar.

title: pig licking good cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil and eggs together.
Beat two minutes at medium speed.
Cut oranges into small pieces
Add oranges and juice to cake mix.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage in heavy skillet; crumble and drain. Beat eggs; mix in milk, salt and mustard. Break bread into small pieces. Stir into egg mixture. Fold in cheese and sausage. Pour mixture into 9 x 13 Pyrex that has been buttered. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: venison shipwreck
directions: In a 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole, slice potatoes.
On top of potatoes, add venison or hamburger.
Add sliced onions, kidney beans and soup.
Salt and pepper to taste as you make layers. Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove lid and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: red potato and egg salad
directions: Combine the potatoes, eggs, scallions and carrots.
Add the parsley, caraway, dill, salt and pepper.
Toss lightly.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Place all ingredients in a covered casserole.
Bake at 250° for 4 to 6 hours.

title: wildcat stinger
directions: Combine in a mixing glass half filled with ice cubes.
Strain into a cocktail glass.
Garnish with lemon rind, worm or olive.

title: strawberry fig preserves
directions: Mash figs; add jello and sugar. Bring to boil and cook slow for 45 minutes. Pour into jars. Seal.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: In large skillet, saute the onions in the margarine until slightly browned.
Next, add the meat and cook until brown.
Now add the flour, salt, pepper, mushrooms, garlic powder, olive oil and dill weed.
Cook 5 minutes.
Next, add the mushroom soup and allow to simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream after it has been beaten thoroughly.
Now allow this to simmer until thoroughly heated.
Do not boil.
Serve with medium-wide noodles.
This goes well with spinach salad and red wine.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine ingredients.
Grease a
9 x 9-inch pan.
Pour ingredients in pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: no-bake maple walnut cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Then boil 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop on waxed paper and cool.

title: apple pie
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in unbaked crust.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Put pie in and reduce heat to 350°.
Bake until apples are tender, 40 to 50 minutes.

title: lemon fantastic
directions: Blend flour, oleo and 1/2 cup nuts and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: low fat pie crust
directions: Sift flour & salt.
Combine in measuring cup the oil and water.
Beat with fork or wisk until thick and creamy.
Pour over flour all at once.
Toss and cut with fork until blended.
Form into ball.
Save 1/4 of crust.
Roll out 3/4 until it fits your pie pan.
Place in pan and prick with fork.
Flute edges.
Roll remaining crust and cut into leaf shapes for top of pie.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Let cream cheese get to room temperature.
Whip in bowl.
Add Jell-O; mix, then add water, 1 cup at a time.
Add frozen strawberries, thawed, drained and chopped.
Mix.
Add nuts and mix again.
Put in mold (Tupperware mold).
Put in refrigerator for 2 to 4 hours.
Make sure it is very firm.
Garnish with Cool Whip and fresh strawberries.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Combine
ingredients
and
bake in 9 x 12-inch prepared pan for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: unbaked chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Boil exactly 2 minutes. Take off heat.
Add salt, vanilla, oats and coconut.
Stir like mad.
Drop on wax paper.

title: paprikas csirke(hungarian stewed chicken)
directions: Rinse chicken and cut up.
Rinse chicken parts and sprinkle with salt.
Finely chop onion and saute in shortening (not butter) until tender.
Remove from heat.
Add paprika and mix well.
Add chicken parts and mix well to coat chicken.
Return to heat. Simmer covered on low heat until chicken is tender (water need not be added).
For a creamy gravy, mix flour into sour cream and blend into sauce.

title: corn topper casserole
directions: Place beans in layer on bottom of 2-quart buttered casserole. Sprinkle onions on top.
Spread undiluted soup over them.
Add ham.
Bake in hot 425° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: impossible custard pie
directions: Mix in order in blender.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes in 10-inch greased pie pan (glass).
This makes two pies.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Pour into a pan the first 3 ingredients and bring to a boil. Boil for 3 minutes. Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix completely and drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: sausage stew
directions: Cut sausage, potatoes and carrots into bite size pieces. Simmer sausage until done in a deep pot.
Add potatoes and enough tomato puree or sauce to cover.
Cook over low heat for 1/2 hour. Keep it covered.
Drain peas.
Add peas and carrots and cook, covered, over low heat until all are tender.

title: crispy potato wedges
directions: Place potatoes in large bowl; add cold water to cover and let stand for 15 minutes. Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Spray a nonstick baking sheet with vegetable cooking spray. Set aside. Drain potatoes in a colander. Spread on a double layer of paper towels. Cover with a second layer of paper towels. Press down on the towels to dry potatoes. Transfer potatoes to a clean large bowl. Sprinkle with oil, pepper and salt; toss gently to combine. Arrange seasoned potatoes in a single layer on a baking sheet. Bake for 20 minutes, using a spatula turn potatoes; sprinkle with garlic salt. Bake until golden, about 20 minutes, turning baking sheet after 10 minutes for even browning. Serve immediately with ketchup on the side.

title: one bowl macaroons
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well. Drop from teaspoon (1-inch apart) onto well-greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove at once from baking sheets.
Makes about 2 dozen
macaroons.

title: layered rhubarb dessert
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan in order given.
Pour water over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breast in water until tender. Drain; cool and save broth. Pull meat off bones. Place in casserole dish. Combine soups and milk. Pour over chicken. Top with dressing mix. Sprinkle with broth until it is moist. Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sherry wine cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix all of the above ingredients well.
Pour into a greased tube pan.
Bake until toothpick clean.

title: fat-free macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water until done.
Leave some water. While still on stove, break up cheese.
Cook until melted.

title: hawaiian pineapple crush
directions: Put into blender and frappe until slushy.
May add 1 banana for extra flavor, if desired.

title: pineapple-apricot cheesecake cookies
directions: Cream the butter and brown sugar.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Reserve

title: green bean moussaka
directions: Put green beans in 2-quart casserole.
Brown meat; drain fat. Stir in tomato sauce, garlic and cinnamon.
Spread over green beans.
Combine eggs and cottage cheese.
Spread over meat.
Put olives and Parmesan on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: almond biscotti
directions: Stir together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt in large bowl. In a separate bowl, mix sugar, butter, eggs, zest of oranges and lemons, vanilla and almond extract. Mix contents of both bowls together and then add sliced almonds. Grease two baking sheets with

Crisco. Take a handful of dough and form a 4-inch wide and 3/4-inch thick biscotti on a sheet of floured waxed paper. The length can be as long as you can fit on your baking sheet. Set the baking sheet on top of the dough then flip over and peel of the waxed paper. Put in preheated 325° oven for about 20 minutes or until light brown. Mix egg white and powdered sugar and brush on biscotti and put back in oven for 10 minutes until golden brown.

Remove from oven and cool. Cut with serrated knife crosswise into 1/2-inch slices and place the cookies on their sides on the baking sheets. Bake 15 minutes longer. Transfer to racks and cool. Store in airtight container.

title: pork chop skillet
directions: Heat a large nonstick skillet.
Add pork chops and brown 2 minutes per side.
Remove pork.
Put onion in skillet and cook for 5 minutes until lightly browned.
Add sauerkraut, gravy and butternut squash. Cover.
Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer 8 minutes.
Stir and top with pork chops.
Cover and simmer 4 to 5 minutes or until pork is no longer pink near the bone. Makes 4 servings.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos and put in a bowl.
In another bowl, blend the pudding with the milk; fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate mixture for 2 to 3 minutes for pudding to thicken.
In large bowl, cream the cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar (until creamy).
Take the pudding from the refrigerator and add it to the cream cheese mixture.
Stir until mixed thoroughly.
Starting with the crushed cookies, layer the mixture and the cookies.
Top and bottom layers should be cookies.
Arrange gummy worms on the surface of the mixture; stick the flowers in the middle and dig in!

title: world famous buckhall barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer on low for 45 minutes or until warm.
Great over chicken.
Enough for a large crowd.

title: egg casserole
directions: Line bottom of casserole (9 x 13-inch) with bread.
Beat eggs; add milk and beat once again.
Combine with ingredients in order listed and pour over bread.
Cover and cook for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into buttered pie pan.
Drain peaches, saving syrup.
Arrange peaches over batter.
Beat the cream cheese, sugar and peach juice until smooth.
Spread over peaches to within 1-inch of edge of batter.
Sprinkle top with sugar and cinnamon.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: party dip
directions: Combine onion and cream cheese.
Thin with dressing.
Serve with cauliflower or fresh vegetables.

title: ship wreck casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in small amount of oil. Add ground beef and cook until brown. Add seasoning to taste. Add corn, soups and half of cheese. Simmer for a few minutes, mix
with cooked noodles. Pour into a large casserole dish and add remaining cheese to top. Bake at 350 degrees until cheese melts and is bubbly.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Line pan with dried beef.
Roll chicken breasts and put a slice of bacon around each one.
Put in pan.
Mix cream of chicken soup (don't add water) and sour cream.
Pour over chicken and sprinkle with paprika.
Cook for 3 hours, covered, at 300° (last 30 minutes, uncovered).
If you warm over, warm it slow.

title: pistachio crunch cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding, eggs, oil and sour cream in large mixing bowl.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
In another bowl, combine brown sugar, cinnamon and pecan pieces.
Mix good with hand.
Sprinkle half of this in greased Bundt pan.
Spoon batter over this.
Sprinkle the remaining half of sugar mixture over batter.
Place in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend onion, celery leaves, parsley, flour, butter, salt, pepper and milk in blender.
Arrange potato slices in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour mixture over potatoes and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: cappuccino
directions: Combine in large bowl. Store in airtight container. 1/3 cup mix to 1 cup hot water.

title: springtime asparagus
directions: Mix mushrooms, dressing and lemon juice in large nonstick skillet. Cook on medium heat 5 minutes. Stir frequently. Top with asparagus. Cover. Reduce heat to medium-low. Simmer 5 minutes or more. Sprinkle with almonds.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool 15 minutes.
While cake cools, bring to a boil in medium saucepan, the milk, sugar and 1/2 cup of the coconut.
Boil 5 minutes.
Punch holes in cake with fork and spoon hot coconut milk over cake.
Cool completely.

title: biscuits supreme
directions: Sift
all
dry
ingredients together; cut in shortening with pastry
blender.
Add milk, all at once; stir only until the dough
will
follow
fork around the bowl.
Turn out on a floured surface.
Knead
gently
for
1 minute.
Roll out 1/2 inch thick and cut with a biscuit cutter.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes in a greased baking pan.

title: banana split ice cream
directions: Beat eggs at medium speed until frothy.
Gradually add sugar, beating until thick.
Add skim milk and salt.
Mix well.
Pour egg mixture into a large pot.
Place over low heat.
Cook, stirring constantly until heated thoroughly.
Combine egg mixture, condensed milk, evaporated milk and vanilla.
Stir well.
Add bananas, cherries and nuts.
Freeze in a 1 1/2 gallon freezer. Let stand for 15 to 20 minutes after freezing.

title: orange cranberry relish
directions: Cut orange into eights, removing seed.
Grind orange and cranberries and add water and sugar.
Relish may be stored in refrigerator for weeks or in freezer 6 months.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except crumbs.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with crumbs and bake 1 hour at 325°.
For crumbs, melt 2 tablespoons butter and add 1 cup cracker crumbs. Mix with bread.

title: spinach salad
directions: Put garlic and salt in salad oil for 1 hour.
Mix together the cider vinegar and lemon juice.
Remove garlic clove from oil (if desired) and gradually add vinegar mixture to oil and beat until frothy.
Mix in 4 hard-boiled eggs to a pound of spinach.
Add generous amount of crisp, crumbled bacon.
Use fresh spinach only. Wash very thoroughly to eliminate sand and cut off stems.
One pound of spinach serves 8 to 10 people.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind zucchini to make 10 cups.
Combine with ground peppers and onions.
Sprinkle salt over vegetables.
Let stand overnight in fridge.
The next morning, rinse in cold water; press out.
Add turmeric, nutmeg, celery, pepper, cornstarch, vinegar and sugar to vegetables.
Cook gently 20 to 30 minutes.
Pour into hot sterilized jars and seal immediately.
Put in water bath to seal lid for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 pints.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients together; reserve 1/2 cup for topping.
Add the 1/2 cup additional flour, baking powder and baking soda to the first mixture; mix well.
Add the egg, vanilla and buttermilk to the mixture; mix well.
Place in greased 9 x 9-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle the topping on; bake in a preheated 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: banana nut date cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar and eggs.
Add bananas and vanilla. Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Blend well.
Stir in dates and nuts.
Pour into tube, loaf or layer pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: baked summer squash
directions: Wash and trim squash.
Shred with shredder or in food processor to measure 4 cups.

title: uncle bob's pink salmon dip
directions: Mix well together.
Spread on crackers or toast and serve.

title: jager-eintopf(hunter's stew)
directions: *Ground beef should only be ground once and be the leanest you can get.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and let stand for 4 hours.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Saute onion, garlic and green pepper until soft.
Add mushrooms and carrots.
Saute 3 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients. Add jalapenos, Worcestershire and Pic-a-Pepper sauce to taste. Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Uncover and simmer for 10 minutes. Taste for spice (hotness).
Serve in bowls and top with your choice of cheese.

title: coconut pie
directions: Separate eggs; reserve about 1/4 cup coconut.
Whip egg whites.
Combine all other ingredients; cook over low heat until thickened; pour into pie shell.
Top with egg whites; sprinkle with 1/4 cup coconut.
Brown on broil for about 2 minutes.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Pour into a saucepan together; simmer. Make 6 servings of Minute rice. Pour simmered beans over rice to serve. Allow to set a few minutes to mingle flavors.

title: cappuccino mix
directions: Mix well add 3 to 4 tsp. per 8-10 oz. cup of water.

title: ham and cheese souffle
directions: Mix together eggs, milk, dry mustard, salt and mushrooms. Grease a casserole dish.
Alternate layers of bread, cheese and ham.
Pour milk and egg mixture over and let stand overnight. Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: puff pastry
directions: Melt butter in 1/4 cup boiling water.
Add flour and a dash of salt.
Stir good until it forms a ball.
Remove from heat and add 1 egg and cheese.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet (bake at 400° for 20 minutes).
Stuff with chicken, ham or tuna salad.

title: hickory smoked brisket
directions: Place brisket on a large piece of aluminum foil.
Sprinkle generously with 1/4 cup liquid smoke and spices.
Wrap well.
Put in crockpot.
Cover and cook on low 10 - 12 hours or high 4 to 6 hours.
Slice brisket into thin slices.
Serve warm with juices poured over brisket.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
In large bowl mix butter, salt, Parmesan, pepper and egg.
Add spaghetti and toss.
Spread evenly in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown meat adding onion, green pepper and garlic.
Drain off fat.
Stir in sauce, sugar and oregano.
Spread cottage cheese over spaghetti layer.
Top with meat mixture and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella.
Bake another 10 minutes.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water until tender.
Drain.
Peel and cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Place in a greased shallow baking pan.
Set aside.

title: cheese and chipped beef log
directions: Combine ingredients and put chipped beef on top.
Serve with crackers.

title: cabbage au gratin
directions: Cut up cabbage and cook in salted water until tender.
Make a white sauce with the butter, flour and milk.

title: hungarian nut crescents
directions: Mix salt with flour in bowl.
Cut in butter until mixture makes coarse crumbs.
Blend together in separate bowl sour cream, egg yolk and vanilla.
Gradually add to flour mixture, mixing well.
Chill until firm enough to handle, about 3 1/2 to 4 hours. Divide dough into 3 parts.
Roll each part on a lightly floured board into a 9 to 10-inch circle about 1/8-inch thick.
Cut each circle into 12 wedges.
Mix nuts, sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle 3/4 of the mixture over the wedges.
Roll from widest end to the point.
Brush with egg white and sprinkle with remaining nut mixture.
Bake on greased baking sheets at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Yield: 3 dozen.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Boil the syrup, water and 1 1/2 cups powdered sugar.
Boil and add the marshmallows and vanilla. Boil and add 1 1/2 cups powdered sugar so you will have 3 cups all together (powdered sugar).
Do not add last 1 1/2 cups sugar until it boils.
Pour over popcorn. (I use my turkey roaster full of popcorn.)
Shape into balls.
Use oleo on your hands or use 2 Baggies over your hands.
Two drops of red or green coloring may be added for Christmas.

title: salsa
directions: Mix vegetables; bring to a boil.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Place in pint jars and process 5 minutes at 5 pounds of pressure to can. Makes 8 pints.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Cream together oil, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients which have been blended together.
Add nuts.
Spread in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool in pan.
Cut in squares.
If desired, top unbaked dough with 1/2 package chocolate or butterscotch chips or Holiday M&M's.

title: apricot cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, eggs, oil, sugar and apricot nectar juice.
Pour batter into a well-greased and floured Bundt tube pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown.
Let set in pan 15 minutes and then turn out.
While still warm, drizzle the topping over cake.

title: macaroni and tomatoes
directions: Cook the macaroni in salted water until tender, about 8 minutes. Add the tomatoes and heat through. Serve hot.

title: onion cheese supper bread
directions: Saute onion in oil until tender but not brown.
Combine egg and milk.
Add to biscuit mix and stir until moistened.
Add onion, half of cheese and parsley.
Spread dough in a greased 8-inch round cake pan.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and parsley.
Drizzle butter over top and bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Serves 8.

title: rainbow punch
directions: Mix 1 can each lemonade, orange juice and grape juice with water as directed on cans.
Pour each juice into an ice cube tray, setting aside any juice that is leftover.
Freeze.
About 15 minutes before serving, mix second can of lemonade and combine with ginger ale in punch bowl.
Add remaining reconstituted fruit juices.
Makes 2 quarts or 12 to 14 servings.

title: judy's cocktail meat balls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well and then add next 4 ingredients. Mix well and shape into 1-inch balls.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix and roll into little balls and sprinkle with sugar.
Place cookies on cookie sheet.
Press down with fork.
Bake at 300° until faintly brown, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: gluten steaks
directions: Gradually mix liquid ingredients into dry ingredients and knead dough.
Roll half at a time on board on wet surface.
Slice off 1/2-inch at a time.
Keep your hands wet and press slices flat.
Drop one at a time into broth and cook 25 minutes.
Keep cover on and stir once in awhile.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix all in dressing jar.
Serve over green salad.

title: hot jambalaya
directions: Saute ham, sausage and vegetables in butter until soft.
Stir in stock, tomatoes, Ro-Tel and seasoning.
Bring to a boil and add rice.
Cook until rice has absorbed liquid, 40 minutes for whole grain rice or you may use Minute rice and reduce time.
Stir in steamed shelled shrimp.
Have the deli department of your grocery steam shrimp to save time.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crust from bread. Butter on both sides; break into pieces and place in bottom of 9 x 13 casserole dish. Fry sausage and crumble; set aside to drain. Sprinkle sausage and cheese on top of bread. Combine milk, eggs and salt; beat well. Pour on top of casserole. Refrigerate overnight. Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before cooking. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: sausage jambalaya
directions: In an ovenproof skillet, cook sausage until lightly browned. Add eggplant, onions and green peppers.
Cook until tender-crisp. Stir in rice, broth, tomatoes and seasonings. Bring to a boil. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Fluff lightly with a fork.
Remove bay leaf.

title: homemade lemonade
directions: In a half gallon pitcher, put the 2 cups of hot water and the sugar.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add lemon juice and the 4 cups of cold water.
Add ice to make a half gallon.

title: corn bread chili pie
directions: Combine in skillet and brown the beef and onion.
Add tomato soup, salt, corn, chili powder and peppers.
Mix and simmer 15 minutes.
Put in greased casserole and top with corn bread topping, which has been mixed acccording to directions on mix.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: russian chicken
directions: Mix Russian dressing, preserves and onion soup.
Pour over chicken and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken - polish style(kurczeta po polsku)
directions: Sprinkle the chicken with salt; let stand 1 hour.
Chop the livers
finely.
Combine
with bread crumbs, egg, salt to taste, dill
weed,
pepper
and
as much milk as needed for a loose, sour cream-like consistency.
Fill cavity
of
chicken with
crumb mixture; truss.
Place chicken
in	roasting
pan. Bake at 400° for about 45 minutes, or until chicken is tender. Baste often with melted butter.

title: cheesy chicken macaroni casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir together all ingredients.
Pour into ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake 1 hour.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: cheesecake bars
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar; add flour and nuts and mix.
Set aside 1 cup of the mixture for topping.
Press remainder in bottom of 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Blend sugar and cream cheese until smooth; add egg, milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Beat well.
Spread over bottom crust and sprinkle with reserved 1 cup topping.
Return to oven and bake 25 minutes more.
Cool, then chill and cut into triangles.
May double recipe and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Makes 20 to 25 bars.

title: peter paul mound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add sifted flour alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Measure all ingredients into a large bowl. Mix together.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: beef-cheese casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in skillet until beef is browned. Add salt, pepper, oregano and tomato sauce.
Simmer slowly. Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream and green pepper. Place half the noodles in bottom of greased 3-quart casserole dish.
Top with cheese mixture; add remaining noodles.
Pour meat mixture over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and let brown slightly.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: freeze peaches
directions: In large bowl, mix orange juice and sugar.
Then slice peaches in bowl.
Make sure all peaches have juice on them.
Put in container and freeze.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: In medium bowl, blend together soup and sour cream; set aside. In large bowl, toss together chicken, onion, 4 ounces Cheddar and picante sauce.
Moisten with about 1/4 of soup mixture.
Divide chicken mixture evenly among tortillas by spooning across center. Blend broth into remaining soup mixture.
Cover bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish with some soup mixture.
Roll tortillas tightly and place seam side down in single layer.
Spread with remaining soup mixture and sprinkle with remaining 4 ounces Cheddar.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Pour half of batter into pan.
Spread half of cheese on batter.
Add remaining batter and top with rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until brown around edges.

title: nut puffs
directions: Heat oven to 300°, slow oven.
Mix together butter, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Form dough into small balls. Place on greased cookie sheet and bake about 30 minutes.
While still hot, roll puffs in confectioners sugar.

title: scalloped potatoes  with ham
directions: Peel potatoes and slice thin.
Make white sauce with margarine, flour and milk.
Put half the potatoes in a greased 2-quart pan.
Cover with half the sauce, seasonings, onion and ham.
Add remaining potatoes, seasonings, onion and ham, then remaining sauce.
Cover and bake in moderate oven at 350° for about 1 hour.
Uncover and continue baking until top is browned. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: yeast bread
directions: Mix yeast, margarine, egg, water and sugar in large bowl. Add flour and mix well. Cover and refrigerate. Use as needed.

title: zucchini hot dish
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan for approximately 1 hour at 325°.
Keep a close eye on this casserole after 45 minutes of baking; it browns quickly!

title: dirt pie
directions: Crush cookies in food processor until it looks like dirt.
Set aside.
Cream oleo, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Mix milk and instant pudding.
In a large bowl, layer cookie crumbs to start and use cookie crumbs to top.

title: tea cakes
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and extract; beat well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill for 1 to 2 hours.
Shape into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Place 2 1/2-inches apart on lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 11 to 13 minutes or until lightly browned (do not overbake). Cool 1 minute on pan before removing to a wire rack.
Yield:
5 1/2 dozen.

title: monkey bread-cinnamon pull aparts
directions: Dip each biscuit in melted margarine and then in mixture of sugars, nuts and cinnamon.
Stand on edge in 9 x 5 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Make 2 side by side rows.
Sprinkle with remaining sugar mixture.
Cover with foil and bake 15 minutes more or until golden and biscuits are done.
Cool 5 minutes and turn out on serving plate.
Great for Saturday morning breakfast or cold winter evening treat.

title: creole eggs
directions: Saute onions, peppers and celery in a large skillet in 4 tablespoons melted butter.
Add tomatoes, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Cook until thick.
In a separate pan, melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Add flour and blend thoroughly.
Add milk and stir until thickened to make a white sauce.
Combine with tomato mixture. Slice eggs in round slices.
In a buttered 9 x 13 x 2-inch glass baking dish, place a layer of white sauce and tomato mixture and a layer of eggs alternately until ingredients are used, ending with sauce.
Top with buttered plain toasted bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 12 servings.

title: roquefort-sherry mayonnaise
directions: Process the egg yolks, mustard and vinegar in a food processor or blender just to combine, about 30 seconds. With the machine running, pour the oil in a thin steady stream through the feed tube to make a thick mayonnaise. Add Roquefort and process just until combined (not smooth). Season to taste with salt and pepper. Makes about 3 cups.

title: spice cake with apple pie filling
directions: Mix pie filling, cake mix and eggs together.
Put 1/2 batter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 sugar and cinnamon over it.
Put remaining 1/2 batter in pan and sprinkle with the remaining 1/2 sugar and cinnamon.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: breakfast rolls
directions: Roll crescent rolls out flat.
Spread slightly with butter. Sprinkle with nuts.
Mix butter, honey and confectioners sugar and set aside.
Separate each roll and roll up crescent style.
Place in sprayed 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven until golden brown. Drizzle honey mixture on warm cooked rolls, not hot rolls.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, butter and salt in a 2-quart dish. Bring to a boil in microwave.
Boil on High for 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and soda.
Stir until smooth.
Put corn in a paper sack. Pour mixture over corn.
Shake well.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Shake again.
Return to microwave.
Cook on High 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake again.

title: milky way ice cream
directions: In heavy saucepan, melt candy bars in 2 cups milk.
Cool. Beat egg and add sugar. Beat well again.
Add vanilla, remaining milk and half and half.
Combine mixtures and mix well.
Pour into gallon freezer can. Add extra milk, if needed, to come to fill line.
Freeze according to freezer directions.

title: peel a pound soup
directions: Dice or cube all veggies.
Place in a large pot.
Add water; add seasonings and simmer until thick.
Can add other vegetables if you like.
Only 97 calories per serving.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Mix together in crock-pot the white almond bark, chocolate chips, cocoa and vegetable oil.
Melt together, then blend in cocktail peanuts until somewhat stiff, probably 2 large packages. Then drop onto wax paper and cool.
Can add paraffin to make shiny.

title: grandma hardin's christmas jam cakegroves, texas
directions: Cream butter and sugar and add eggs.
Add other ingredients and beat all until they are blended.
Cook at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt butter and cocoa together. Remove from heat and stir in sugar and eggs.

Mix well. Add flour, salt, chopped nuts and vanilla. Mix well. Spoon batter into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Sprinkle marshmallows on top of warm cake. Cover with your favorite chocolate frosting.
I like to use this:

title: garlic potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into wedges.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Bake at 375° for approximately 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: grilled corn-on-the-cob
directions: Peel and cut up eggplant.
Dip in beaten egg and roll in a mixture of flour and Italian bread crumbs.
Brown in oil and drain on paper towels.
Put a layer of eggplant in a baking dish.
Add each additional layer in order: spaghetti sauce (Ragu), Parmesan cheese, Mozzarella cheese and sprinkle dried minced onion and chili powder on top.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with salad and garlic bread.

title: dressing for cole slaw
directions: Mix well and bring to boil.
Simmer for 3 minutes.
Pour over cabbage, bell pepper and onions.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: easy sticky buns
directions: Mix together brown sugar, butter and corn syrup.
Spread in bottom of two 8-inch square baking pans.
Mix together pecans, cinnamon and white sugar.
Divide in half for each tube of rolls.

title: herb dip for vegetables
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let set in refrigerator several hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine squash, butter, salt, pepper and onion; add beaten eggs.
Alternate layers of squash, bread crumbs and cheese in a 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce(makes 6 to 7 quarts)
directions: Grind peppers and onions. Cook 1/2 hour in oil. Put through a sieve then add to juice. Add remaining ingredients. Cook until thickened. Put sauce in sterilized jars and seal. Process 15 minutes in pressure canner.

title: magic chocolate french fudge
directions: In top
of double boiler, melt chocolate over hot water; stir occasionally.
Remove
from heat.
Add sweetened condensed milk, salt,
vanilla
extract
and
nut meats.
Stir only until smooth. Turn into waxed paper lined 8-inch square pan.
Spread mixture evenly
and
smooth surface.
Refrigerate about 2 hours or until firm.
Turn candy onto cutting board to cut.
Store in airtight container.

title: chicken feed
directions: Melt almond bark.
Mix all ingredients together well and drop on wax paper.
Leave until firm.
Put in plastic bag or airtight container.
Can be frozen.
Great for all ages.

title: lasagna
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan.
Saute the onions, garlic and green pepper until softened.
Add the mushrooms and saute until tender. Add the ground beef and pepper.
Cook until meat loses its red color.
Drain well.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, basil, oregano, parsley and bay leaves.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours or until sauce has thickened.
While cooking, if sauce becomes too thick, add small amount of water as needed.

title: egg yolk pie pastry
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Place egg in cup size measure.
Add enough water to make a scant cupful.
Beat. Sprinkle egg water mixture over flour mixture and mix with a fork until crumbly.
Form into 5 or 6 pie portions.
Roll out on floured board in pie shapes.
Make into pies.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Put butter in cold, heavy skillet.
Melt slowly; add eggs, sugar, salt and dates.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly and mashing dates, for 12 to 15 minutes or until very thick.
Pour over Rice Krispies and mix well.
Cool and form into balls or figures.
Roll in coconut.
Yields 25 servings.

title: apple good
directions: Heat oven
to 350°. Grease and lightly dust with flour, one baking dish, 9-inches square and 2-inches deep.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding dry with pineapple and juice.
Add marshmallows. Add Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: rice broccoli bake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl and spoon into a lightly oiled casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Melt oleo; add onion and celery and saute until clear.
Add broccoli and stir.
Add soup; stir and simmer several minutes. Add Cheez Whiz and mix.
Add rice; stir and simmer.
Bake in buttered casserole at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: winter vegetable beef soup
directions: In an 8-quart kettle, melt butter and cook onions until tender, about 5 to 7 minutes.
Stir in ground beef.
Add garlic. Cook until brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring soup to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat and simmer soup, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.
Make day or 2 before serving.
Stretch by adding more carrots, potatoes or other vegetables.

title: no-bake cheesecake
directions: Use a rectangular (8 x 13-inch) pan or glass dish for crust. Mix cheesecake according to directions.
Mix in softened cream cheese, Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Fold in other ingredients until well blended.
Pour in crust; chill for at least an hour.
Top with your favorite pie filling.

title: lucky if you get a bite
directions: Mix flour and butter and bake in long cake pan until light brown.
Mix cream cheese and brown sugar and spread over first layer when cool.
Mix vanilla instant pie filling with milk.
Beat until thick, then spread over second layer.
On third layer, spread Cool Whip and pecans.

title: dip for raw vegetables
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Chill before serving.
May be made several days ahead of time.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Stir in all remaining ingredients.
Chill mixture.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Place butter, sugar, milk, cocoa and salt in heavy saucepan over low heat until butter melts.
Stir frequently with wooden spoon.
When butter has melted and starts to boil, let boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla. Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper to cool.

title: gingerbread boys
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Blend in molasses, water, flour, salt, soda, ginger, nutmeg and allspice.
Cover; chill 2 to 3 hours.
Roll dough 1/4-inch thick on lightly covered floured cloth board.
Cut with cutter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Press raisins into dough for eyes, nose and buttons.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove immediately from cookie sheet.
Cool and decorate.

title: beef tips
directions: Combine stew meat with other ingredients.
Cook at 325° for 2 to 3 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Chop bell pepper and onion.
Drain corn and mix together with mayonnaise.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: blueberry ice cream
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, vanilla, blueberries and milk.
Freeze. Whip frozen mixture, then fold in heavy cream.
Return to freezer.

title: shrimp souffle
directions: Layer shrimp, bread and cheese in greased casserole.
Pour over oleo and egg mixture. Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour. Bake 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.
Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Prebake a pastry shell.
Hull and wash strawberries.
Place 3 cups strawberries in the baked and cooled shell.
In a saucepan, simmer together 1 cup strawberries and 2/3 cup water for 3 minutes.
Mix together the cornstarch in 1/3 cup water.
Add the cornstarch mixture and 1 cup sugar to the cooked strawberries. Cook over medium heat for 1 minute.
The mixture will start milky and then turn clear.
Pour the mixture over the strawberries in the pastry shell and cool.
Serve with whipped cream

title: cream puffs
directions: Bring water and margarine to boil.
Stir in flour until it leaves edge of pan and forms a ball (only about one minute). Remove from heat and cool to lukewarm.
Beat eggs one at a time and blend with flour mixture.
Spoon out cream puffs on cookie sheets.
Puffs should be size of biscuit.
Bake 40 minutes or until golden brown in oven at 350°.

title: oreo cookie balls
directions: Crush cookies real fine. Mix with cream cheese. Form into balls. Chill for 30 minutes. Dip into melted almond bark. Store in refrigerator.

title: scratch pancakes
directions: Stir all ingredients in a medium bowl and spoon onto hot griddle.
Quick, easy and good!

title: salmon patties or loaf
directions: Remove bones and break into chunks.
Add crackers, beaten eggs, seasoning, onions and some liquid from salmon.
Mix thoroughly and shape into patties or loaf.
Either fry or bake in greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and pour in baking dish.
Top with brown sugar, pecans and 1/3 cup butter.
Spread on top.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: cherry cupcake
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and eggs until creamy.
Put paper liners in the cupcake pan.
Put Nilla Wafers into paper cup liner, then pour 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Put cherry pie filling on top and chill.

title: english cookies
directions: Mix together and drop by spoonfuls onto buttered pans.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Combine soup, milk, salt, chicken, vegetables, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 onions.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Unwrap rolls. Separate into 2 rectangles.
Press together perforated cuts.
Cut each rectangle lengthwise into 6 strips.
Lattice over casserole. Bake uncovered 15 minutes, then top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake uncovered 3 to 5 minutes.

title: cranberry swirl salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Stir in pineapple and cranberry sauce. Chill until partially set. Spoon into 8 inch square dish. Spoon sour cream on top and stir to swirl. Chill until firm. Cut into squares to serve.

title: pastitsio
directions: Cook onion and turkey in skillet over medium heat until onion is soft and turkey is no longer pink.
Add tomato sauce and spices.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.

title: pineapple-coconut cake
directions: Mix ingredients; beat 3 minutes.
Pour into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: bite size apple pies
directions: Place cinnamon and sugar in a gallon size plastic bag and shake, mixing well.
Set aside.
Unroll crescents and cut each in half longways.
You should now have 16 pieces.
Slice apples into 8 equal pieces and place into sugar mixture.
Shake to coat well. Place apples onto crescent dough and roll them up wide end first. Put onto cookie sheet.
Pop into 375° oven for 10 to 15 minutes. Makes 16 mini pies.

title: gau (chinese mochi cake)
directions: Combine Mochiko, sugar and baking soda.
Add coconut milk and water.
Mix well.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Pour batter into a greased pan and top with sesame seed.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: microwave peanut patties
directions: Boil on High for 3 minutes.
Stir and add 1 1/2 cups raw peanuts.
Cook on High for 9 minutes (soft boil).
Add 2 tablespoons of butter and 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Add a few drops of red food coloring.
Stir until cool and thick.
Drop on wax paper.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook macaroni as package label directs; drain.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together. Put in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cocoa sheath cake(excellent)
directions: In a big bowl, sift together the sugar and flour.
Mix in saucepan and bring to a boil the oleo, cocoa, Crisco and water. Pour over flour and sugar and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased pan at 350°.

title: red raspberry pie
directions: You will need 1 baked pie shell or 1 graham cracker crust. Mix sugar, cornstarch or clear jel and water.
Bring to boil. Boil a little, then add raspberry jello, mixing well.
Cool, then add raspberries.
May need to use less water with frozen berries. Put in pie shells and chill.
Top with whipped topping or whipped cream.

title: best yet cracker jacks
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Add soda and stir into 5 quarts popped corn.
Spread on well-greased cookie sheet.
Place in a 225° oven for 40 minutes.
Stir frequently. (Peanuts may be added, if desired.)

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion, add peppers.
Mix eggs, milk and oil. Add bread mix and corn.
Pour half of batter into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread meat mixture, sprinkle cheese.
Add rest of batter.
Bake in preheated 350° oven approximately 45 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef in a large skillet.
Drain and place in a 4-quart crock-pot.
Saute onion and bell pepper in skillet until onion is clear.
Add to crock-pot along with remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Cook on high setting 3 to 4 hours or low setting for 6 to 8 hours.
This can be frozen and is also good in taco shells.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Drain pineapple chunks and reserve.
Pour syrup into small saucepan.
Add sugar, lemon and orange slices and cinnamon. Bring to simmer; cook 5 minutes.
Add cranberries; simmer until they begin to burst.
Stir in drained pineapple chunks.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: angel hair pasta with creamy mushroom sauce
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain. Meanwhile, for sauce, in a medium saucepan cook the mushrooms and onion in the butter (or margarine) until vegetables are tender. Stir in cream cheese, salt and pepper. Cook and stir over low heat until cheese is melted. Gradually stir in milk and chives; heat through. Pour sauce over pasta. Toss to coat. Serve immediately.

title: venison stroganoff
directions: Brown venison cubes in butter.
Stir in onion soup mix.
Add water, parsley, garlic powder, pepper and oregano.
When meat is tender, add 1/2 cup of sour cream.
Blend 1/4 cup cornstarch with small amount of water.
Stir into meat until thickened.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: pot roast
directions: Flour each side of roast.
Brown on each side in pan.
Add 3/4 cup water.
Simmer, covered, 3 to 4 hours.
One hour before done, add carrots, potatoes, onions and seasonings to taste, garlic, etc.

title: oven omelet
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs, milk and salt.
Add bacon, cheese and onion.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake uncovered 40 to 45 minutes or until omelet is set and top is golden brown.

title: no bake strawberry yogurt pie
directions: In a bowl, mix yogurt and Cool Whip and crushed strawberries (save some to spread on top if desired) together.
Pour into graham cracker Ready-Crust.
Chill; serve.
Makes a nice, light dessert.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg and molasses.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill dough.
Roll into balls.
Dip in sugar. Sprinkle with 2 or 3 drops of water.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: oven-barbecued ribs for 4
directions: Salt and pepper short ribs.
Place in layer in shallow baking pan.
Add water.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in hot oven at 400°.
Saute onion and garlic in butter.
Add tomato puree, salt, celery salt, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and liquid smoke. Simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove ribs from oven. Drain off some fat, if desired.
Spoon sauce over ribs.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes.

title: new york brass rail cheesecake
directions: Blend well in large mixer bowl.
Butter a deep 10-inch spring-form pan.
Line the bottom with crushed lemon cookies. Pour batter into pan.
Place cake pan into a larger pan of hot water, half the depth of the cake pan.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 80 minutes or until completely set.
Let cool thoroughly before removing from spring-form pan.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in casserole.
Cover with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hungry jack beef casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Stir in next 5 ingredients; heat until bubbly.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Cut biscuits in half to form 20 half circles.
Place cut side down around edge of casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 35 minutes in 350° oven. Use 8 x 8-inch greased pan.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 4 long triangles and place crosswise on ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Press over bottom and up the sides to form a crust.
Seal perforations. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.

title: prune cake
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, eggs and buttermilk. Set aside. Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and spices.
Add flour mixture to the first 4 ingredients; mix well. Add prunes, vanilla and nuts. Blend well and pour into pan of choice. Bake at 350° until done.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and molasses.
Add sifted dry ingredients (not sugar).
Beat until smooth.
Roll into small ball and drop into sugar.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven about 10 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugars, egg and vanilla until fluffy. Add in flour, soda and salt. When well mixed, add in nuts and chocolate chips. Drop teaspoon of dough on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: e-z chicken tetrazzini
directions: In saucepan, combine soup, water and cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Stir occasionally.
Add remaining ingredients and heat.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt butter and cool.
Add all other ingredients one at a time.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 40 minutes at 300°.

title: blueberry party salad
directions: Dissolve cherry jello in boiling water.
Add Knox gelatine, pineapple and blueberry pie filling.
Pour into 9 x 11-inch rectangular dish.
After this mixture is firm, spread with Cool Whip.
Can be used in a mold.

title: breakfast bundt rolls
directions: Place in bundt pan in above order.
Put in cold over overnight.
In the morning bake at 325°.
Do not preheat oven. Bake 30-45 minutes.
Then invert on plate while hot.
If you have a gas stove, you can place the rolls in the microwave overnight.

title: champagne punch
directions: Use punch bowl with large piece of ice. Have plenty of fruit mixed well.
Use fruit like pineapple bits, orange slices, lime and strawberries.

title: soup "au giraumon" squash
directions: Wash meat with lemon and rinse with warm water.
Cut and combine all ingredients into a casserole with enough water.
Boil and cook until everything is tender, for about 40 to 45 minutes. Makes 4 servings.
Serve warm.

title: our french onion soup
directions: Peel the onions and chop roughly.
Melt the butter in the pan; fry the onions.
Once brown, sprinkle flour and stir well.
Pour wine and water over them; allow to boil.
In a large, ovenproof bowl, place 1 slice of bread, then 1 slice of cheese and so on. Pour the contents of the pan over the bread and cheese; cook in oven for 35 minutes at 325°.
Mix and serve.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all together. Add 1 egg at a time. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Grease and flour 3 loaf pans.

title: grandmom's green tomato relish
directions: Cut tomatoes and onions into thin slices.
Stew until tender. Jar while hot.

title: butterhorns
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add eggs, sugar, salt and butter.
Then add flour.
Let rise.
Roll out into a circle and cut into pie shape.
Roll up from wide edge.
Let rise.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: apricot wafer pie
directions: Combine cookie crumbs and 2 Tbsp. melted butter.
Spread 3/4 of the crumbs on the bottom of a 7x11-inch pan.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use 3 teaspoons per 6-ounce cup of hot water.
Sweeten if desired.
Makes 4 pints.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix pineapple, flour and sugar together and pour into a greased dish.
Melt margarine and add crackers and cheese.
Pour over pineapple mixture. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: berry shortcake
directions: Combine all cake ingredients except strawberries and whipped cream.
Beat at medium speed until well mixed.
Spread in a greased and floured 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool completely.
Cut into squares.
Split if desired and serve with strawberries and whipped cream.

title: brioches
directions: In bottom of pan, pour molasses and water.
Mix the first 4 ingredients, then add shortening as to make pie shells and milk. Roll dough in 1 large piece; spread over it small apple pieces and walnuts.
Form a roll; slice approximately 1-inch thick.
Drop in molasses and water mixture.
Cook for 35 minutes at 250°.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook noodles until tender, drain.
Soak in cold water.
While noodles are soaking, dice tomatoes and slice onion into rings. Slice broccoli and cauliflower into bite size pieces.
Drain noodles and mix well.
Chill at least one hour before serving.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients well; add buttermilk, eggs and fat.
Put in hot skillet.
Cook at 425° for 17 minutes.
Serve hot. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: overnight salad
directions: Cook egg, sugar, vinegar and butter until thick;
let cool and then pour over whipped cream.
Mix in remaining ingredients.

title: chili
directions: Steam hamburger meat in covered skillet until rawness is gone; stir several times.
Drain off grease and extra liquid.
Add chili mix, stew mix, cumin, tomato sauce, beans, onion and garlic.
Add 2 cups water, also make up the extra that you poured off of liquid.
You can add salt but is hard on high blood pressure, but is good with no salt added.
Crackers is enough.
Cook in crock-pot about 2 1/2 hours.
Freezes well.

title: bite-size cubed deer
directions: Be sure to wash your meat.
Tear your cubed deer into bite-size pieces and sprinkle with your meat tenderizer.
Then batter your pieces in the flour and drop into hot oil.
Cook until pieces begin to float.
Take them out and serve with side dish of your choice.

title: chocolate banana cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Cream butter or shortening. Gradually add brown sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add beaten eggs and blend well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with banana pulp, a little at a time, beating well after each addition until smooth. Pour half of batter in well-greased 8-inch square pan.
Melt chocolate chips in a saucepan and spread over batter. Cover with remaining batter and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Frost with Butter Frosting.

title: easy pot roast
directions: You will also need 1 Reynolds oven bag (large size).

title: spinach with cheese
directions: Cook spinach according to directions.
Drain spinach. Crumble in cream cheese and mix well.
Add raw egg and a little Parmesan cheese.
(Stir in a little and sprinkle a little on top.)
Put in casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 400 degrees, or until casserole gets bubbly.

title: mud pies
directions: Crush Oreos, mix with melted margarine.
Press into cake pan.
Let ice cream sit at room temperature for 1/2 hour; spread on crust. Freeze 2 hours.
Pour warm hot fudge topping over ice cream. Freeze until needed.
Top with whipped topping and sprinkle with nuts.

title: fresh mushroom soup
directions: Chop the onion fine and cook in butter until brown.
Slice mushrooms and add.
Stir until done.
Add flour and stir to coat mushrooms.
Continue cooking for 5 minutes at medium-high heat, stirring occasionally to keep from burning.
Add beef stock, stirring continuously.
Reduce to medium heat; cook ten minutes (do not boil).
Add cream and spices.
Stir and serve.

title: chocolate crinkle cookies
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients; stir in.
Chill dough in freezer until firm; store in freezer.

title: doris's strawberry cake
directions: Sift together well cake mix and jello.
Add eggs, oil, strawberries, water.
Mix well. Makes two layers.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: reese's cups
directions: Mix well with hands.
Pack in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin and pour over mixture.
Cut in squares before paraffin gets too cold.

title: cream cheese danish
directions: Unroll 1 tube of dough into bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Press to sides of pan, and press all seams together.

title: the ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream shortening, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Blend until creamy.
Blend in egg. Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture, gradually.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop rounded tablespoons of dough 3 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on baking sheet 2 minutes. Remove to cooling rack.
Makes 3 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: raisin buttermilk pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs lightly. Crumble in sugar, making sure there are no lumps. Beat until light.
Stir in salt, cinnamon and buttermilk until well mixed. Spread 1 cup raisins in each pie shell.

Pour 1/3 custard mixture (about 2 cups) into each shell. Bake on lowest rack in preheated 375° oven for 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Serve warm or cool. Pies freeze well. When cool, wrap airtight and freeze. Will keep about 1 month.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Make teaspoon size balls.
Place balls on a tray.
Eat when you like.

title: guacamole burgers
directions: Mash avocado in small bowl.
Stir in lemon juice, onion, 1/2 teaspoon salt and hot pepper sauce.
Form ground beef into 6 patties.
Pan-broil on both sides or broil in oven.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Place each patty on bun half.
Top with tomato slice, avocado mixture, lettuce and bun top.
Makes 6 servings.

title: papas enchiladas(pinked potatoes)
directions: Boil medium size potatoes until soft; peel and dice.
Fry bacon until crisp; remove from skillet.
Add vinegar, salt, chili powder to bacon fat; add diced potatoes and heat thoroughly.
Turn onto heated platter, garnish with crisp bacon.
Serve hot.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook the broccoli as directed on package. Drain and place on the bottom of an 8 x 11-inch baking dish.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder together and pour mixture over broccoli and chicken breasts in baking dish.
Melt margarine and add bread crumbs to moisten.
Arrange shredded cheese and bread crumbs to the top of the dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes and serve.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
I use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine cornmeal and red pepper in bowl. Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Spoon into 8X8 baking pan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Bake at 450 degrees for 25 minutes or until golden brown. Cut into 2 inch square.

title: matthew's waffles
directions: Sift flour and dry ingredients.
Beat egg yolks and add butter and milk.
Pour liquid mixture into dry and combine with just a few strokes.
Batter should have a pebbled look.

title: wedding cake frosting
directions: Put all ingredients into bowl.
Add hot water, a few drops at a time, while beating with mixer until spreading consistency.
Frost cake.
(It will form a smooth, glossy crust as it dries, but icing will stay moist.)

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix the sugar and eggs and the molasses together, and then add the cooled margarine.

title: chocolate brickle sheet cake
directions: Boil, stirring constantly, the cocoa, margarine and water. Blend remaining ingredients.
Bake 20 minutes in a 400° oven. Remove from heat.
Frost immediately.

title: watergate cake
directions: Cream all together and pour into greased pan 13 x 9-inch. Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine ingredients and bake in greased casserole dish until set in 350° oven.
This recipe was given to me by Sam's aunt, who is 92 years young.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer in order; lettuce, cauliflower, sugar, onion, crumbled bacon and cheese.
Cover and let stand overnight.
Add 1 cup mayonnaise before using and serve.

title: velveeta broccoli salad
directions: Cook broccoli as directed, but not too soft; drain. Cube cheese and 1/2 stick butter.
Mix together and layer broccoli, cheese and butter in 1-quart casserole.
Melt 2/3 stick butter. Roll or crumble Ritz crackers, not too fine; add to melted butter. Mix until coated.
Top broccoli with buttered Ritz crackers.
Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 6.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients thoroughly; put into loaf pan.
Cover with 2 strips bacon (optional).
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: no bake pie
directions: Let ice cream soften slightly.
Mix in milk.
Add the instant pudding and stir well.
Pour the mixture into the pie shell.
Put in freezer until firm.
Remove 10 minutes before serving.

title: easy turkey pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except crust); set aside.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Seal in Tupperware in refrigerator until ready to use.
These freeze well so you can roll them, cut them and place on a cookie sheet until frozen, then place in Ziploc bag.

title: microwave chicken with wild rice
directions: Reserve 1 tablespoon of rice seasoning mix.
Combine remaining seasoning with rice, mushrooms, sherry and 1 1/3 cups of hot water in a 7 x 11-inch glass baking dish.
Cover.
Microwave on High for 15 minutes.
Stir rice and seasoned chicken with reserved seasoning mix. Arrange chicken skin side up over rice.
Sprinkle with paprika and cover.
Microwave on High for 12 to 15 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink near bone, turning dish every 5 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Sift flour once.
Measure.
Add baking powder.
Sift 3 times. Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually and cream.
Add egg yolks.
Add flour alternately with milk, a small amount at a time.
Beat after each addition.

title: pumpkin pie squares(recipe served at club meetings)
directions: Combine flour, oats, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup margarine in a bowl.
Mix until crumbly.
Press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: grits-sausage casserole
directions: Will need 2-quart baking dish.

title: cabbage au gratin
directions: Cook cabbage 7 minutes in boiling salt water--drain thoroughly.
Make cream sauce from butter, flour and milk.
Cook until smooth and thick.
Remove from heat and stir in 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Add sauce with cheese to the cabbage.
Mix well. Pour into greased casserole, sprinkle top with bread crumbs.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 350 degree oven.
Serve hot.

title: cream cheese tarts
directions: Let cream cheese soften; beat with eggs and sugar until smooth.
Place vanilla wafers in foil cupcake papers in muffin tin.
Fill about 1/2 to
full.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes, until puffed.
Cool
to 5 minutes, then cover with cherry pie filling.
Chill
and
top
with
Cool
Whip.
Makes about 18 tarts.

title: german chocolate earthquake cake
directions: In a saucepan, put 1 stick oleo and cream cheese.
Heat until warm enough to stir in a box of powdered sugar.
Mix well.
Spread over cake mix as evenly as possible.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Can be turned out on cake plate.

title: crispy eggplant
directions: In small bowl, stir together first 3 ingredients.
In shallow dish or on sheet of waxed paper, combine next 3 ingredients. Brush both sides of eggplant with real mayonnaise mixture; coat with crumb mixture.
Place in shallow roasting pan or on baking sheet.
Bake in 425° oven 15 to 17 minutes or until browned. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ketchup.
Put in pan.
Put ketchup on top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: creamy double fudge
directions: Line an 8-inch square pan with foil.
In a micro bowl, place peanut butter chips and 2/3 cup sweetened condensed milk. Microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes; stir after 1 minute.
Repeat until chips are melted and mix is smooth when stirred.
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Spread evenly into prepared pan.

title: baked party ham
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel skin from ham; trim fat.
Score ham in diamond pattern.
Insert cloves in cross pattern.
Pack brown sugar over ham.
Bake 30 minutes.
Heat pineapple juice and marmalade in pan over medium heat.
Remove from heat.
Add bourbon.
Remove ham from oven and pour pineapple sauce over ham. Bake 1 1/2 hours, basting frequently.

title: rolls
directions: Mix scalded milk and shortening together until melted. Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix all ingredients together adding enough flour until thick.
Knead until bread texture (10 minutes). Refrigerate overnight.
Roll into balls and let raise until doubled.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: tomato crisp
directions: Cut tomatoes
into
small wedges and put in large bowl. Mix 1/2
cup
sugar
and
spices
together
and
sprinkle over tomatoes.
Add
lemon
juice and toss well. Spread evenly into buttered 1 1/2 quart casserole. Blend remaining 1/2 cup sugar, flour, salt
and
butter into crumbs.
Mix in chopped nuts and sprinkle over
top
of
tomato
mixture.
Bake in oven at 350° about 35 minutes.

title: artichoke quiche
directions: Drain artichokes and save oil.
Beat eggs, add oil, artichokes and remaining ingredients.
Save some cheese for the top.
Put in a small baking pan and top with remaining cheese. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: custard mystery
directions: Beat to a cream and add beaten egg whites last to which has been added 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Put in baking dish and set in a dish of hot water.
Bake in moderate oven 30 minutes.

title: christmas morning eggs
directions: Remove crust from bread.
Cut bread into cubes.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Combine eggs and milk in a large bowl. Mix well.
Pour over bread.
Sprinkle with cheese, salt and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Heat oven to 350°. Sprinkle with bacon.
Bake for 1 hour.
Serve immediately.

title: spider legs
directions: Melt chips over low heat, add nuts and noodles and stir well. Drop teaspoons onto waxed paper.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: For filling, in a medium saucepan combine sugar, cornstarch and salt; gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Reduce heat; cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Separate egg yolks from whites; set whites aside for meringue.
Beat egg yolks slightly. Gradually stir 1 cup of the hot mixture into yolks.
Return egg mixture to saucepan; bring to a gentle boil.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more. Remove from heat.
Stir in butter or margarine, vanilla and 1 cup flaked coconut.
Pour hot filling into baked pastry shell.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix and place in greased casserole dish and bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cover to bake.

title: kernes' meat loaf
directions: Mix all, except tomato sauce, together well.
Place in greased baking dish.
Pour tomato sauce over top.
Cook at 350° until done.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute celery, onion and
pepper in one stick of butter. Add remainder of ingredients and mix until cheese melts.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Brown onion in melted margarine.
Add broccoli.
When broccoli is thawed, add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese balls
directions: Let all cheeses stand out at room temperature.
When soft, beat cheeses in mixer.
Add onion, Worcestershire sauce, mayonnaise and 1/4 cup pecans.
Mix well, then chill in refrigerator for 2 hours.
After chilled, form into ball.
Cover ball with parsley, remaining pecans and slices of olives.
Serve with party crackers.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and celery. Drain and mix with other ingredients.
Put in casserole dish and bake for 40 minutes at 325°.

title: spiced cider
directions: Put apple juice and cranberry juice in 30 cup percolator.
In percolator basket put sugar, cinnamon, cloves and salt.
Perk and serve.

title: white fudge cake
directions: In small saucepan, melt white chocolate and hot water over low heat; cool.
In large mixer bowl, combine flour, sugar, soda, baking powder, salt, butter, and buttermilk; blend at low speed until moistened.
Beat 1 minute at medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add eggs, melted white chocolate mixture, and vanilla.
Blend; beat 1 minute at medium speed.
Stir in pecans and coconut.
Pour batter into 2 (9 inch) round layer pans which have been greased and floured on the bottom only.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sugar-free strawberry pudding pie
directions: Cook pudding according to package directions.
Remove from heat.
Add dry jello and stir.
Let cool and thicken a few minutes.
Fold the strawberries into cool pudding mixture.
Pour into pie shell or graham cracker crust.
Chill and top with Cool Whip.

title: lasagna casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salted water. Drain!
Cook beef until brown. Stir in tomato sauce, sugar, salt, garlic salt and pepper. Remove from heat. Combine the cottage cheese, sour cream, cream cheese, green onions (chopped) and green pepper.
Spread half the noodles in two (2-inch deep) sheet pans. Moisten with some of the meat sauce. Cover with cheese mixture. Top with remaining noodles, then meat sauce. Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour. Serves 100.

title: crispy confections
directions: Combine caramels and water in a 4-cup glass measuring cup. Microwave at High 1 to 2 minutes; stir well to combine.
Combine the cereals and coconut in a large bowl; pour caramel mixture on top.
Toss well until coated.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper. Makes 4 dozen.

title: midnight cake with vanilla frosting
directions: Blend together Crisco and sugar until fluffy.
Blend in eggs. In a saucepan heat water and then slowly add cocoa, stir until smooth.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add to the Crisco/sugar mix, alternating with the cocoa mixture. Blend in vanilla and mix well.
Pour batter into an 8 x 8-inch square pan that has been greased and lined with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Let cool before frosting.

title: asparagus bacon quiche
directions: Line the unpricked pastry shell

with a double thickness of heavy-duty foil. Bake at 450° for 5 minutes; remove foil. Bake 5 minutes more. Remove from the oven and set aside. Cook asparagus in a small amount of water until crisp-tender, about 3 to 4 minutes. Drain well. Arrange the bacon and asparagus in the crust. In a bowl, beat eggs. Add cream, 1/2 cup cheese, onions, sugar, salt, pepper and nutmeg. Pour over asparagus. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes longer or until knife inserted near the center comes out clean. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: esther's pepper relish
directions: Chop or grind peppers.
Boil for 5 minutes.
But do not scald onions.
Add these after scalding; drain.
Add vinegar and sugar and onions.
Add salt.
Boil for 1/2 hour, stirring once in a while.
Seal in sterilized jars.

title: green pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.

title: party mix
directions: Combine cereals, pretzels and nuts in a large microwave cooking
bag.
Combine
margarine,	Worcestershire	sauce
and seasoned salt in a small bowl.
Microwave on High for 1 minute or until margarine is melted.	Pour over cereal mixture.
With bag open, microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Shake.
Microwave on High another 3 minutes.

title: tex mex chops
directions: Brown chops in large skillet in oil over medium heat, approximately 5 minutes.
Turn chops; add salsa and chiles. Lower heat; cover and simmer gently 8 to 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: cranberry bar cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl stir together the flour, oats, brown sugar and baking soda.
Stir in the margarine or butter and mix thoroughly.
Reserve 1 cup of the flour-oat mixture for the topping.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Grease a baking dish and place a row of potatoes in it and sprinkle with salt, pepper, flour and dot with butter.
Add a row of onions and sprinkle again.
Pour scalded milk over and last layer of potatoes and dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, covered.
We like to add a layer of thinly sliced ham!

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Mix together milk, salsa and soup.
In baking dish, layer tortilla strips, chicken and sauce; repeat layers.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: crab cakes
directions: Flake crabmeat into large bowl.
Add bread crumbs, lime juice, egg, Worcestershire, dill and scallions.
Mix well.
Shape into eight patties.
Refrigerate 30 minutes, until firm.
Melt butter in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Cook patties 4 to 5 minutes on each side, until browned.
Serve with lime wedges.

title: tropical punch
directions: (*Do not dilute frozen fruit juice.)

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.
Pour over cream cheese.
Serve with crackers.

title: lemon squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, cream together butter and 1/2 cup of confectioners sugar until fluffy.
Add 2 cups of flour.
Beat until blended.
Spread evenly over bottom of well greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
(It will be a little difficult to spread around but work with it.)
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello and water and then add other ingredients, except sour cream.
Do not drain fruit.
Jell half of the mixture in a pan.
When well set, spread sour cream on top.
Pour other half of jello over sour cream and jell until set.

title: chicken squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cream cheese and melted margarine until smooth.
Add chicken, salt, pepper, milk, chives or onions and pimento.
Mix well.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until silver knife comes out clean.

title: ham and glazed apples
directions: In
a
large
skillet,
melt
margarine until sizzling. Stir in brown sugar and Dijon mustard.
Add apples.
Cook over medium heat,
stirring
occasionally until apples are crispy-tender, about
5 to 7 minutes.
Place ham in the same skillet. Arrange apples
on the steak.
Cover.
Continue cooking until ham is heated through, 5 to 7 minutes.

title: strawberry fluff pie
directions: Combine strawberries and 1/4 cup sugar.
Stir in sour cream and lemon juice.
Beat egg whites with salt until foamy. Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold into strawberries-sour cream mixture.
Pile into baked pie shell. Freeze several hours or overnight.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: champagne salad
directions: For each serving, place crisp lettuce leaf on plate.
