On top of it, place upside down, 1 chilled pear half.
Make bunny with narrow end for face.
For eyes 2 raisins, for nose 1 red cinnamon candy, for ears 2 blanches almonds and for tail cottage cheese ball.
(Cute huh?)

title: russian tea
directions: Bring water to a boil and add cloves and cinnamon sticks. Cover and let stand 1/2 hour.
Remove spices and tea bags and add sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Add lemonade, orange juice and pineapple juice.
Mix well.
Makes approximately 1 1/2 gallons.

title: pepperidge farm chicken breasts
directions: Combine in flat bowl sour cream, onion soup mix and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir to blend.
Crush stuffing mix.
Dip chicken in sour cream mixture and then put in stuffing mix to coat.

title: japanese pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: quick banana pudding
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients until well blended; fold in Cool Whip.
Layer with pudding mix first, then wafers, bananas, then pudding mix until all used up.
Crush cookies and spread on top.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix well.
Pour into ice cream freezer; add milk up to line. Mix well and freeze in freezer.
(Very yummy.)

title: hamburg pie
directions: Saut onions in frypan. Cook the hamburg with onions. Add desired seasonings. Before putting in pie crust, add 2 tablespoons Bisquick. Beat eggs and cottage cheese together. Pour over the top and bake in moderate oven until done.

title: apple raisin bread
directions: Blend well
and pour into 2 greased bread pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat together potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla and melted butter.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Combine brown sugar, flour, soft butter and nuts.
Sprinkle on top of potato mixture. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fried okra
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour, salt and pepper.
Cut stems off okra and slice.
Coat okra in flour mixture.
Coat tomatoes and mix with okra.
Fry in hot skillet until golden brown.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Grease a Bundt pan.
Lay frozen rolls on the bottom.
(It looks meager, but don't put more or it will rise over pan edge.) Mix pudding, sugar and nuts; pour over frozen rolls.
Melt butter and pour over rolls and dry ingredients.
Cover with towel; leave it out overnight to rise by morning.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Invert and serve warm.

title: oriental chicken and rice
directions: Stir-fry chicken until done.

Meanwhile, for sauce, in a small saucepan, combine brown sugar and cornstarch. Stir in water, vinegar, soy sauce, bouillon, garlic powder and ground ginger. Add green pepper and pimento; cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat; keep warm.

title: italian wedding soup
directions: Heat chicken broth, cut up chicken, spinach and cooked meat balls.
Cook until spinach is done.
Add pasta and bring to boil. Boil 5 minutes.
Turn off heat.
Beat eggs and Parmesan cheese. Pour on top of soup.
Cover with lid.
Let sit for 10 minutes.

title: glenda's clam chowder
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients and liquid drained from clams. Cook until vegetables are tender.
Lower heat to low. Add clams and milk. Cook slowly 15 minutes.
Make roux of cornstarch or flour and water to thicken.
Cook until thickened on low.

title: fresh cranberry relish
directions: Rinse cranberries; drain.
Grind in blender all ingredients in the order listed.

title: hot pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers.
Combine vinegar and sugar.
Heat to a boil and add peppers and onions.
Cook 10 minutes.
Pack in jars.

title: cinnamon toast cobbler
directions: Drain peaches, reserving 1 cup syrup.
Combine cornstarch and salt; slowly blend in reserved syrup.
Cook and stir until mixture comes to boiling.
Reduce heat; cook and stir 2 minutes.
Add lemon juice, 1/4 cup butter and peaches.
Heat just to bubbling. Turn into a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Cut bread lengthwise into 1-inch strips; dip into 1/4 cup melted butter, then into a mixture of sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Arrange over peaches. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes, or until toasty.
Makes 6 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender; drain and mash well. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Cook 30 to 45 minutes at 375°. I usually use more squash and use 3/4 to 1 cup of other ingredients.

title: easy toffee(variations and substitutions are listed at the end.)
directions: Line a large cookie sheet with foil. Lay crackers on foil in a solid cover, crackers touching. Boil butter and brown sugar together for 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Pour over crackers, spreading to cover them all.

Bake at 400° for 5 to 7 minutes; do not allow sugar mixture to burn. Remove from oven and allow to sit about 3 minutes. Sprinkle chocolate chips evenly over candy and spread with a spatula or fork as chocolate begins to melt. Refrigerate. Chocolate will harden in about 30 minutes and candy can be broken into pieces (usually in 1 1/4-inch squares with a pizza cutter when candy just firms, for less crumbs).

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in a 3-quart dish.
Cover and microwave at High 4 minutes; stir well.
Return to microwave at High 7 to 9 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring once.

title: pepperidge chicken casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and bring to a boil 1 stick margarine and 2 cups stuffing mix.
Put margarine in baking dish and melt.
Put stuffing in melted margarine and stir well.
Take out 2/3 cup mixture and save for top.
Pour chicken mixture in baking dish. Spread remaining stuffing on top and bake 10 minutes at 425°.

title: seafood jubilee
directions: Boil fettucini as per instructions on box.
Melt butter in skillet.
Lightly saute scallops and shrimp in skillet and add Old Bay to taste.
Divide fettucini onto 2 platters and top with grated Mozzarella, shrimp and scallops; use pimento pieces for garnish. Hurry into preheated oven until cheese is melted.
Bon appetit!!

title: old fashioned blackberry cake
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, and eggs thoroughly. Sift together flour, soda, cloves, cinnamon, and allspice. Add sour milk to above and mix completely. Add blackberries and blend softly. May add nuts and raisins if desired, 1/2 c. each. Frost with a creamy caramel frosting. Use as a substitute for Jam Cake-- it is just as good.

title: easy homemade ice cream
directions: This recipe has been a family favorite for the Pace/Mueller families for the past 30 years.

title: bologna salad
directions: Grind all ingredients.
After grinding, add 2 tablespoons of dill vinegar.
Mix in salad dressing, to spreading consistency. Refrigerate.
(Tastes very much like ham salad.)

title: pioneer macaroni and cheese
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and pour over eggs and milk. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Garnish with parsley, pimiento strips and pepper rings.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and continue beating until fluffy. Add flour, soda, salt, baking powder and vanilla. Mix until well blended. Add rolled oats and drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet about 2-inches apart.
Bake until done (12 to 13 minutes) at 350°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together eggs, sugar, butter and buttermilk.
Add dry ingredients, crushed bananas, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: "more!" casserole
directions: Cook meat in shortening until it turns white.
Add onion, peppers (optional), salt, oregano, tomatoes, chili powder and vegetables.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions; drain and combine with meat mixture.
Spoon mixture into two 2-quart baking dishes and cover evenly with shredded cheese.
Bake covered at 350° for 45 minutes. Yields 9 to 12 servings.
Better made 24 to 36 hours before cooking to season.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Layer ingredients in bowl.
Sprinkle salt and pepper, then sprinkle hot sauce on top to taste.
Dip.

title: zucchini lasagna
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings.
Bring to boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Slice zucchini crosswise into 1/4-inch slices.
In small bowl combine cottage cheese and egg. In greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan, place half the zucchini and sprinkle with half the flour.
Top with cottage cheese mixture and half the meat mixture.
Repeat layer of zucchini and flour. Sprinkle with cheese and remaining meat mixture.
Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes or until heated through.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with additional cheese, if desired.
To cut more easily, let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: cranberry - banana bread
directions: Place cranberries in medium saucepan.
Cover and cook over medium heat 5 minutes or until cranberries begin to pop.
Uncover and remove from heat.
Combine sugar and oil in a medium bowl; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer 2 minutes or until well blended.
Add egg and egg whites; beat until light and lemon colored.
Combine dry ingredients;
add to creamed mixture alternately with bananas, mixing well after each addition.
Fold in cranberries.
Pour batter into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove from pan and let cool on wire rack.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into lightly greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix together water, sugar and yeast, then add to flour, egg and oil.
Pour into greased muffin pans.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 450°.

title: chex mix
directions: Combine Chex cereal, nuts, and pretzels in 13x9x2-inch baking pan. Set aside. Stir together remaining ingredients: gently stir into cereal mixture until evenly coated. Bake at 250 degrees about 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes. Spread on paper towels to cool. Makes about 8 cups.

title: chili dip
directions: Mix together and warm until cheese is melted.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and chips together.
Mix well. Pour over Rice Chex and mix well.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over and mix or shake to coat.

title: low calorie tomato juice dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients with mixer or blender.
Beat until well blended.
Refrigerate.
Makes 1 cup.
Contains 25 calories per tablespoon.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Place cream cheese and butter in a large mixing bowl.
Blend with an electric mixer on low speed until combined.
Stop the machine.
Add confectioners sugar, a bit at a time, blending with the mixer on low speed until the sugar is well incorporated.
Add the vanilla, then increase the mixer speed to medium and blend the frosting until fluffy.

title: glazed beef balls
directions: Heat ketchup, water and apple jelly.
Drop in meat balls. Make them small.
Simmer until done (about 45 minutes).
Turn balls after 20 minutes for even glazing.
Top with sour cream.

title: brownies
directions: Melt margarine in medium saucepan.
Add 1 box brown sugar and stir until dissolved.
Remove from stove.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and mix, then vanilla and nuts.
Mix well by hand. Pour in greased oblong pan.
Bake at 350° until done.
Let cool a while.
Cut into squares and roll in confectioners sugar until covered.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix squash and onion in large bowl. Mix all together. Place in large casserole. Top with 1/2 cheese, grated and mixed with 2 cups bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 12. Can do ahead.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add flavoring; mix well. Add coloring.
Mix well.
Put white sugar in mold.
Add approximately 1 teaspoon dough to mold, making it level.
Push out of mold onto wax paper, pretty side up.
Air dry 2 to 3 hours. Layer between wax paper and refrigerate or freeze until ready to use.

title: red rice
directions: Cook and break bacon into small pieces.
Put aside.
Cook tomatoes, onion, sugar and salt until heated.
Add rice.
Cover and cook until rice is tender.
Stir bacon pieces into rice and serve.

title: almond coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add flour and almond extract.
Line a 9-inch cake pan with foil.
Spread batter evenly.
Sprinkle almond slivers on top. Bake for approximately 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool.
Lift foil out of pan; peel away foil.

title: delicious brownies
directions: Combine the oleo and cocoa.
Add the remaining ingredients. Bake on a large cookie sheet at 350° for 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Ice with powdered sugar fudge frosting.

title: italian potato salad
directions: * More oil and vinegar may be added to taste once mixed.

title: crab cheese puff
directions: Mix ingredients together, except muffins.
Cut eight muffins in half; toast under broiler.
Spread thin layer of crab meat mixture on each muffin piece.
Put under broiler until spread starts to bubble.
Serve hot.
This is a great appetizer.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Spray 11 inch x 7 inch pan with Pam.
Spread blueberries on bottom.
Sprinkle lemon juice on berries.
In a small bowl, combine 3/4 c. sugar, flour, baking powder and salt.
Work butter into mixture until crumbly.
Add milk.
Mix with spatula.
Spread over berries.
Mix together cornstarch and 3/4 c. sugar.
Sprinkle over mixture.
Pour boiling water over mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate covered spiders
directions: Melt the chips in saucepan over low heat.
May add 1 tablespoon water, if necessary.
Stir in noodles, raisins or nuts carefully so as not to crunch the noodles.
Spoon onto wax paper. Cool and store in airtight container.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Stir soup until smooth.
Add milk and pepper. In buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole, alternate layers of potatoes, onion, sauce and cheese. Dot with butter. Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover. Bake at 375° for 1 hour. Uncover. Bake 15 more minutes.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients, except nuts.
Freeze in electric freezer for 20 minutes.
Add nuts and continue freezing until done.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add sugar.
Continue to beat until stiff.
Add chocolate bits and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Heat oven at 250° for 15 minutes.
Turn oven off; put cookies in oven and leave overnight.

title: chicken curry
directions: Mix in first five ingredients for sauce.
Boil chicken and cut into pieces.
Clean and cut broccoli or use frozen package, thawed.
Stir-fry broccoli.
Mix chicken, broccoli and sauce.
Top with cheese.
Bake for 1/2 hour in 9 x 12-inch pan at 375°.

title: my favorite pound cake
directions: All ingredients at room temperature.
Cream together Crisco, butter, eggs, vanilla and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add this to creamed mixture.
Now add milk gradually as needed.
Mix until batter is fluffy.
Bake at 350° in greased and floured tube pan for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: mustard barbeque sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and let come to a boil.
Store in glass quart jars with plastic tops to keep from corroding metal.
If you triple the recipe, it will be 2 quarts.

title: arkansas mudd
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Spread with Marshmallow Creme while still warm.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Beat egg whites and fold in.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: ham ball
directions: Blend deviled ham, olives, mustard and Tabasco.
Form in ball on serving dish.
Chill.
Combine cream cheese and milk and frost ball with mixture.
Keep chilled.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before serving time.
Trim with parsley.

title: taco casserole
directions: Top with chopped tomatoes, sliced green onions.

title: crazy corn
directions: Mix margarine, syrup, sugar and salt in large saucepan over low heat until melted.
Bring to boil.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and soda; mix well and pour mixture over popcorn.
Bake at 250° for 3/4 to 1 hour, stirring every fifteen minutes.

title: gumdrops
directions: Soak gelatin in 2 tablespoons of water.
Cook sugar and syrup until it reaches 280°.
Do not stir while cooking.
When it reaches 280° add gelatin and lemon juice.
Remove from heat. Divide the mixture into 3 parts.
Add food coloring and flavorings to each mixture.
Pour into square pan so that the depth of the gumdrops will be about 1-inch.
When firm, cut into squares or strips and roll in sugar.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Mix brown sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt in a 2-quart glass bowl and place in microwave on High until it boils.
Stir occasionally.
Boil mixture 2 minutes.
Add 1/2 teaspoon baking soda.
Spray a large grocery bag with Pam.
Put the popcorn in the bag and pour the caramel mixture over corn.
Fold down the top of the bag and shake well.
Place bag in microwave and cook on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove bag and shake well.
Place bag in microwave and cook another 1 1/2 minutes still on High setting. Take out and again, shake well.
Place bag one more time in microwave; cook on High for only 1/2 minute.
Place caramel corn on counter top or wax paper to cool.

title: cole slaw with dressing
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; bring to boil and season to taste. Pour while hot over salad of cabbage, carrots and onion.
Chill thoroughly before serving.

title: texas jalapeno grits
directions: Cook grits as labeled on box.
Add half the grits in a deep casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Mix sour cream and jalapenos together.
Add half of that on top of grits, then add half of each cheese. Repeat the same way again.
Finish on top with the cheeses. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
In a large pot, add all ingredients.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: baked beans
directions: Saute vegetables in margarine.
Add remaining ingredients, except pork and beans, bacon and pepper.
Cook on low 5 minutes. In a large mixing bowl, place pork and beans.
Add vegetable mixture and mix together well.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Stir in flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Add chips and nuts.
Stir.
Make out in balls and bake at 325° until lightly browned.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel and slice eggplants; flour first, then dip into egg batter, then dip them in bread crumbs.
Heat oil; fry eggplants on both sides.
Remove from pan and place them on absorbent paper toweling.
(This is to remove the excess oil.)

title: sausage balls
directions: Let cheese
and
sausage come to room temperature.
Mix all ingredients.
Form
into balls and bake in 350° oven until sausage is done and slightly brown.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together; cut in butter and Crisco until crumbly.
Stir in milk.

title: raisin pie
directions: Put raisins in a small pan and cover with water.
Let boil slow for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla. Mix sugar and flour together; then add to other mixture, adding buttermilk last.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Needs to cook slow so you may want to reduce heat to 350°.

title: vegetable bake dish
directions: In a quart casserole dish, mix all ingredients.
Sprinkle cheese and cracker crumbs over mixture.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 hour.

title: chicken pie
directions: Grease pan.
Take cooked chicken off bones and place in bottom of pan.
Heat and pour over chicken the cream of chicken soup and chicken broth mixed together.
Mix flour, milk, baking powder and melted margarine.
Pour over mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake 45 minutes at 425°.

title: milky way cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt 8 candy bars and 1 stick oleo in double boiler until smooth; set aside.
Cream sugar and 1 stick oleo; add eggs, one at a time, beating until smooth.
Add flour, buttermilk and soda.
Add Milky Way mixture, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan for 40 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pound cake
directions: Sift flour, then measure.
Add baking powder and salt.
Sift 5 or 6 times.
Cream the margarine and Crisco.
Add sugar.
Cream thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add flavoring and bake in a greased and floured pan for 1 hour and 25 minutes at 325°.

title: meat souffle
directions: Beat egg yolks; add meat, liquid, butter, salt and pepper. Fold in well beaten egg whites.
Bake in buttered pan for 1/2 hour in a moderate oven.
Turn out on hot platter and serve plain or with mushrooms or tomato sauce.

title: pepper steak
directions: Heat oil and add beef until red color disappears.
Add vegetables.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes while stirring.

title: cake doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs.
Add 1 cup sugar and melted Crisco.
Add 1 cup milk.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Combine dry and liquid ingredients, stirring, only until smooth.
Roll dough to about 1/2-inch thickness on a floured board.
Dough should be soft.
Cut with floured doughnut cutter.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
In large bowl, mix salad dressing and Salad Supreme.
Add vegetables and spaghetti; mix well.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: apple nut squares
directions: Beat together in medium size bowl the eggs, sugar and oil. Sift together and mix in the flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Fold in diced apples and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in lightly greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Can be topped with powdered sugar sprinkled lightly after baking.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake for 25 minutes.
Allow to cool 5 minutes.
To serve, cut with a pointed knife.

title: cereal bread
directions: Prepare cereal bread as directed, adding 1/2 cup raisins and 1/4 cup grated orange rind with the cereal and substituting 1/2 cup orange juice for 1/2 cup milk.
Bake about 1 hour and 5 minutes.

title: cream cheese and pecan danish
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Unfold pastry; roll to 15 x 10-inch rectangle.
Place in
15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.

title: creamy tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain.
Mix noodles, tuna, sour cream, milk, salt and pepper in a 2-quart casserole. Mix bread crumbs, cheese and margarine; sprinkle over tuna mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until hot and bubbly, 35 to 40 minutes.

title: quick muffins
directions: Drop from spoon into muffin pan.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: chocolate sauce 2
directions: Heat together chocolate and water in small saucepan over low heat until chocolate is melted.
Stir in sugar until smooth. Bring to boiling; boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and vanilla until butter is melted. Serve warm or at room temperature.
Sauce will thicken slightly on standing.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces.
Coat well with flour, salt and pepper.
Let stand in flour for 15 minutes.
Remove chicken from flour and soak in mixture of egg and milk for 15 minutes.
Roll in flour and deep fry in peanut oil; top with sauce, cashews and green onions.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients. Mix the remaining ingredients together and pour over salad. Mix well. Serve and enjoy.

title: banana punch slush
directions: Boil sugar and 6 cups of water and cool. Add orange juice, lemonade, pineapple juice, water and bananas. Freeze. Take out frozen mixture 3-4 hours before serving to make it slushy. Add ginger ale before serving.

title: lemon pie
directions: Thaw out lemonade.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into crust and refrigerate until well chilled.

title: korean barbecue sauce(kun koki)
directions: Mix
all ingredients, except chicken or meat.
Marinate boneless
chicken
or meat for 1 hour or more.
Broil, pan fry or charcoal.
Serves 6.

title: savory flank steak
directions: Sprinkle one side of flank steak with salt and pepper, parsley, garlic and cheese.
Roll steak up tightly, jelly roll fashion and secure with string.
Brown on all sides in shortening in large skillet or Dutch oven.

title: tropical salad
directions: Drain liquids from peaches and pineapple; add water to make 4 cups.
Drain liquid from Mandarin oranges, discard.
Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups liquid, heated to boil.
Add remaining 2 cups liquid and fruits.
Pour into 3-quart Pyrex dish or individual molds.
Garnish with orange slice and touch of mint or Cool Whip.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and salt until frothy.
Gradually beat in milk, vanilla and nutmeg.
Sprinkle more nutmeg on top.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Beat together the oil and sugar.
Add the eggs and bananas. Beat well.
Sift together the dry ingredients.
Add to banana mixture with buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir in nuts. Pour in greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
Makes 12 to 15 muffins.

title: frozen fruit slush
directions: Boil water and sugar for 5 minutes and cool.
Add rest of ingredients and freeze.
Eat when slightly frozen.

title: baked round steak
directions: Cut meat into serving size pieces.
Roll pieces in flour.
Fry in vegetable oil in pan until brown.
Season with salt and pepper. Put meat in small roaster.
Add flour to drippings in frypan to make gravy.
Add water if not right consistency.
Pour gravy over the meat pieces in the roaster.
Slice 1 large onion and place in roaster.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours and then serve.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve the Jell-O with 1 cup boiling water. Add the strawberry juice, pineapple, strawberries and bananas.
Pour half of the mixture in dish. Allow to gel. Spread sour cream.
Pour remaining mixture and refrigerate.

title: kyenam(african fish dish)
directions: Soak bay leaves, peppercorns and cloves in 1/3 cup of oil overnight.
Rub cleaned fish with salt and black pepper and then the flavored oil.
Bake in a hot pan or in the oven or grill on a charcoal fire.
Then fry onion, tomatoes, tomato paste and red hot pepper in the rest of the oil.
Add dried shrimp or anchovy. Place the cooked fish on a bed of plain, boiled rice and coat with the tomato, onion and pepper sauce.
Decorate with French-fried onions, sliced green peppers, fried plaintain, sliced hard-boiled eggs, etc.
Serves 4.

title: homemade baked beans
directions: Mix the beans, brown sugar and catsup.
Put the bacon across the top of the beans in a baking dish.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: pioneer stew
directions: Cook beef, onion and green pepper until meat is browned and vegetables are tender.
Drain corn, beans and tomatoes.
Add liquids, chili powder and salt to meat and cook until liquid is reduced to about half.
Add corn, beans and tomatoes.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in cheese and serve.

title: fruity banana pudding
directions: In oblong baking dish, layer cookies. Slice bananas on top of cookies. Slice strawberries on top of bananas. Mix pudding as directed on box and pour over fruit. Repeat layers and sprinkle remaining (crush) cookies on top.

title: breakfast muffins
directions: Combine 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon. Set aside. In a bowl, stir together flour, 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder, nutmeg and salt. In another bowl, combine egg, milk and 1/3 cup melted butter. Add to flour mixture. Stir until moistened. Fill greased muffin pan (or line with baking cups) 2/3 full. Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Immediately dip tops into 3 tablespoons melted butter, then dip or sprinkle tops in cinnamon-sugar mixture.

title: breakfast rolls
directions: Split dinner rolls in half lengthwise.
Butter bottom half. Layer shaved ham over bottom.
Top with single layer of Swiss cheese, then single layer of American cheese.
Replace top. Combine melted margarine and poppy seed.
Pour over top.
Cut individual rolls apart.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate overnight. Next, morning, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy orange sherbet salad
directions: Pour boiling water over jello in large bowl to dissolve well. Add softened sherbet and Cool Whip.
Mix well with beater or in a mixer.
Add crushed pineapple and oranges.
Place in a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Cool until set and serve.
(Makes a large amount.)

title: carrot saute
directions: To capture the true, sweet flavor of carrots, melt butter or margarine in a heavy skillet.
Add carrots.
Sprinkle with a little salt.
Stir and cover.
Cook over medium heat (only about 5 minutes).
Stir a time or two and replace lid quickly.
Serve at once.
Test for doneness.

title: easy salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate for several hours.
Makes a large salad.

title: tortilla cheese canapes
directions: Spread all ingredients on tortillas one at a time.
Roll and chill overnight.
Slice crosswise in 1/2-inch slices.

title: beef and potato casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion together.
Place in a 9 x 13 inch cake pan.
Top with generous amount of potato rounds, sliced about 1/2 inch thick.
Add 1 can of water to the 2 cans of mushroom soup and mix well; pour over potatoes.
Salt generously and bake, covered, 1 hour at 375°.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Pound chicken until thin.
Combine eggs, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in egg mixture and then in bread crumbs.
Brown quickly in oil.
Drain chicken and put in casserole pan.
While chicken is cooking, stir tomato sauce, basil and garlic.
Heat to boiling. Simmer 10 minutes.
Add margarine.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Cover.
Cook 1/2 hour at 350°.
Uncover and put Mozzarella cheese on top; bake until cheese melts (approximately 5 minutes).
Serve with side of spaghetti.

title: meatballs and sauce
directions: Mix first ten ingredients together for meatballs.
Shape into balls, roll in flour and fry in skillet until brown on both sides. Remove and place in baking dish.

title: favorite salad
directions: Drain tomatoes.
Save juice. Add water to make 2 cups.
Heat 1 cup to boiling. Stir in Jell-O. Add the other cup when cool. Mix tomatoes and cottage cheese. Add to gelatin mixture.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crusts from bread and spread with margarine.
Place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish and set aside.
Cook sausage until browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain well.
Spoon over bread slices.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine eggs, half and half and salt; mix well and pour over cheese.
Cover casserole and chill overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking. Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, mix first 4 ingredients, then add rest. Grease and flour 2 bread loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: make-ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add cream cheese, salt and pepper, mixing well.
Put in greased two-quart casserole.
Top with pats of butter.
Cover.
Potatoes may be stored in refrigerator for several days.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix well.
Roll about the size of a quarter.
Put on cookie sheet and bake in a 250° to 275° oven.
These may be made ahead of time.
Roll out, put on cookie sheet and freeze.
When frozen, put in a Ziploc bag and return to freezer.
Take out as needed and cook by directions.

title: creamy vanilla pudding
directions: Combine cornstarch and sugar; stir in milk.
Cook in microwave on High for 7 minutes.
Beat half of the hot mixture into the eggs. Blend egg mixture into remaining hot mixture.
Microwave 2 1/2 minutes or until thickened.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Can use in banana or pineapple pudding recipe.

title: cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line a 9-inch spring-mold pan with any graham cracker crust recipe off box.
Beat above ingredients with mixer in order listed.
Bake in spring-mold pan for 45 minutes. After 45 minutes, turn oven off and leave in for 2 hours. Do not open oven door throughout this process.

title: icebox cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla, eggs, Nestle cream and rum.
Throw off excess water from cream after chilling.
Take 1/3 of mixture, mix with peaches or fruit cocktail.
Dice cake; place 1/2 layer on bottom of dish.
Pour fruit on top of cake.
Add rest of cake on top.
Pour rest of cream on top of cake.
Garnish with cherries or crushed nuts.
Place in refrigerator to chill and serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar and oil, mix together.
Add remaining dry ingredients.
Add zucchini; mix.
Pour into 2 greased bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: barb taft's pistachio salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and pudding together.
Drain pineapple, then add it.
Add nuts and marshmallows.

title: diane's texas grits
directions: Bring water to boil; add grits.
Slow boil for 10 minutes. Add butter.
Beat eggs; stir in slowly.
Add Mexican Velveeta; mix and mix.
Pour into shallow baking pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until brown on top.

title: cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into chocolate pie shell.
Cover with cherry pie filling or sweetened berries.
Refrigerate.
It's easy!

title: pineapple banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs and beat well. Add bananas, crushed pineapple and nuts, then mix well.
Sift flour, soda and salt; mix with egg-fat mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 1 large or 2 small loaves.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat soup; add cream cheese.
Continue heating until melted. Remove from heat.
Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water and combine the gelatin mixture with tomato soup
mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into lightly greased ring mold. Chill overnight.
Unmold and serve with Ritz crackers.

title: layered nacho dip
directions: Combine sour cream and taco seasoning.
Starting with beans, layer ingredients in order listed.
Serve with nacho cheese or corn chips.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well.
Boil until a bit dropped in cold water forms a firm ball.
Dissolve the baking soda in hot water and butter.
Pour over the popped corn (already popped and which the unpopped kernels have been removed).
Stir well; form into balls.

title: oven steak supper
directions: Place meat in center of 3-foot length of aluminum foil. Sprinkle meat with soup mix.
Cover with vegetables.
Dot with butter; sprinkle with salt.
Fold foil and seal securely to hold in juices.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake in a 450° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: twinkie surprise
directions: Layer split Twinkies in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Slice bananas and layer over Twinkies. Mix milk with pudding; spread over bananas. Spread pineapple over pudding. Top with Cool Whip and cherries. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.

title: pickled green beans
directions: Wash, drain and cut up beans.
Pack beans, lengthwise, into jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
To each pint, add 1/4 teaspoon cayenne pepper, 1 clove garlic and 1 head dill.
Combine remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Pour boiling hot water over beans, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Adjust lids.
Process 10 minutes in boiling water bath.
Yields about 4 pints.

title: tater tots casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Bake Tater Tots in 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Grease casserole dish and add Tater Tots, ground beef and mushroom soup; mix well.
Top with cheese.
Cover with foil. Bake for 30 to 45 minutes until bubbly.
Quick dinner and easy.

title: 24 hour coleslaw
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl and refrigerate at least 24 hours before using.
Keeps well in refrigerator for at least two weeks.

title: party mix
directions: *Cook pecans with very small amount of margarine in a 350 oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Watch closely so they won't get too done.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake yellow cake mix as directed on box in a 9x13 pan.
Let cool then crumble half cake in a punch bowl.
Prepare pudding according to box.
Layer on top of cake with half of the cherry pie filling, half of the pudding, half of the pineapple, half of the bananas, and half of the cool whip.
Repeat layers starting with the cake.
Garnish with chopped pecans, coconut and cherries.

title: spinach cauliflower toss
directions: In a small frying pan, toast nuts over medium heat, shaking pan often, until nuts are golden (3-5 minutes). Set aside.

title: scalloped chicken and oyster dressing
directions: Cook chicken in water until done, about 1 hour. Cool. Remove meat from bones.

title: fried potatoes and onions
directions: Cover and fry potatoes in small amount of Wesson oil until tender.
Just before they start to brown, add the diced onion. Cover and leave covered for about 5 minutes.
Then uncover;
turn heat up to lightly brown potatoes and onion.

title: rhubarb crumble
directions: Mix together; press 1/2 in 9-inch pie plate.
Save remaining for top.

title: york sensational brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
(If using a glass pan, heat to 325°.) Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
In a large bowl with spoon or wire whisk, stir together butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs. Stir until well blended.
Stir in flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt and blend well.
Reserve 2 cups batter.
Spread remaining batter in prepared pan.
Arrange peppermint patties in single layer over batter, about 1/2-inch apart.
Spread reserved 2 cups of batter over patties.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan.
Cool completely in pan on wire rack.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 36 brownies.

title: alaska snow crab louis dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except crab.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve with crab.
Makes 1 2/3 cups.

title: fresh apple cake with butterscotch chips
directions: Mix apples, sugar and eggs together.
Add oil, nuts, flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Mix until well blended, then add butterscotch chips.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: brisket of beef
directions: Lay brisket in roasting pan.
Mix soup and water together. Pour half over meat. Add potatoes and carrots in pan with roast. Pour the rest of the soup over veggies.
Cover tightly with foil. Bake in slow oven at 250° to 275° for 6 to 8 hours.

title: goobers
directions: Cream together the peanut butter and butter. Add the powdered sugar. (May add a few drops of water if needed.) Roll into round balls and place on cookie sheet. Yields 50 to 60.

title: pineapple muffins
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Blend in sugar and wheat germ.
Combine egg, oil and pineapple and add to flour mixture.
Stir only until moistened.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° approximately 20 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream the Crisco.
Add sugar; continue creaming.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add vanilla, then the sifted dry ingredients alternately with the milk.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes in a large angel food pan at 325°.

title: 7 layer 24 hour salad
directions: Arrange in layers in clear salad bowl.
Start with spinach. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and 1 teaspoon of sugar.
Add layers of bacon and eggs.
Then add lettuce.
Sprinkle again with salt, pepper and 1 teaspoon of sugar.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix all together except beef gravy and form into 20 patties. Line pan with foil.
Put patties on foil and cover with foil. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
When done, drain off grease and pour beef gravy over patties.
Leave in oven, uncovered, long enough to warm.

title: holiday cherry cakes
directions: Add sugar and butter; add eggs, then flour and lemon.
Pour on a greased pan; mark off 20 servings.
Put pie filling in center of each section.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch cookie sheet.

title: hot and sour soup
directions: In 2-quart saucepan (medium-high heat), heat broth, olives, tofu and green onions.
Blend cornstarch with water until smooth; stir into broth gradually.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Remove from heat.
Slowly pour beaten egg into soup while stirring gently in one direction.
Stir in remaining ingredients before serving.
Serves 4.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add crushed pretzels and 1 tablespoon of sugar.
Spread in glass baking dish.
Bake for 10 minutes at 250°. Let cool.

title: american goulash
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions and drain well. Brown meat, onion and pepper.
Add cooked and drained macaroni, seasonings, tomatoes and tomato soup.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Mix crumbs with melted margarine and sprinkle over top.
Grate cheese over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: kraut
directions: Put 1 teaspoon salt in bottom of quart jar.
Fill with cut cabbage.
On top of cabbage, put 1 teaspoon salt, 1 teaspoon sugar and 1 teaspoon vinegar.
Fill jar until cabbage is covered.
Seal tight.
Let stand for a few weeks.
Jar may leak a bit the first week or so.

title: grandma's tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternating with buttermilk.
Mix well.
Add extract and mix thoroughly.
Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness on a floured surface.
Cut with a 2 1/2-inch round cookie cutter. Place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until edges begin to brown.
Sprinkle with sugar if desired. Cool.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: wedding punch
directions: Add few drops of food coloring, if desired, to make any color you want.
Pour over an ice ring.
Serves 50.

title: tahitian punch
directions: In large bowl, mix juices; drop in sherbet by spoonfuls.
Add beverage and mix a little, then serve.

title: red hot jello salad
directions: Melt red hots in 2 cups water.
Add dry Jell-O and applesauce. Chill until set.

title: heavenly hash browns
directions: Mix all ingredients in greased casserole. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients until crumbly and put in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Pour this mixture over first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sticky buns
directions: Tear one loaf thawed bread into irregular pieces and place in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle the mixture of brown sugar, pudding, butter and cinnamon over the bread pieces.
Tear up the second loaf of thawed bread and layer on top.
Cover with a wet towel and let rise about four hours.
Bake at 350 for 30 minutes. Turn upside down immediately.
Nuts and raisins may be added with the brown sugar layer.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add sour cream and vanilla; mix well.
Add rest of batter ingredients and mix until very smooth.
Pour half of the batter in greased tube pan. Sprinkle half of the filling mixture on top of batter.
Pour rest of batter over filling mixture and top with rest of filling.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine 1 cup mashed strawberries with 1 cup water in a saucepan.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Add 1 cup sugar and the cornstarch which has been dissolved in the 1/3 cup water.
Boil until mixture turns clear, approximately 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
At this time, 4 drops of red food coloring may be added, if desired. Cool glaze.
Add remaining berries to glaze and toss gently to coat.
Arrange in pie shell and refrigerate.
Garnish with whipped cream before serving.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits according to directions on the box.
Add the cheese, margarine, seasoned salt and Tabasco.
Stir until cheese and margarine are melted.
Add 3 beaten eggs.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: banana split cake
directions: In a mixing bowl toss together the graham cracker crumbs and the melted 1/2 cup butter.
Press crumb mixture onto bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In a small bowl beat the remaining 1/2 cup butter about 30 seconds until softened.
Add powdered sugar; beat until fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Spread egg mixture over crumb mixture.
Slice bananas lengthwise into halves and arrange over egg mixture.
Spoon pineapple over bananas.
Spread Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.
Cover; refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop ham into small squares.
Chop the green stems of onion. Mix with cream cheese.
Roll into a ball.
(Optional:
Roll in chopped nuts.)
Serve with crackers.

title: turkey in a sack
directions: Spread turkey heavily with mayonnaise using pastry brush. Place in brown bag.
Fasten bag ends together.
Place bag on rack in pan.
Bake at 325° until done.
Chicken or small birds may be used instead of turkey.
Split sack containing bird.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: white sangria
directions: Mix together and serve cold.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix together and shape into balls (size of large marble). Brown; pour sauce over meatballs in large casserole dish.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Melt butter and add cracker crumbs. Reserve 1/2 cup. Grease 2-quart casserole dish. Add grated zucchini, onion, egg, garlic powder, cheese, salt, pepper and unreserved cracker crumbs and butter. Mix well. Top with the reserved 1/2 cup cracker crumbs and butter. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease 2-quart casserole. Pour mixture into casserole and top with buttered croutons. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: overnight breakfast casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole in the following order:
bread cubes, cooked sausage, green peppers and cheese.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over layers.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: salmon divan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, over low heat, melt butter.
Blend in flour, onion powder and sugar.
Mix until smooth. Cook and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Gradually add half and half, stirring until smooth with each addition.
Cook and stir over medium to high heat until sauce just comes to a boil and is thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sherry.

title: layered dip
directions: Spread beans on shallow pan or dish.
Combine sour cream and salad dressing mix and spread over beans.
Add layers of tomatoes, chilies, ripe olives, shredded cheese and avocado, if desired. Serve with thick corn chips.

title: chocolate mint brownies
directions: Combine chocolate and butter; cook over low heat until melted, stirring constantly.
Let stand 10 minutes.
In bowl, beat eggs with electric mixer.
Gradually add sugar and beat well.
In separate bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add chocolate mixture and flour mixture to eggs and sugar.
Stir in chopped pecans and vanilla.
Spoon into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until pick comes out clean.
Let cool for 10 minutes.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Cook seasoning in butter until transparent.
Add soup and water.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes. Add salt and peppers and crawfish tails.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Add green onions to it before eating each time.
This will add color for looks and seasoning.
The Etouffee is better if cooked a day before the planned meal.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Place layer of jalapeno and Cheddar cheese dip into center of serving plate and spread almost to edge of plate.
Mix taco seasoning and mayonnaise together.
Place on top of first layer. Place shredded lettuce around outside of platter.
Place all remaining chopped vegetables on top of cheese mixture.
Place shredded pepper cheese on top of everything. Now serve with nacho chips and enjoy.

title: play dough
directions: Mix in a medium pot the first 3 ingredients.
Combine and add remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat and stir (about 3 to 5 minutes).
It will look like a "globby" mess and you'll be sure it's not turning out, but it will.
When it forms a ball in the center of the pot, turn out and knead on the lightly floured surface.
Store in an airtight container or plastic bag.

title: salami bread sticks
directions: Spread cream cheese in middle of salami slice.
Roll around bread stick.
Cut sticks in smaller sizes after rolled.
Do this just before you serve or bread sticks will become soggy.

title: chunky spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook beef and onions. Drain off fat. Combine in 2-quart saucepan with juice from drained tomatoes and spices. Bring to boil, then simmer 20 minutes. Add tomatoes and paste. Bring to boiling; serve over spaghetti.

title: texas torte (or mexican fudge)
directions: Beat eggs.
Add flour, salt and milk; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Pour into greased 8 x 12-inch Pyrex dish. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: love balls
directions: Mix coconut and milk together. Roll into balls, then roll in dry, small box of Jell-O.
Place in an airtight container and refrigerate.

title: chocolate skillet torte
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Line a 10 inch iron skillet with aluminum foil, allowing extra foil to hang over edges. This will be used later for removing torte from skillet.
Cream together the butter, 3/4 c. sugar,
brown sugar, and cocoa. Add eggs and beat well.

Gradually add flour and then add almond extract, mixing well. Pour into foil-lined skillet. Sprinkle almonds over top of batter and then sprinkle the 1 tablespoon sugar over the top. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean when inserted into center of torte.

Do not overbake. This should have the texture of a brownie. Remove from oven and then remove torte from skillet, using the foil. Do not remove the foil while torte is still warm. Melt the vanilla chips with 1 tsp. shortening. Drizzle over torte. Melt the chocolate chips with 1 tsp. shortening and drizzle over torte. When cool, remove foil carefully and plate.

title: waffles
directions: Add soda to eggs and buttermilk.
Add dry ingredients which are sifted together.
Add melted butter.
Beat until smooth.

title: corn casserole dish(serves 6 or 8 people)
directions: Combine all these ingredients together and bake for 30 minutes in the oven at 350°.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Top with 1/4 cup fine bread crumbs, mixed with 1 tablespoon of melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Good as side dish for prime rib.

title: caramel bars
directions: Roll out cookie dough.
Pat out dough in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes at 350°.
While warm, put morsels over the cookie dough.
Put back into oven for 5 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan; heat to a slow boil. Cool and store in Ziploc bag and freeze. The sauce will not totally freeze, so you can take out as much as you need.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together; cut in shortening or butter until mixture resembles coarse corn meal.
Add milk and mix briefly or until dry ingredients are moistened.
Place on a floured board and knead gently about 10 times; roll out to about 1/2-inch thickness.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 450° for about 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield: 2 dozen biscuits.

title: tuna-macaroni toss
directions: In a 5-quart saucepot, cook macaroni as directed; drain. Return to saucepot; keep warm.
Meanwhile, in 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, melt butter or oleo.
Add onion and cook until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in flour until blended; cook 1 minute.
Gradually stir in milk, bouillon, salt and pepper. Cook until thickened and smooth, stirring constantly.
Stir in tuna and heat through.
Gently toss macaroni in saucepot with tuna mixture.
Spoon mixture into warm bowl; garnish with parsley.

title: sausage
directions: First, cut it, cut it, cut it.
Then you cook it long, long. Then you eat it.

title: busy woman's dream
directions: Crumble raw beef in bottom of 10 x 10-inch casserole dish. Spread soup evenly over top of meat.
Place Tater Tots on top. Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly and Tater Tots are brown.

title: haddock delmonico
directions: Place serving portions of fish in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch greased baking dish.
Combine margarine, lemon, onion and seasonings and pour over fish.
Cook until fish flakes at 350° (approximately 25 minutes).
Remove serving portion onto plate and top with melted cranberry sauce, garnished with parsley.

title: fruit salad
directions: Save juice from the fruit.
Add water to make 3 cups.
Put juice and water in pan and add pudding mixes.
Cook until thick. Set off stove and cool for 20 to 30 minutes.
Stir 1 time.
Pour over fruit and chill.

title: hobo dish
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Crumble hamburger on bottom of greased casserole dish.
Add salt and pepper.
Layer potatoes, carrots, onions and celery.
Combine water with soup and pour over vegetables.
Bake at 375° for 1 to 2 hours.

title: impossible chicken pie
directions: Lightly grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Sprinkle chicken, mushrooms, onion, salt and cheese in pan.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour in pan.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Mix until smooth sugar, salt, egg and Crisco.
Dissolve yeast powders in warm water.
Add to first mixture.
Then add plain flour.
Knead until smooth.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours or until yeast rises.
Knead and cut with biscuit cutter. Put in greased pan and let rise 45 minutes.
Bake at 450° until done.

title: baked green beans
directions: Mix together all ingredients and put into baking dish, approximately 8 x 8-inch size.
Cut 4 strips bacon into pieces. Lay on top of bean mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered, and then 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: shrimp appetizers
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in Cheez Whiz until fairly smooth.
Mix in garlic and mayonnaise.
Fold in shrimp.
Spread on English muffins.
Freeze until firm (about 1 1/2 hours).
Cut each muffin in eighths.
Place in freezer container and keep in freezer.

title: easy cinnamon rolls
directions: Roll dough into 9 x 12-inch rectangle.
Spread with margarine and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Spread chopped apples, raisins and pecans over dough.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Cut into one-inch slices.
Place on oiled baking sheet and let rise until nearly doubled in size.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes or until done. Calories: 183.

title: oven chicken and pasta
directions: Melt butter in a 10 x 15-inch baking dish in a 400° oven. Stir in onion, garlic, basil and pepper.
Place chicken in butter mixture; then turn over.
Bake until chicken is done, about 45 minutes.

title: pat-in-pan pie crust(no rolling!)
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour, sugar and salt; add oil and milk.
Blend well.
Pat into 9-inch pie pan, fluting edges if desired.
For baked pie crust, bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes to fill with desired filling and bake as filling recipe requires.

title: glaze for fresh raspberry or strawberry pie
directions: Combine the water, sugar, cornstarch and gelatin in a saucepan; bring to a boil and cook until thickened.
Cool.
Pour glaze over fruit in pie shell and chill.

title: butterscotch chews
directions: Melt butter; add sugar, eggs and dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Place in a greased pan (about 8 x 10-inch).
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with 4x sugar while warm.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Break the crackers into small pieces and place in a medium bowl.
Drain the juices from the salmon over the crackers and toss.
Add the salmon to the bowl with the crackers.
Add the eggs, onion, pepper and salt.
Toss to combine.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat together the sugar, syrup, salt, flour and eggs.
Add vanilla, nuts and butter.
Pour into a 9-inch deep dish unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: portobello mushrooms
directions: Combine tomatoes, cheese, 1/2 teaspoon oil, rosemary, pepper and garlic in small bowl.

title: sausage cheese quiche
directions: Cube bread into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put sausage on top of bread. Sprinkle with cheese.
Beat eggs and 2 1/4 cups milk and pour over cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, mix 1/2 cup milk with mushroom soup and pour over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: spicy pecan muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, combine dry ingredients including nuts.
In a smaller bowl, combine liquid ingredients.
Add liquid to dry and mix only until moistened throughout.
Spoon batter into lined muffin cups.
Bake 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: In skillet, combine browned beef and spices with tomatoes in skillet.
Heat through.
Cover bottom and sides of 13 x 9-inch baking dish with tortillas.
Pour beef mixture over tortillas. Place a layer of tortillas over beef mixture.
Combine cottage cheese and Jack cheese; pour over tortillas.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with remaining ingredients over top.
Serve with sour cream and salsa if desired.

title: haystacks candy
directions: Melt peanut butter and butterscotch chips.
Mix in noodles and nuts; coat well.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Place in refrigerator to chill.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well.
Add eggs and zucchini. Sift together the dry ingredients and add.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken soup
directions: Wash and clean chicken backs and gizzards, leaving fat on backs.
Split backs in half.
In a large pot, cook for 45 minutes the chicken backs, gizzards, celery, onions, green pepper, potatoes, salt, pepper, garlic powder, carrots and water.
Add the remaining ingredients after the mixture cooks.
Okra may be omitted if you dislike it.
Cook for another 15 minutes.
Serve in bowl or cups.
Soup will be thick like a stew.
Good with corn bread or crackers.
Good hearty eating.
Enjoy!

title: chess pie
directions: Cook at 350° until done.

title: ladyfinger cake
directions: Line 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan with ladyfingers.
Do not pull each one apart.
Line up in sheets (single sheets).
Line the sides first and then the bottom filling in the large cracks.

title: no salt oven-baked chicken
directions: Spray an oven pan with Pam.
Place chicken breasts in pan. Mix the vegetables with the cream of mushroom soup.
Sprinkle Mrs. Dash and Parmesan cheese over all.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until juices run clear.

title: alabama shrimp creole
directions: Cook all ingredients, except spices and shrimp, in oil for 5 minutes.
Add 1 cup of water and cook down for 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, except shrimp; cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes.
Add water, if needed.
Add shrimp and cook 20 minutes longer.
Serve over cooked long grain rice.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix first four ingredients together in a saucepan.
Will be thick.
Add 2 cups water.
Cook to full boil.
Cool for 5 minutes.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Whip until fluffy. Gradually add milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust. Chill before garnishing top with pie filling.

title: cherry gelatin-cranberry salad
directions: Cook together the water and cranberries.
When soft, add sugar and cook 5 minutes.
Pour mixture over gelatin.
Let cool.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into mold.
Chill well.

title: salmon fritters
directions: Pour juice of salmon into measuring cup.
Set aside.
Put drained salmon into mixing bowl.
Add 1 egg; use fork to break up salmon, taking out bone.
Mix real well.
When gummy, add flour and mix well with fork.
May add pepper.
Take 1/4 cup of salmon juice and add 1 heaping teaspoon baking powder to juice; beat with fork.
It will foam.
After foaming, add to salmon mixture.
Mix well (it will be thin).

title: jerry's lemon garlic chicken
directions: Pour 1/4 cup oil into 9 x 13 x 2-inch Pyrex baking dish.
Flour and salt chicken pieces and place the pieces, skin side down, in a single layer.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.
Turn chicken and pour sauce over chicken.
To make sauce, use the 1/4 cup olive oil and add all other ingredients to it.
Bake another 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: barbecue seasoning
directions: Saute onions until brown. Combine all ingredients in large pot and bring to a simmer. Do not boil. Makes about 2 quarts. Keep in refrigerator up to 10 weeks.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix and put in punch bowl; add ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: banana crunch cake
directions: Blend eggs, sour cream, bananas and yellow cake mix for 2 minutes.
In a separate bowl, mix oleo, frosting and rolled oats together for the filling.

title: jay's cheese ball
directions: Put all ingredients in large bowl and mix well with both hands.
Form into ball and roll in chopped pecans.
This recipe makes two cheese balls.

title: dandelion with bacon dressing
directions: Wash greens thoroughly.
Cook in small amount of salted water until tender and drain well.
Chop if leaves are large.
Add onions.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove and set aside.
To bacon drippings, add vinegar, mustard, sugar, salt and pepper to taste. Add to hot vegetables.
Garnish with egg slices and reserved bacon, crumbled.
Serves 4.

title: cabbage skillet
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add cabbage, onion and tomato sauce.
Add 2 cans of water.
Add garlic, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves approximately 5.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix together rice, green pepper and onion.
Put in glass baking pan (with a lid).
Place chicken on top of rice, pour all soup on top of chicken.
Add salt and pepper, if desired.
Cover and cook at 375° in oven until chicken is done (about 1 1/2 hours).

title: garlic pretzels
directions: Mix first three ingredients, put broken pretzels in bowl and pour oil mixture over the pretzels.
Soak 10 minutes, then stir often.
Pour on a cookie sheet and bake for 5 minutes at 325°.

title: make ahead pie dough
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening with pastry knife until it resembles cornmeal.
Combine egg, vinegar and water in a bowl.
Stir into flour mixture.
Divide dough into 4 equal parts. Shape into balls.
Wrap tightly and chill.
May be frozen for 1 week in refrigerator.

title: pita bread
directions: In mixing bowl, combine warm water, yeast, sugar, salt and olive oil.
Mix well.
Gradually work in enough flour to make a soft dough that leaves the sides of the bowl and does not stick to hands.
Turn onto a lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover and let set 20 minutes. Shape dough into balls about the size of oranges and flatten slightly.
Place the balls on floured surface and keep covered with a dish towel to prevent dough from drying.
Let set 5 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: In a shallow casserole dish, combine fruit, sugar, 1 tablespoon flour and cinnamon.
In a medium bowl, mix 2/3 cup flour, baking powder and brown sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture is the size of small peas.
Stir in milk until moistened; add more if necessary.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto fruit.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted into crust comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: flaming toilet paper
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Blend soup, milk and chili powder in saucepan.
Crush chips.

title: charlotte's cheese bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/2 cup of cheese and butter. Spread in 8 or 9-inch greased dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Pour butter over cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: fast and easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 12 to 16 cookies.

title: quiche divan
directions: Place broccoli in the bottom of the pastry shell.
Cover with chicken and cheese.
Beat together eggs, cream, salt and pepper. Pour over the broccoli, chicken and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean. Cool slightly before serving.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix beans, soup and mayonnaise; pour into casserole dish. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and almonds.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and brown on top.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into 2 greased bread pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°; glass pans, bake at 325°.

title: banana split pudding
directions: In a bowl, whisk milk and pudding mix for 2 minutes.
Add banana, strawberries and pineapple.
Dollop with whipped topping. Drizzle with chocolate syrup, sprinkle with pecans.
Top with strawberries and bananas.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Peel, chop and core apples.
Fill crock-pot with apples. Sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon, salt and cloves.
Cook on high for 12 hours or to desired thickness.
Yields 4 cups.

title: swedish rye bread
directions: Pour boiling water over molasses, oatmeal, brown sugar and shortening.
Mix well and let stand until lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Mix together.
Gradually add flour, rye flour and salt.
Knead well.
Let rise in warm place.
Form into 2 loaves.
Let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve proudly.

title: chili
directions: Ground beef with onion, celery, green pepper, salt and pepper, then add remaining ingredients and bake at 300° for two hours.

title: wassail
directions: Heat cider with cinnamon stick to boiling; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in rest of ingredients and simmer 5 minutes longer.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Simmer all ingredients, except fruit slices, together for 15 to 20 minutes or until ready to serve.
Add sliced lemon and orange to punch bowl when ready to serve.
Serves 15 to 20 people.

title: ham and chicken casserole
directions: In skillet, saut onion in butter until tender. In large bowl, combine ham, chicken, peppers, olives, soup, sour cream, salt, pepper and onion. Fold in noodles. Pour into greased 2 1/2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with the Parmesan cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 minutes or until bubbly. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: holiday cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add egg and sour cream.
Add dry ingredients, mixing well. Fold in dates, nuts and cherries. Bake at 350° to 375° for 12 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy. Melt margarine.
Mix sugar and eggs. Add coconut, buttermilk and margarine.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic together. Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Serve hot.
May garnish with Cheddar cheese or sour cream.

title: cocoons
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Mixture should be very stiff and in a large, round shape.
Pinch off small amount and roll into cocoon shape.
Place on a large cookie sheet close together but not touching (Cocoons will not rise).
Bake at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot.

title: mac gregor bay chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken breasts in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Layer Swiss cheese slices over chicken.
Mix together 2 out of the 3 soups with milk.
Place soup mixture over the cheese.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Take dish out of oven and sprinkle bread crumbs over chicken.
Bake for another 15 minutes.

title: thai chicken salad
directions: Make Peanut Sauce; set aside. Remove chicken from bones and cut into bite size pieces (about 3 cups). Toss lettuce, chicken, parsley and onions in large bowl. Place lettuce mixture in center of large serving plate. Arrange noodles around edge of plate. Sprinkle peanuts over lettuce mixture. Drizzle sauce over salad. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and press into greased 9 x 6-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Contains 180 calories per serving.

title: killer chocolate cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan; spread pecans and coconut on bottom. Mix cake according to directions on box.
Spread over nuts and coconut.
Melt the cream cheese and margarine together (microwave is easiest way).
Add the box of confectioners sugar.
Pour this mixture over the cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Cool and serve out of pan.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: chocolate crackles
directions: Combine cocoa, oil and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla and other ingredients.
Chill dough.
Shape in small balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Put the ingredients into a large mixing bowl in order given, without mixing.
With electric mixer, blend and then beat at high speed for 5 minutes.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan; pour batter into the pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Let cool in the pan before removing.

title: janie's easy lemon cake
directions: Grease
and
flour a 10-inch Bundt pan.
Combine butter, pecans and coconut; spread on bottom of pan.
Combine cake mix, sour cream,
eggs,
water,
oil,
lemon and extract; beat for 2 minutes.
Spoon
on
top
of other batter in pan.
Bake at 350° for 45
to
minutes.
Cool
10 minutes.
Remove to platter, drizzle with glaze that has been made with 1 cup powdered sugar and 2 teaspoons lemon juice.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Cream Crisco and brown sugar.
Add the rest of ingredients and mix well.
Roll dough into walnut sized balls.
Dip in sugar and place sugar side up and 3-inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Sprinkle cookies with water for a cracked surface.
Bake at 375° until done.
Don't overbake or they will be hard.
Can chill dough overnight.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain beets, reserving 2 tablespoons juice.
Set beets and juice aside.

title: quick cherry dessert
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs; beat until light and fluffy.
Add almond extract.
Stir in flour.
Add baking powder until smooth. Spoon pie filling over cake in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bacon.
Pour into baking dish. Lay bacon strips on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: apricot pie
directions: In large bowl, sprinkle apricots with lemon juice.
Combine sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Add sugar mixture to apricots; toss to coat fruit.
Fill a pastry-lined 9-inch pie plate with apricot mixture; dot with butter.
Put on top crust.
Seal and flute edge. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Check to see if crust is browning. If brown, cover edges with foil and bake at 375° for another 25 minutes until golden brown.
Cool on rack before serving.

title: marguaritas
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into chilled glasses.
Put slice of lime on rim of glass.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Brown onion in margarine.
Combine with soup, broth and chilies.
Add chicken and heat.
In large baking dish (9 x 13-inch) place a layer of tortillas, layer of soup mixture. Repeat layers as needed.
Top with cheese.
May be frozen.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: k's cajun seasoning
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Fill a shaker for daily use.
Store remainder in a tightly covered container.
It has a long shelf life and can be used on all kinds of recipes.

title: fish soup
directions: Over medium heat, cook potatoes, onion, garlic and bay leaves in a saucepan for 5 minutes until onions are translucent.
Add remaining ingredients, except fish.
Boil until vegetables are tender.
Add fish and heat until cooked through.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Beat eggs and add to rest of mixture.
Bake on lightly greased griddle.

title: skewered lamb (souvlakia)
directions: Cut meat into 1-inch cubes and place in marinating dish.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover and refrigerate overnight, stirring occasionally.

title: old fashioned lemonade
directions: Wash fruit and slice thinly. Remove seeds.
Place lemon slices in a large bowl. Cover fruit with sugar.
Let stand for 10 minutes, then press firmly with potato masher to extract juice. Add water and continue to press fruit until liquid is well flavored.
Add ice cubes.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: teriyaki chicken wings
directions: Mix last four ingredients together.
In a large pan or marinating dish, marinate chicken wings for at least 24 hours in the fridge.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, turning frequently.

title: chicken chimichangas
directions: Combine chicken, sauce, onions and spices and simmer 5 minutes in saucepan.
Brush tortillas with margarine.
Spoon meat mixture and cheese in tortillas.
Fold and place in 9 x 12-inch aluminum pan.
Bake at 450°
for 10 minutes.
Garnish with olives.

title: italian beef in the crock-pot
directions: Cut roast in small squares.
Place roast, bouillon cubes, garlic salt and Italian dressing in crock-pot.
Add enough water to almost cover all beef.
Cook on low for 8 hours.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Cream together the first 4 ingredients.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk, mixing until well blended.
Sift dry ingredients and add to moist mixture; mix in zucchini last.
Spoon into greased and floured 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan and sprinkle top of cake with chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: orange salad #1
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add orange juice, sherbet and oranges.
Refrigerate.

title: double chocolate walnut biscotti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour a large baking sheet.
In a bowl, whisk together flour, cocoa powder, baking soda and salt.
In another bowl with an electric mixer, beat together butter and granulated sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat until combined well.
Stir in flour mixture to form a stiff dough.
Stir in walnuts and chocolate chips.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add crushed crackers, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well, pour in buttered pan.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Combine in a large bowl the broccoli, rice, onion, butter, celery, soups and melted Cheeez Whiz; mix well.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: yummy coconut bars
directions: Mix together crackers, butter and sugar.
Press into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake for 10 minutes while mixing coconut, milk and vanilla.
Spread onto cracker crust and return to oven for 10 minutes more.
Spread chips over coconut and return to oven to melt slightly.
Remove and immediately spread chips out smoothly over top while hot.
Cool and cut before cold.
Store in airtight container.

title: cranberry apple orange salad
directions: Empty cranberries into large mixing bowl.
Chop remaining ingredients coarsely in food processor or blender.
Add to berries and marinate overnight or several days.

title: cream cheese croissant squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Unroll 1 can of dough. Press in bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan to form crust. Firmly press perforations to seal.

title: lurline's shoe peg casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl. Spray a large casserole dish with Pam.
Pour ingredients into casserole dish. Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until done.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and let gel.
Whip dry whipped topping and cream cheese.
Spread over gelled mixture.
Top with shredded cheese.

title: chapati
directions: Knead the dough as you would pizza dough, only this time with only flour and water.
You may add or reduce the water or flour to make a soft nonsticky dough.
The softer the better. Using a rolling pin, spread small piece of dough to make it flat and circular.
Spread some oil on it, as we do donuts.
After rolling, spread it again and lay it on a cooking pan (should be heavy). Cook one side until it has brown spots.
Turn it and apply some oil.
When the other side is brown, do the same.
Turn again and cook both sides until golden brown.
Store in a tight place.
Keep them warm and soft.
Serve warm with chicken or beef (or any) soup.

title: baked chicken
directions: Put chipped beef in cold water for 1/2 hour before cooking. Place chipped beef in bottom of pan.
Wrap bacon around chicken. Combine sour cream, mushroom soup, mushrooms and pimentos.
Pour mushroom sauce over chicken.
Cook for 2 hours at 325° to 350°. Uncover the last 30 minutes.

title: vinegar cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar together.
Add all remaining ingredients. Beat until blended.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Before baking, flatten with a flat bottom glass dipped in ice water.
Bake 350 for 8 minutes or until edges are lightly golden.
Makes 3 dozen depending on size.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on cookies.

title: spinach pie
directions: Cook spinach according to directions on package.
Drain well. Press with fork in strainer.
Beat eggs and add salt, pepper, Parmesan cheese, cooled spinach, Ricotta cheese and shredded Muenster.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Line greased pan with crescent rolls; put in mixture.
Form lattice crust on top with extra dough.
Bake at 350° until dough turns brown.

title: 1950's mystery pudding cake
directions: Mix and sprinkle on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°, until tests done.

title: corn fritters
directions: Drain corn, reserving liquid.
Add enough milk to liquid to measure 1 cup.
Combine egg, milk mixture and corn.
Combine dry ingredients.
Mix just until moist.
Drop batter from tablespoon into 375° deep fat.
Fry until brown, 3 to 4 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve warm maple syrup with fritters.

title: pot stickers
directions: For filling:
Squeeze cabbage to remove as much moisture as possible; place in large bowl.
Add pork, onion, water, soy sauce, cornstarch, ginger, sesame oil and sugar; mix well.
Place 1 rounded teaspoonful filling in center of each pot sticker wrapper.

title: coffee crumb cake
directions: Combine sugar, salt, flour and baking powder.
Mix well.
Add Wesson oil.
Take out 1 cup and to this, add cinnamon and set this aside for use as topping.
To 1 egg, beaten with a fork, add enough milk to make 1 cup.
Add this along with vanilla to flour mixture and mix with an electric mixer to make very smooth.
Pour batter into rectangular baking pan (13 x 9-inch) and sprinkle crumb mixture over batter.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix molasses, butter and sugar with boiling water.
Add sifted flour and baking soda to the spices.
Add well beaten eggs, then stir in raisins and nuts.
Bake in loaf or square pan for 40 minutes at approximately 350°.

title: buttermilk pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy, adding sugar gradually.
Blend in vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add buttermilk.
Sprinkle pecans in bottom of a 9-inch unbaked pastry shell and pour filling over.
Bake at 300° for 1
1/2 hours.
Best if served at room temperature.

title: hidden valley ranch sausage stars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
