Blot sausage dry with paper towels and combine with cheeses, salad dressing, olives and red pepper.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef with onions and bell peppers and drain.
Add tomato paste, water and mushrooms.
Add garlic to taste.
Add oregano and parsley flakes.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top. Simmer over low heat for 30 to 40 minutes, stirring occasionally. Prepare noodles according to package and serve together.

title: grape gelatin salad
directions: Mix gelatin and water in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add pineapple, then blueberry pie filling.
Let mixture congeal thoroughly.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix together in a jar.
When ready to serve, add 2 to 3 tablespoons to a cup of hot water.

title: water chestnut dip
directions: Mix the sour cream, cream cheese, Miracle Whip and water chestnuts.
Add the rest of the ingredients to taste.
Mix all well.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: homemade sauerkraut
directions: Wash cabbage well and drain.
Cut in half and decore.
Slice cabbage into very thin slices.
Mix salt with cabbage.
Pack very tightly (stomp) into a 3 gallon stone jar.
Make sure juice (water) is above cabbage 1/2 inch.
Invert plate on top of cabbage to weight it under water so as not to float.
Cover jar with cloth. Let stand for 5 days.
Taste for sourness (if not enough, let sit a couple more days).
Put into large pot and bring to a boil.
Place in glass jars with seals and lids to can.

title: blackberry custard pie
directions: Cook blackberries; add sugar and stir.
Add margarine and stir.
Mix 1/2 cup milk and flour, stirring until the mixture is not lumpy.
Combine blackberries and flour mixture and cook until done.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Let cool, then top with 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip.

title: heavenly fresh coconut cake
directions: Reserve coconut milk and grate coconuts.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and 1 1/2 teaspoons salt.
Repeat sifting.
Beat egg whites with remaining salt until stiff peaks form.
Whip the cream until stiff and fold lightly into egg whites with wire whisk.

title: creamed peas
directions: Wash beans well, cover with water 3 to 4 times height of beans, bring to boil, then simmer 1 hour or until bean skins slip off easily.
Drain and rinse twice.
Place in baking dish, add remaining ingredients and then water to well above top of beans. Bake at 300° for 2 hours, then at 275° for 3 hours.
Check to make sure liquid covers beans, but do not stir.
Leave in oven overnight.
Reheat the following day.

title: clam dip
directions: Heat cream cheese in double boiler or fondue pan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve warm.
Enjoy!

title: pork chops pizzaiola
directions: Sprinkle chops on both sides with black pepper.
Heat in heavy skillet.
Add chops and brown 5 minutes per side.
Add garlic, mushrooms, tomatoes and green pepper.
Place chops on top of vegetables.
Add wine or broth.
Sprinkle with oregano.
Cover and cook 15 to 20 minutes until chops are no longer pink and vegetables are crisp.
Good served with buttered noodles.

title: liver paste
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Cook onion and chicken livers until onion is transparent and livers are pink; do not fry.
Put liver mixture with juice in the blender.
Add hard-cooked eggs.
Blend well until smooth.
Add garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Add salad dressing.
Mix well.
Refrigerate.
Very good.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well. Pour into a lightly greased 1-quart baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: stuffed eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise and remove the yolks.
Mash yolks with the cream, salt and pepper.
Stuff the egg whites with egg yolk mixture and serve.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the sugar with the Snowdrift. Beat eggs.
Mix soda and water, flour, cinnamon, raisins and oatmeal. Bake.

title: picnic baked beans
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Combine with remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into large baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until hot.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: ohelo berry pie
directions: Mix
fruit,
sugar and tapioca in bowl.
Place	in
uncooked pie crust.	Dot with butter; cover with top crust.	Cut slits
in crust
for steam to escape.
Bake at
400°	for
45 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: taco dip
directions: Beat together cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning. Stir in Cheddar cheese, green chilies and onion.
Chill.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice as package directs.
Brown sausage.
When sausage is almost done, add onion and bell pepper to it and saute until tender.
To cooked rice, add sausage mixture, cheese, milk and pepper; mix well.
Place in casserole dish and microwave on High for 10 minutes with cover and lightly stir enough to mix. Microwave on High another 5 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Melt butter.
Add all ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350 degrees or until straw comes out clean.

title: savory sauerkraut
directions: Mix all ingredients and heat well.
Serve.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Add cream of tartar. Gradually add sugar.
Continue beating until stiff peaks form. Add vanilla.
Break crackers into large pieces and fold in.
Add nuts.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Spread pie filling over cooled cake.
Cut into servings and top with Cool Whip or any whipped cream.

title: french silk pie
directions: In a bowl, beat butter and sugar with an electric mixer on medium speed about 4 minutes or until fluffy.
Stir in chocolate and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating on high after each addition and scraping sides of bowl constantly.
Transfer to baked pie shell.
Cover; chill for 5 to 24 hours or until set.
If desired, top with unsweetened whip cream and chocolate curls.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Fry meat; crumble and drain.
Put in large baking dish.
Cover with sauce, then layer with cheese.
Mix eggs, Bisquick and milk and pour over the top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 400°.

title: heavenly fruit salad
directions: Refrigerate for 12 hours.

title: quick danish pastry
directions: In saucepan, bring water to boil. Add butter. Stir and simmer until butter melts. Remove from heat and add almond extract. Stir in flour until blended. Return to low heat; cook and stir 1 minute or until dough follows spoon around pan. Remove from heat. Beat in eggs, 1 at a time. Beat well after each addition until well combined. Spread evenly over crust in pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, until brown. Remove to rack to cool. (Pastry will fall, forming custard like filling.) Spread with Sugar Glaze.

title: ribbon icebox dessert
directions: Line bottom of	a
x 13-inch pan with half of graham crackers.
Cut to fit if necessary.
Beat powdered sugar and 3 tablespoons cream.	Spread	on crackers and top with remaining crackers.
Chill.
Heat to boiling water and juice.
Add jello and dissolve.
Cool until partially set.
Divide into 2 parts. Add 3/4 cup
of
evaporated
milk to one part and beat at high speed until fluffy.
Pour over crackers.
Chill.
Add 3/4 cup water and fruit
to
other part.
Pour over whipped layer and chill until set.
Cut into squares.

title: carrot cake and icing
directions: Sift together dry ingredients (first 6 in list).
Separately beat sugar into oil (room temperature) on high speed.
When the mixture is fluffy, add eggs at room temperature, one at a time. Gradually add dry ingredients to liquid.
Bake in a 10 x 15-inch pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 350° or use 9 x 13-inch or an 8-inch square pan.
A Bundt pan would require more time.
Test the cake for doneness by inserting toothpick to see if dough is cohering, or lightly touch the top to see whether it springs back.

title: ambrosia balls
directions: Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes until set (not brown) at 400°.
While warm, roll in confectioners sugar.
Cool.
Roll in sugar again.
Makes 4 dozen.
Different and delicious!

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut flowerets off broccoli; cut in very small pieces.
Add raisins, bacon bits and sunflower seeds.
Mix Miracle Whip with vinegar and sugar.
Mix with broccoli mixture.
Top with separated purple onion slices (optional).

title: country spoon bread
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Add corns, sour cream, butter and muffin mix and stir.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with cheese and bake 15 more minutes.
Serve hot.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: In large skillet, mix margarine, sugar, milk and cocoa.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, add peanut butter, vanilla, salt and oatmeal.
Mix well. Drop from spoon onto wax paper.
Let cool.

title: cheesy french bread
directions: Cut French bread into slices but not through bottom crust. Insert thin slice of cheese between each.
Melt margarine; combine with minced onion and poppy seed.
Pour over top of bread. Sprinkle with paprika.
Wrap loosely in foil leaving open at top. Heat in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until cheese melts. Serves 6 to 8.

title: sausage-greens pie
directions: Brown 1 pie shell.
To ground sausage add eggs, Mozzarella cheese, Ricotta cheese, salt, pepper and garlic.
Mix well.
Blend in greens.
Pour into brown pie shell.
Cut remaining uncooked pie crust into strips.
Lace over top of the green sausage mixture. Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: chocolate peanut delight
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine dry cake mix, butter, milk and egg. Add 3/4 c. of peanuts.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
In a mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese, peanut butter, sugar, condensed milk and vanilla until smooth.
Fold in 3 cups whipped topping.
Spread over the crust; top with the remaining whipped topping and peanuts. In a microwave-safe bowl, heat chocolate chips and butter on high for 1 minute or until melted.
Stir in vanilla until smooth; drizzle over cake.
Refrigerate for 2-3 hours before cutting.
Yield: 12-15 servings.

title: traveling junk food
directions: In saucepan, combine the first 4 ingredients.
Cook until sugar melts.
In a 9 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish, mix the last 3 ingredients.
Pour liquid mixture over dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until crisp.

title: cranberry cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl, combine flour, oats, 3/4 cup sugar and margarine; mix until crumbly.
Reserving 1 1/2 cups crumb mixture, press remainder firmly on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Mix together all of the ingredients.

title: one minute chocolate frosting
directions: Boil sugar, margarine, milk and cocoa together 1 minute; add vanilla.
Beat until cool or ready to spread.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in boiling water.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool. (Frosting may be found on back of Hershey's cocoa box.)

title: rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Drain and cool. Collect all ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir to mix, but avoid mashing.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cut potatoes into thin slices, but not all the way through.
Put potatoes in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with herbs.
Bake potatoes at 425° for 55 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheeses. Bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: italian cheese log
directions: After cheese has softened, mix in onion, black olives and garlic.
Refrigerate until hard enough to shape into log.
Roll log in chopped pecans or walnuts.

title: baked fish delmar
directions: Combine butter, lemon juice, onions, salt and parsley flakes. Place single layer of fish in sprayed 8 x 11-inch baking pan. Pour mixture over and bake in preheated 325° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.
Ten minutes before finished, sprinkle paprika over fillets.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Cream butter and add sugar.
Blend thoroughly.
Add egg yolk and vanilla.
Sift flour and baking soda and mix well with first mixture.
Spread in ungreased pan and then prick deeply with a fork.
Bake in a 250° moderate oven for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: oven porcupines
directions: Mix meat, rice, 1/2 cup water, onion, salt, garlic powder and black pepper.
Shape the mixture by rounded tablespoonfuls into balls.
Place meatballs in long pan or baking dish.
Stir together remaining ingredients and pour over meatballs.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: angel "deviled" eggs
directions: Boil eggs with hot water.
Once the eggs cool for about 15 minutes, peel the eggs.
After you peeled the eggs, cut them in half, then take out the yolk and put them in the bowl.
After you've taken out the yolk and put it in the bowl, add some mustard and mayonnaise and mix it with a whisk.
After you've mixed it up thoroughly, put the yolk back in each egg equally.
Then powder some paprika on it...and Voile!..Angel "Deviled" eggs.

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: Mix all ingredients (except chicken) together.
Pour into a Pam sprayed 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put chicken pieces on mixture.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Cover loosely with foil.
Test chicken with a fork, if tender and if liquid is absorbed.
If desired, uncover last 15 minutes to brown chicken.

title: polish sausage stir-fry
directions: In wok or large skillet, heat oil.
Add potatoes and carrots. Stir-fry a little; add onions.
Stir-fry and cover a few minutes. Add broccoli, mushrooms and sausage, stir and mix.
Add seasonings; cover and cook until vegetables are done.
Stir occasionally.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix with mixer on low.
Refrigerate for a couple of hours.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add sifted dry ingredients to this mixture.
Add carrots, packed firmly.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Turn into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chuck wagon slaw
directions: In large bowl, combine mayonnaise and seasonings.
Add cabbage and beans, mixing lightly but thoroughly.
Cover and chill to blend flavors.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Simmer together until veggies are well done, about 1 hour.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions making 2 (8-inch) layers. When completely cool, split both layers.
Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut and blend well.
Spread between layers and on top of cake.
Seal in airtight container and refrigerate 3 days before serving.

title: snow covered almond crescent cookies
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat butter, sugar and almond extract until well blended. Add flour and salt.

Mix well. Stir in oats and almonds. Use level tablespoonfuls. Shape dough into crescents. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 14 to 17 minutes until light golden brown. Remove warm cookies to wire rack. Sift with powdered sugar. Cool completely.
Store tightly covered.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: fresh pear cake(super moist)
directions: Combine pears and 2 cups sugar. Let set for a few hours or overnight. Stir occasionally to extract juice. Mix remaining ingredients easily with big spoon. Grease and flour bundt pan. Bake at 325 to 350 degrees for about 70 to 90 minutes.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and onion salt (to taste).
Roll chicken in seasoned flour.
Melt butter in skillet; brown chicken on both sides.
Remove chicken to casserole dish.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Spoon over chicken.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: riveria garden salad
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese according to directions.
Add sour cream and Miracle Whip; mix.
Add vegetables, salt and pepper. Mix again lightly and chill.

title: classic potato salad
directions: Peel and dice potatoes. Add salt and cook for 20 minutes or until done, but not overdone. Cool slightly. Add other ingredients, adjusting amounts to individual taste.
After potato salad is mixed, sprinkle with paprika and chill.
Serves 20.

title: stay-crisp vegetable slaw
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Mix vegetables; sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cold water.
Mix sugar, vinegar, celery seed, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in gelatin and cool until slightly thickened; beat well.
Gradually beat in oil.
Drain vegetables.
Add dressing and toss until coated.
It will keep for a few days in refrigerator.

title: apple carrot muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; stir in carrots, apples and almonds.
Make well in center of mixture and combine egg, oil and vanilla; stir until moistened.
Spoon into muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Great with coffee in the mornings.

title: gilbert's favorite chicken pie
directions: Boil fryer until tender.
Remove bones and skin.
Cut up and place in 2-quart baking dish.
Mix broth and soup, stirring until smooth.
Sprinkle salt and pepper over chicken and pour broth mixture over it.
Melt butter and mix with flour and milk.
Pour this mixture over chicken and bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: easy noodle casserole
directions: In large skillet, brown beef with onion and garlic.
Drain well.
Mix in tomatoes, oregano, salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Mix in zucchini.
After 10 minutes, blend in noodles.

title: meringue kisses(a melt in your mouth cookie)
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, not dry.
Add sugar gradually while blending with mixer.
Blend in vanilla, then fold in chocolate chips.
Drop onto cookie sheet lined with brown paper. Bake at 250° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool before removing from paper.
Can be colored with food coloring for special occasions. Makes 3 dozen.

title: corn bread casserole
directions: Combine eggs, cornmeal, salt, corn, milk, and vegetable oil in bowl; set aside.
Cook ground beef until browned.
Drain, set aside.
Pour half cornmeal mixture into a greased 10 1/2 inch iron skilled.
Sprinkle evenly with ground beef, pour on salsa and top with cheese.
Pour the rest of batter over top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let stand.
Serves 6-8.

title: turtle cake
directions: Make filling first so it can cool.
Melt Kraft caramels and margarine in a saucepan.
Add Eagle Brand milk; stir often and cool.
Mix German chocolate
cake
as directed.
Pour half the batter in a greased and floured
9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove from
oven
and
cool.
Pour
filling over cake layer; sprinkle with
pecans
and
chocolate
chips. Pour remaining batter on top and
bake
to
minutes at 350°.

title: dowen's coconut pie
directions: Throw it all in a bowl and stir real well.
Divide between 2 (9-inch) pie pans and bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes (or until lightly browned).
It actually makes its own crust, so the hardest part is cleaning up the kitchen!
Serves 4 men or 12 ladies.

title: scalloped corn
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish, mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until liquid is set and top is a golden brown.
Cool for 5 minutes before serving.

title: anita's lasagna
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well. Boil a 1 pound package of lasagna noodles. Spread 1 tablespoon of sauce thinly in the bottom of a 9 x 13 inch pan. Put one layer of noodles down; put close together - no need to overlap. One layer should require 3 or 4 noodles. Sprinkle with grated cheese of choice. Spread 1/2 the cheese filling as a layer over the noodles. Cover with 4-5 slices of cheese. Then add another layer of noodles, sprinkle with grated cheese, and cover this layer with sauce. Add another layer of noodles, grated cheese, rest of cheese filling and sliced cheese. Add the last layer of noodles, grated cheese and sauce. Bake in 350° oven for 30-40 minutes or in 400° oven for 20-30 minutes, or until the cheese filling appears to be firm.
Allow to cool for 5-10 minutes.
Serve with any leftover sauce.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, Karo and water in heavy pan, cook over medium heat, slowly.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Cook until soft ball stage (238°).
Add peanuts and salt.
Cook to hard crack stage (298°), stirring constantly.
Peanuts turn to golden brown, stir with wooden spoon, about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, soda and vanilla.
Stir slightly.
It turns yellow.
Pour onto buttered jellyroll pan; flatten.
Cool.
Break into pieces. Put into airtight container.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise together. Spread mixture over ham slices. Place a dill spear at one of ham slice and roll it up. Secure with a toothpick. Let chill for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cinnamon christmas ornaments
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add 1 tablespoon water extra if needed, to form a dough.
Roll between plastic to about 1/8-inch thick. Use hollow cookie cutters; put on rack to let dry.
Use a straw to put hole in top of each ornament.
When dry, tie with ribbon; hang on tree.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Cook melted butter and brown sugar 2 minutes.
Add milk; cook 2 minutes.
Cool.
Add confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Beat and spread.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and sugar.
Add 2 cups of hot water; stir to dissolve, then add the other 6 cups of cold water.
Stir.
Add pineapple juice and stir.
Just before serving, add 2 quarts of ginger ale.

title: 15-minute super sundae pie
directions: In a mixer bowl, stir slightly softened ice cream until smooth. Spoon the ice cream until pie crust is almost full and cover with the inverted plastic lid. Place pie in freezer for several hours until hard.

title: ice apple tea
directions: Place tea bags in pitcher. Cover with boiling water.
Leave for 5 minutes.
Squeeze tea bags and discard. Stir in honey until dissolved. Stir in apple juice. Chill or add ice cubes to glasses. Drop a lemon slice and mint sprig in each.
Makes 4 servings.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Mix all ingredients except oats.
Stir in oats and pat in 9 x 13-inch greased Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Take out of oven and run knife around sides.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix soups, broth and onion soup mix and heat on top of stove. Mix in rest of ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
You may top with bread crumbs or crushed corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves about 6.

title: low-fat pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Except for pie shell and garnish, beat all ingredients in a large bowl with mixer until smooth.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes, until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack, then chill about 4 hours or up to 2 days.
Just before serving, garnish with whipped topping; sprinkle cinnamon and pecan halves.

title: peach crisp
directions: Toss peaches with 1/3 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Spoon into a lightly greased 9-inch deep pie plate and set aside.
Combine flour and remaining sugar.
Cut in butter with pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle on top of peaches.
Bake at 375° for 35 or 40 minutes.
Based on 6 servings, each serving contains:
283 calories; 8g fat; 79mg sodium; 21mg cholesterol.

title: symphony pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and melted chocolate together.
Pour into ready-made crust.
Freeze or refrigerate.

title: crispy oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix above ingredients together until light and fluffy.
Add 1 cup sifted self-rising flour and mix well.
Then stir in: 1 cup rolled oats (not instant or quick cooking), 1/2 chopped nuts and 1/2 cup raisins.

title: taco salad
directions: Cut lettuce and tomatoes into small pieces.
Cut Longhorn into cubes.
Crumble up the chips.
Brown the ground meat.
Chop the onion and green pepper.
Mix everything together, then add the dressing.
Good cold or at room temperature.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding, milk and condensed milk in bowl and beat until thick.
Add whipping cream.
Place wafers and bananas in bowl. Pour pudding mixture over wafers and bananas.
Chill about 1 hour. Spread Cool Whip on top.

title: coney island wiener sauce
directions: Brown hamburg and onion; drain.
Add spices and boiling water. Simmer 2 1/2 hours.

title: french cheese rolls
directions: In a small bowl, beat cream cheese with electric mixer until soft. Add milk; continue beating until smooth. Cut crusts from bread. Roll over each slice once with rolling pin to flatten slightly.

Spread each bread slice with cream cheese mixture and 1 tablespoon preserves. Roll up each slice, jelly roll fashion. Wrap rolls individually in waxed paper or plastic wrap. Refrigerate overnight or at least 2 hours.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Tenderize meat.
Cut into thin strips; trim fat.
Brown lightly in butter.
Remove meat from pan.
Add onions and mushrooms; cook until tender.
Add meat, tomato juice, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 50 minutes, until fork-tender.

title: foil packs
directions: Clean and peel ingredients.
Tear off pieces of foil about 12 to 15 inches long, one for each serving needed.
Place a mixture of the chopped veggies in foil equal to a serving size.
Crumble ground beef over the veggies; salt and pepper.
Wrap with rolled seams to keep in steam.
Place packs on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 45 minutes.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: In saucepan, melt butter on low heat.
Remove and add flour, dry mustard and salt.
Mix well.
Add milk and heat on medium heat until sauce thickens.
Add cheese and heat until cheese melts. Stir occasionally.
Crumble bread crumbs over top and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in oven at 375°.

title: quick baked beans
directions: Fry bacon.
Reserve 2 teaspoons drippings.
Saute green peppers and onion in drippings for 2 minutes.
Add beans, mustard, catsup and sugar; mix well.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Combine bacon and stir into beans.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: chicken salad supreme
directions: Combine mayonnaise
and mustard.
Toss dressing lightly with remaining ingredients and chill.
Serves 4.

title: eggplant appetizer
directions: Peel eggplant.
Cut into 1-inch cubes.
Heat oil and start cooking chopped celery, then add eggplant, green pepper, onion and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Add nutmeg, curry powder and oregano to taste.
Then add Worcestershire sauce, tomato paste, salt and pepper.
Serve hot or cold on crackers or bread.

title: pickle wraps
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with garlic powder.
Spread on ham or turkey slices (or your meat of choice), put a pickle in the middle and roll up.

title: homemade - hand churned fruit ice cream(strawberry - peach)
directions: Churn in hand churn with crushed ice and plenty of salt.

title: midnight cake
directions: Cream shortening, add sugar gradually, and cream until fluffy.
Blend in well beaten eggs, slowly.
Add hot water to cocoa, and mix until smooth.
Stir to dissolve completely.
Sift flour, salt, soda, and baking powder together, and add to cream mixture alternately with hot water and cocoa mixture.
Blend in vanilla.
Pour into a 8-inch square pan; bake 30-55 minutes in a moderate oven 320-350°.

title: yankee noodle bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In skillet sprayed with butter flavored cooking spray, brown frankfurters, green pepper and onion until tender.
Combine with noodles, tomato sauce, brown sugar substitute, mustard and pepper.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: claudia sanders yeast rolls
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Work in butter.
Set aside. Dissolve yeast in water.
Combine the yeast, egg and sugar.
Add yeast mixture to flour mixture.
Shape into rolls and place on a greased baking pan.
Let rise 2 1/2 hours.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 425°.
Makes 12 rolls.

title: rinderrouladen
directions: Pound beef until 1/4 inch thick.
Cut into pieces 7x4 inches. Lightly sprinkle with salt and black pepper.
Spread each piece with 1 Tbsp. mustard.
Place 1/2 strip bacon down center of each piece.
Sprinkle with onion and snipped parsley.
Place 1/2 of a pickle on narrow end of each piece, roll up.
Fasten with wooden picks.
Heat oil in 10 inch skillet until hot.
Cook rolls over medium heat, until brown on all sides.
Add 1/4 cup water, 1/2 tsp salt and 1/4 tsp pepper.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until beef is tender, about 1 hour.
Remove rolls and keep them warm.
Add enough water to liquid in skillet if necessary to measure about 1 cup.
Mix 2 Tbsp of flour and 2 Tbsp of water, then stir gradually into broth.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir for 1 minute and add water if needed. Serve rolls with gravy.
Garnish with parsley springs and serve over mashed potatoes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple (drained). Add marshmallows and nuts. Stir. Mix in Cool Whip. Chill and serve.

title: chris' breakfast delight
directions: Mix the ingredients in a blender or mixer.

title: baked parmesan chicken
directions: Combine egg and milk; stir well and set aside.
Combine cheese, flour, paprika, salt and pepper; mix well.
Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Dip in egg mixture and dredge in flour mixture. Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish; pour margarine over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine in 2 1/2 to 3 quart casserole dish.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour into casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, uncovered.

title: self-frosting double fudge cake
directions: Empty dry cake mix into bowl.
Add eggs and pudding.
Mix well. (Batter will be thick.)
Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle top of batter with sugar, then chocolate chips and top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: never fail chocolate or caramel frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla.
Over medium heat, stir until sugar dissolves.
When mixture comes to a boil, boil for 4 minutes.
Add vanilla; cool and beat.

title: chili con questa dip
directions: Brown beef; add all the other ingredients except cheese. Simmer 5 minutes.
In a double boiler, melt cheese and add to the browned beef mixture.
Serve in chafing dish or small crock-pot with Doritos chips.

title: clifford's salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in refrigerator to chill before serving.

title: cherry cheer
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Fold in whipped topping.
Chill for about 1 hour before serving.

title: aria pork chop dinner
directions: Sear pork chops quickly on both sides.
Put seared pork chops in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan (greased).
Place rice on each pork chops.
Top with mushrooms, green bell peppers, onion, salt and pepper.
Now take your whole tomatoes and open it up like a flower and place over the top of each pork chop.
Pour remaining juice in baking pan.
Optional toppings are:
Parmesan cheese or sharp Cheddar cheese.
Place your Aria Pork Chops, covered, in the oven at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake another 10 or 15 minutes or until tender.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
In a plastic bag or bowl, mix 3/4 cup sugar and cinnamon and shake until pieces are coated. Layer in greased Bundt pan.
Between each layer, pour melted butter and brown sugar and sprinkle with chopped nuts and cherries. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: apple delight
directions: Place apples in ungreased pan.
Mix other ingredients together with fork and sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° in ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 30 minutes.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix first three ingredients together. Add remaining ingredients. Store in a large container. To serve add 1/3 cup mixture to 1 cup boiling water.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Melt margarine.
Mix rest of ingredients. Pour over.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers thoroughly, using a vegetable brush; drain on rack.
Slice unpeeled cucumbers into 1/8 to 1/4-inch slices; discard ends.
Add onions and garlic.
Add salt and mix thoroughly; cover with crushed ice or ice cubes; let stand 3 hours.
Drain thoroughly; remove garlic cloves.
Combine sugar, spices and vinegar; heat just to boiling.
Add drained cucumbers and onion slices and heat 5 minutes.
Pack hot pickles loosely into clean, hot pint jars to 1/2-inch of top.
Adjust jar lids. Process in boiling water for 5 minutes (start to count processing time as soon as water in canner returns to boiling).
Remove jars and complete seals if necessary.
Set jars upright to cool.

title: sausage egg casserole
directions: Spread bread crumbs in bottom of casserole dish.
Brown sausage and layer over crumbs.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Pour over sausage.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate no bake cookies
directions: Boil for 1 minute the sugar, cocoa, milk and oleo; remove from heat.
Add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir and drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: crushed banana nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours or until done.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain reserve drippings in saucepan. Crumble bacon, set aside.
Add potatoes, celery, onion, salt, thyme, pepper, clam liquid.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
In quart jar with lid, add flour to milk.
Shake well.
Stir into vegetables mixture.
Cook over medium heat 15 minutes or until thickened. Stir in clams gently, stirring frequently.
Do Not Boil.
Garnish each serving with bacon. 4 servings.

title: indian fry bread 2(makes about 2 dozen)
directions: Put flour, baking powder and salt in a large bowl.
Mix well. Add water and stir until dough begins to form a ball.
On a lightly floured surface, knead dough lightly, 2 to 3 minutes.
Do not over work.
Place in a bowl and refrigerate 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, milk, butter, eggs and vanilla. Mix well with mixer.
Spoon in lightly greased 2-quart casserole.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening in large mixer bowl until light.
Add sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix baking cocoa, food coloring and water in small bowl to make paste.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Mix flour and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with mixture of vanilla and buttermilk, beating well after each addition. Sprinkle with soda; drizzle with vinegar.
Stir gently until mixed; do not beat.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Remove to wire racks to cool.
Spread frosting between layers and over top and side of cake.
Garnish with coconut.
This is a beautiful Valentine or Christmas treat.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in lard with a pastry blender.
Add liquid, one or two tablespoons at a time.
Makes 2 double crust pies.

title: pickled eggs
directions: In a large bowl, mix vinegar, 4 cups water, garlic, bay leaf, spices and salt.
Add eggs on onion rings.
Cover.
Refrigerate for several days.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Mix together all ingredients except the grated cheese.
Pour into a greased 3-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle the grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Save some of the caps from the mushrooms for topping.
Cut up the rest of mushrooms.
Brown the croutons in half of the butter. Place in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Saute onion and cut up mushrooms in remaining butter.
Spread evenly over croutons.
Over this, spread the undiluted soup.
Top with the mushroom caps.
Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Good with steak.

title: very blueberry pie
directions: Make
a
smooth paste of water, flour and salt.
Boil 1 cup of the blueberries with sugar and 1/2 cup water.
Add the flour paste and stir until it thickens.
Remove from stove and cool. When
cool,
add the remaining blueberries and put into baked pie
shell.
Refrigerate.
When
cold,
garnish
with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: nut torte
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff.
Combine sugars and slowly add to egg whites.
Fold in flavorings.
Combine crackers and nuts; fold into eggs.
Pour into two well-greased (1 tablespoon each) pie pans.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes (no longer).
Will be light in color, but darkens as cools.
When cake is cooled, slice bananas on top until covered (5 or 6).
Cover with whipped topping, making certain to cover completely and seal edges.
Sprinkle over
topping, 1/2 cup chopped pecans and 1/2 cup maraschino cherries, chopped fine.
Refrigerate.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Drain chopped vegetables.
Add seasoned vinegar and cook very slowly for about 1/2 hour.
Pack into hot jars and process for 15 minutes.
This makes about 6 pints.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix oleo, shortening, water and cocoa.
Let come to boil and set aside.
Put sugar, flour, eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla in bowl and pour in cocoa mixture.
Stir up.
Put in a 9 x 12-inch greased, floured pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: wild blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat
oven
Sift together the dry ingredients. Toss in blueberries.
Stir in mixture of egg, milk, oil and rind. For perfect muffins, do not overmix.
Batter should look lumpy. Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.	Sprinkle tops with
a
little powdered
sugar.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until muffins
are	puffed and golden.
Run a knife around inside of each
cup
to
loosen muffins
and
serve
at once.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: chuck wagon stew (gene aaron's special)(texarkansas southwest regional)
directions: Brown hamburger and chopped onion together.
Add beans, corn, soup and tomatoes.
Simmer about 20 minutes.
Serve with plain or jalapeno corn bread.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Put in crock-pot with all other ingredients except beans.
Cook on low setting 8 to 10 hours.
Add beans last hour.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Boil together all ingredients.
Add cooked rice and simmer.

title: glorified pork chops
directions: In a skillet in hot oil, cook half of the chops 10 minutes until browned.
Remove; set aside.
Repeat with remaining chops. Spoon off fat.
In skillet, combine soup and water.
Return chops to skillet.
Cover and cook over low heat for 10 minutes or until chops are no longer pink.
Serve over rice.

title: easy stew
directions: Pour all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 8 hours. Delicious served over rice.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all.
Put in loaf pan.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: waldorf chicken salad
directions: Line 2-quart salad bowl with spinach. Sprinkle egg on spinach. Arrange grated carrots around edge of spinach. Arrange chicken, celery, apple, walnuts and raisins in center. Serve with Honey Mustard Dressing on the side.

title: lenten mocha cake
directions: Add sugar, oil, cocoa and mix, then dry ingredients and vanilla.
Mix well.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar or chocolate frosting.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 15 3/4 x 10 1/2-inch jellyroll pan.
Line with waxed paper and grease again.
In medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In large bowl with mixer at high speed, beat egg whites until soft peaks form. Gradually beat in 1/3 cup sugar, one tablespoon at a time, until sugar dissolves and stiff glossy peaks form.
In another bowl, with mixer at high speed, beat egg yolks until lemon color. Gradually beat in 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat in flour mixture and pumpkin pie filling.
Gently fold into beaten egg whites.
Spread batter in pan.
Bake 15 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Spread a clean towel on counter.
Sprinkle towel with ground walnuts.
Turn cake immediately onto towel.
Remove waxed paper.
Roll cake in towel from short end.
Cool.

title: hot cheese chowder
directions: Saute celery, onion and green pepper in butter in Dutch oven until tender.
Add chicken broth, potato and carrot; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: kahlua dip
directions: Mix and refrigerate at least overnight.
Great on fruit, especially strawberries.
Was a big hit at a graduation party.

title: grilled chicken or turkey breast
directions: Make marinade of all ingredients.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Soak yeast in warm water.
Mix liquids and white sugar together.
Add 2 cups flour; beat until smooth, then add rest of flour and mix well.
Let stand 4 hours.
Roll out and spread with oleo, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Let rise until double in size. Bake 8 to 10 minutes in hot oven.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Melt butter; put onion and pepper (chopped) in it with oregano and parsley.
Simmer until onion and peppers are soft.
Add clams with lemon juice.
Cook for 10 minutes more.
Add bread crumbs and mix well.
Put into a square tin dish and add American cheese on top of it.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.
Serve warm with crackers.
And enjoy!!!

title: caramel icing
directions: Mix all ingredients well in heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Cook without stirring until a rolling boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir and test in ice water for very soft ball.
Cool to lukewarm by placing saucepan in ice cold water.
When cool, beat.
Mixture will lose shine and get a little thick.
May seem a little thin, but begin to frost cake, the icing will harden quickly.
Place frosted cake in airtight cake box.

title: smoked sausage sauerkraut casserole
directions: Heat oil in skillet and fry chopped onions.
Add sauerkraut and simmer for 2 minutes.
Add water and sausage; cook until done. Stir in grated potato, carrot, salt and sugar.
Cook 4 to 5 additional minutes.

title: vegetable squares(vegetable pizza)
directions: Flatten crescent rolls in cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix mayonnaise, cream cheese and Ranch dressing.
Spread on dough.
Cut vegetables and cheese in small pieces and spread vegetables on top.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: creamy potluck potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water for 10 to 12 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain again.
In a large mixing bowl, stir together the soup, sour cream, cream cheese and butter.
Add 1/4 cup of Cheddar cheese, 3 tablespoons of green onion, skim milk, parsley, garlic salt and pepper.
Stir mixture to combine.
Stir in potatoes.
Place in 2-quart shallow casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven or until heated through.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake until cheese melts.
Sprinkle with remaining green onion.

title: spicy rice
directions: Soak rice in hot water for 15 minutes.
Rinse in colander and let drain.
Saute rice in butter until golden.
Puree tomatoes, onions and garlic in blender with chicken stock.
Combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then simmer until the liquid is absorbed.
Add peas.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: banana cooler
directions: In electric blender, combine half the ice, the lime juice, sugar, pineapple juice and banana.
Blend with cover on at high speed until smooth.
Add remaining ice; blend more.
Serve in stem glass.
Yields 1 serving.

title: fudge
directions: Butter large, heavy pan well.
Mix chocolate, butter, sugar and milk.
Stir over medium-low heat to soft boil.
Cut heat off. Add marshmallow, vanilla and nuts.
Set in cold water.
Beat until there is change in color.
Pour into buttered Pyrex dish or jelly roll pan.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: turkeyburger "pizzarella"
directions: Combine ground turkey, egg, garlic salt, onion flakes, 2 tablespoons tomato sauce and Italian seasonings.
In a 10-inch quiche pan, sprayed with Pam, spread turkey mixture to line the bottom and sides to form crust.
Bake in a preheated 450° oven for 12 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Remove from oven and drain surface grease and pour on remaining tomato sauce with added Italian seasonings (if desired).
Sprinkle with cheese and return to oven for 7 minutes.
To serve, cut into pizza shaped wedges.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until smooth. Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well after each. Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add to creamed mixture. Place flour and coconut to cream mix. Makes a very stiff dough. Mix by hand. Put in greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: chipped beef spread
directions: Blend softened cream cheese and milk together. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Spread can be refrigerated at this point.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until it looks like it is going to brown. Serve with crackers as a spread or dip.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix like on package.
When it comes out of oven, poke holes all over.
Pour Eagle Brand milk all over.
Cool.
Ice with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: honey walnut bread
directions: Scald 1 cup milk. Add 1 cup honey and sugar. Stir over medium heat until the sugar is dissolved.
Cool the mixture. Beat in the butter and eggs.
Sift together the flour, salt and baking soda and stir into the batter.
Beat well. Add the walnuts and orange rind.

Pour the batter into a floured and buttered loaf pan and bake the bread in a moderately slow oven at 325° for about 1 hour. Cool the bread for 15 minutes in the pan and then turn it out on a wire rack to cool. Serve thinly sliced with butter or cream cheese.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, crackers, milk, onions and salt.
Make into small meatballs.
Roll in flour.
Brown in oil.
Drain.
Make sauce.
Drain pineapple.
Add enough water to pineapple juice to make 1 cup.
Mix vinegar, brown sugar, soy sauce, lemon juice and cornstarch.
Cook until thick.
Add bell pepper, pineapple and pimento.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Layer cheese, chilies, cheese and sausage in 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat eggs, milk and flour; pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon-sour cream tarts
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions.
Cool and stir together with sour cream; chill.
Drain raspberries, reserving 2/3 cup syrup.
Mix sugar and cornstarch in small saucepan; gradually stir in reserved syrup.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and boils.
Remove from heat and chill.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Use food processor to mince meat.
Cook all ingredients in crock-pot for 4 hours on high or 8 hours on low.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Cook the sugar, flour, oleo and half and half and set aside. Bake the pie shell in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Place the cooked filling into the partially baked shell and bake for another 25 minutes.
Sprinkle nutmeg or cinnamon on top.
Cool and enjoy.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Use only spices you might like in sauce.

title: date carrot cake
directions: Drain pineapple well.
Beat margarine and sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Beat in pineapple, carrots, dates and vanilla.
Combine flour, soda, cinnamon, ginger and salt. Gradually beat in flour mixture until well blended.
Pour batter into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven 50 to 60 minutes until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Serves 20.

title: marinated cucumbers, onions and tomatoes
directions: Alternate cucumbers, onions and tomatoes in bowl with lid. Mix equal parts vinegar (white or wine, I use red wine) and water. Mix vinegar, water, sugar, salt and pepper all together; pour over cucumbers, onions and tomatoes.
Stir a few times while marinating 2 to 3 hours at least before using.
Vinegar mixture should cover the vegetables.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, soup, sour cream, carrot and onion.
Melt margarine and stir in stuffing mix.
In 9 x 13-inch greased pan, layer chicken mixture, then stuffing mix and remaining chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in moderate oven (325° to 350°) until firm.
Tasty with buttered cracker crumbs on top of dishes.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Mix
shortening and sugar;
beat well.	Add vanilla and lemon juice.
Add
egg
and beat until light. Add flour, soda and
salt; alternate	with buttermilk.
Drop by tablespoonful and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Top with raisins.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: broccoli-red pepper salad(christmas)
directions: Peel broccoli stalks, cut into 1/4-inch size pieces.
Cook stalks in boiling water 1 minute.
Add flowerets, cook 1 to 3 minutes until crisp-tender.
Rinse in ice cold water and drain. Mix last 5 ingredients.
Toss with peppers.
Serve cold.
Serves 12.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix well.
Form into small balls.
Heat in heavy skillet 2 tablespoons oil.
Add meatballs, a few at a time.
Brown slowly, turning gently to brown evenly.
Remove meatballs when brown.
To drippings, add 1 cup water, stock or consomme.
Bring to a boil, stirring to loosen browned particles.
Combine 1 tablespoon flour and 2 tablespoons cold water.
Blend until smooth.
Slowly add to skillet, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Add meatballs.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Place cleaned fryer hen in Dutch oven with water and poultry seasoning (generous amount); salt and pepper if your diet allows. Cook until meat falls away from bone.
Let cool and then remove meat from bone.
Add remaining ingredients to chicken, sprinkling slivered almonds on top of salad.

title: goulash
directions: Brown ground beef.
Partially cook macaroni.
Drain broth.
Add chopped onion to meat and cook 3 or 4 minutes.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and 1 cup water.
Cook for about 5 minutes.
Add macaroni, catsup and 1/2 cup water.
Simmer until macaroni is done.

title: weiner-cheese & rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for one hour at 350°.
Do not add salt.

title: chicken and noodle casserole
directions: Place rinsed chicken into skillet with tight fitting lid.
Add onion and 1/2 cup of water.
Simmer until tender, about 1 hour. Cool and dice.

title: peach pie
directions: Cook jello, sugar, cornstarch and water until thick.
Cool. Place peaches in pie shell.
Pour mixture over fruit.
Cool and enjoy.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of pan.
Mix sugar and butter in bowl.
Stir eggs until blended.
Add bananas, buttermilk and vanilla.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt until moistened. Stir in nuts.
Pour into pan.
Bake 8-inch loaf for about 1 hour; bake 9-inch loaf for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes. Loosen sides.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely before slicing. Wrap tightly; store at room temperature, up to 4 days, or refrigerate up to 10 days.

title: fruit cake roll
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into 3 or 4 logs.
Coat with confectioners sugar.
Refrigerate until firm enough to slice. Store in refrigerator.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onions.
Drain.
Add to cooked and drained macaroni in large casserole dish.
Mix tomato soup and onion soup mix.
Add enough water to make mixture soupy.
Top with grated cheese and bake at 350° in oven until cheese is melted.

title: running board zucchini chicken
directions: Brown the chicken pieces in the 3 tablespoons of olive oil. Remove pieces from pan and add all other ingredients, except bouquet garni, salt and flour.
Fry briefly, stirring constantly. Add chicken and bouquet garni and simmer, covered, until chicken is done, about 30 minutes.
Remove bouquet garni.
Season to taste with salt.
Thicken with a flour and water paste, if desired. Makes 4 servings.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir well.
Best if allowed to remain in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Sprinkle pie crusts evenly with 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg.
Bake in a preheated 475° oven for 2 minutes.
Remove from oven and gently press crusts down while warm; set aside.
Heat milk and evaporated milk in a large saucepan over medium heat.
(Do not boil.) Process eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt with remaining 1 teaspoon nutmeg in a blender until smooth.
Turn blender on high; add half of hot mixture in a slow, steady stream.
Stir egg mixture into remaining hot milk mixture.
Pour evenly into pie crusts.
Bake at 475° for 5 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 425° and bake 15 minutes.
(Pie will not be set.)
Cool on a wire rack 45 minutes. Chill.
Yield: 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt 1 stick of margarine in a square Pyrex dish.
Add 1 heaping cup graham cracker crumbs.
Next, add chocolate chips, pecans and coconut.
Pour in 1 can Eagle Brand milk and stir. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool, then cut into squares.

title: fruit cocktail cookies
directions: Mix together shortening, brown sugar, sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Add raisins, drained fruit cocktail, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon, cloves and salt.
Mix all the ingredients and drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: vegetable sandwich
directions: Chop separately in food processor the first 5 ingredients, then drain.
Melt gelatin in 2 tablespoons vegetable juice; heat to melt.
Add to vegetables.
Stir in mayonnaise.
Allow to stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: mom's chocolate pie
directions: Bake shell according to instructions provided. Mix all dry ingredients together in saucepan. Add rest of ingredients and cook over low heat until thick. Pour in baked pie shell.

title: hot crabmeat appetizer
directions: Combine all ingredients, except almonds, mixing until well blended.
Spoon mixture into 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: company brussels sprouts
directions: In a skillet, fry bacon just until cooked.
Drain, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings.
Add remaining ingredients; cook and stir over medium-high heat for 10 to 15 minutes or until Brussels sprouts are crisp-tender.
Yields 4 servings.

title: bill's beef dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients with the cream cheese. If desired, sprinkle nuts on top. Serve with wheat crackers.

title: sweet muffins
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Grease a muffin tin.
Beat egg. Stir in milk and oil.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Beat for 20 to 25 minutes.
You can mix these the night before.
Kids love them.

title: pacific coast bake
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Stir in rice and salmon.
Add combined mayonnaise and egg; mix lightly.
Layer half the salmon mixture, Parmesan cheese and broccoli in 1-quart casserole.
Cover with 1 cup Cheddar cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with broccoli. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining Cheddar cheese; continue baking until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: choose-a-fruit twist
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and seal perforations to form 2 rectangles.
Pat each into an 8 x 4-inch rectangle.
Spread cream cheese on each and top with preserves and nuts.
Cut each rectangle into four 8 x 1-inch strips.
(You will have a total of 24 strips.)
Fold each strip in half and twist; they will be 1 x 4-inches.
Place on a lightly greased foil-lined baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool and store in airtight container.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine warm sweet potatoes with 1/4 cup margarine, milk, 2 eggs, 1 cup sugar and vanilla in mixer bowl.
Beat until smooth. Spoon into shallow baking dish.

title: soft caraway rye pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water with sugar and salt.
Mix the two types of flour and the caraway seed together and add to the warm yeast liquid.
The dough will be stiff; knead about 5 minutes, then divide it into 12 pieces.
Roll each piece into a long rope and form into a pretzel.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Brush with water and sprinkle with salt.
Do not let dough rise.
Bake at 475° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: barbecued chicken wings
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°.
Remove the wing tips and break each wing into two pieces.
Place in a shallow baking dish.
Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over the wings.
Bake for 1 hour and serve in the baking dish.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions on box.
Put frozen vegetables in strainer.
Drain pasta over frozen vegetables. After all water has been drained from pasta and vegetables, pour into desired bowl.
Pour salad dressing over pasta and vegetables; mix together.
The flavor comes out better when prepared overnight.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Note:
If strawberries are in season, you may substitute them for one or all of the fruit.

title: kiss my grits
directions: Brown, crumble and drain sausage. Mix all together in a 2 qt. baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until browned.

title: italian beef sandwiches
directions: Combine beef roast, water, salt and onions in a large roasting pan. Cover and cook at 325° for 2 hours until done. Remove roast and cool (save the juice). Slice, then layer in a covered
dish. Add all spices to the juice you saved from the roast. Bring to a boil and pour over meat. Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours. Serve on French bread.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: To make meatballs, combine all ingredients (mixture will be soft) and shape into walnut size balls.
Place meatballs in a single layer on wax paper-lined cookie sheets; freeze until solid (overnight).
Store frozen meatballs in freezer bags until ready to cook.

title: eggnog quick bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C). Grease bottom only of a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan, or three 5 3/4 x 3 1/4-inch loaf pans.
Beat eggs in large bowl.

Blend in sugar, eggnog, butter, rum extract and vanilla. Stir together flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg. Mix into eggnog mixture; stir to just moisten dry ingredients. Pour batter into prepared pan or pans. Bake bread in large pan for 40 to 60 minutes or until a tester inserted in the center comes out clean. Breads baked in the smaller pans require 35 to 40 minutes. Cool 10 minutes, and then remove bread from pan.
Cool completely. Wrap tightly and store in the refrigerator.

title: corned beef cracker dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together excluding 1/2 the chopped pecans. Put the mixture into a pie plate and sprinkle remaining pecans on top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm on crackers.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Unroll crescent rolls and separate dough into 16 triangles. Cut each apple into eight wedges.	Wrap a crescent roll triangle around each apple wedge and place in a greased 13 x 9 baking dish.

title: tomato pie
directions: Brown crust according to package directions.
Peel and dice tomatoes.
Put
into pie crust.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Crumble bacon on top.
Mix together cheese and mayonnaise.
Put on top of mixture.

title: recipe for happiness
directions: Mix all of these together and bake in oven of Forgiveness for two Prayer hours.
Then cool on table of Understanding.

title: chicken 'n hash brown bake
directions: Thaw hash browns overnight in refrigerator.
Layer in an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place chicken and mushrooms over the hash browns.
Stir together the sour cream, broth, soup, bouillon, onions, red pepper and garlic.
Pour over all.
Sprinkle with paprika and almonds. Bake, uncovered, for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
tags: frozen southern style hash brown potatoes

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cut up fryer and brown in butter. Combine remaining ingredients and boil 4 minutes. Place chicken in roaster and pour sauce over. Cover. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hour or until chicken is tender. Baste often.

title: woodchucks
directions: Make a white sauce with the first 3 ingredients. Add remaining ingredients. Serve on toast.

title: frosting
directions: Bring milk, brown sugar and butter to boil.
Let cool.
Add vanilla.
Spread on any kind of cake.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Hollow out bread (round loaf).
Tear bread in bite size pieces.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Cook over medium heat.
Bring to boil.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir until chocolate melts.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 tsp. vanilla. Beat with beater until thick.
Use sauce hot or cold.

title: two handed oatmeal cookies
directions: This makes a large batch.
Beat eggs.
Mix with sugars, peanut butter, margarine, soda and vanilla.
At this point you'll probably have to use hands.
Add oats, M&M's and chocolate chips.
Mix. Roll in balls and press down on cookie sheet with palm of hand.
Glass will smash the M&M's.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all together.
Pour some bacon grease in and mix.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix the cake mix according to box.
Add cream and margarine. Pour half of batter in greased and floured pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: almond bread pudding
directions: Break up bread into pieces. Cover with half and half. Let stand 1 hour.

title: pistachio-pineapple salad
directions: Mix together crushed pineapple and pistachio pudding mix. Add miniature marshmallows, nuts and cherries. Fold in Cool Whip. Let set, chilled, for several hours.

title: june's date tea loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour boiling water over dates and let cool.
Cream shortening and sugar; beat in egg.
Add soda to the date mixture after it has cooled.
Add flour, salt and the cool water to the creamed mixture and beat.
Stir in date mixture and continue to beat until smooth.
Fold in nuts.
Put in greased loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done in center. Loosen sides and cool slightly on wire rack.
Wrap securely in foil.
Serve with cream cheese, whipped with a small amount of orange juice and a dash of orange flavoring.

title: chocolate chip muffins
directions: You will need baking cups.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill, then make into balls.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Brown hamburger, chopped onion, and green pepper.
In bowl, mix hamburger mixture, mushrooms, spaghetti sauce and pizza sauce. Shred Cheddar and Mozzarella cheeses.
Layer twice in crock-pot noodles, meat/sauce and cheese.
Cook on low approximately 1 1/2 hours, until cheese is melted and mixture is heated through.
May also be baked in oven at 350° until mixture is heated through and cheese is melted.

title: seven-layer dip
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef. Set aside to drain and cool to room temperature.

title: french green bean casserole
directions: In casserole dish, place first 3 ingredients.
Pour mushroom soup over this.
Place in oven until bubbly hot.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, butter and sugar.
Press firmly into 9 x 13-inch baking dish; reserve some crumbs for garnish.
Blend thawed orange juice with milk; fold in Cool Whip and oranges.
Do not beat.
Pour mixture over crust; top with reserved crumbs. Refrigerate or freeze until serving.

title: shrimp spaghetti
directions: Peel and
devein
shrimp
or
you may use thawed frozen shrimp.
Have
ready
cooked spaghetti; set aside.
In heavy 3 quart saucepan, melt butter over medium heat (5 to 7 minutes). Add remaining
ingredients,
except
spaghetti,
tomatoes and cheese. Stir to blend.
Cook
over
medium
heat until shrimp turn pink (5 to 7
minutes).
Add
cooked spaghetti.
Continue cooking until spaghetti
is heated through. Stir occasionally. Remove from heat and add
tomatoes.
Cover and let stand until tomatoes are heated through.
To serve:
Sprinkle with cheese. Serve with salad and garlic bread.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: hot surprises
directions: Divide
sausage
into
8 pieces and flatten out.
Rinse peppers and cut stem from top.
Split pepper on one side; open up and remove seeds.
Cut a strip of cheese to fit inside each pepper and
stuff
peppers.
Lay
one
pepper on each sausage patty
and enclose
completely with sausage.
Cook in a large skillet
until done,
turning
several times.
Drain on paper towels.
Be careful
when
you
first bite; the cheese inside will be hot.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning.
Spread mixture on a round serving platter. Top with lettuce, tomatoes, cheeses and black olives. Place some tortilla chips around dip near edge of platter.
Pour the rest of the chips in a bowl and dig in.
Enjoy!

title: mother's nut and jam cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Mix remaining ingredients as listed.
Place in cake pans.
Yields approximately 4 layers. Bake at 300 degrees for 25 minutes.

title: sausage cake
directions: Cream sausage and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients and add in order.
Batter will be stiff.
Pour into 9 x 13 baking dish and bake for approximately 1 hour at 350°. Watch closely the last 10 minutes of baking time as it may easily burn.
Cool and refrigerate until used.
This cake freezes very well.

title: cherry crumb pie
directions: Mix cherries, juice from can plus enough water to make 1 cup, and rest of filling ingredients. In saucepan, cook until mixture boils, becomes thick, and is clear-looking. Pour into unbaked pie shell.

title: turkey burgers
directions: Note:
Amount of ingredients may be adjusted according to the size of the roast.

title: mom's sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet. Press flat with bottom of glass dipped in sugar; be sure to dip glass in sugar between each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen cookies.

title: microwave fast chocolate-pecan fudge
directions: Line square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch, with foil; set aside.
In medium micro-proof bowl, microwave butter on High power 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until melted; add cocoa and stir until smooth.
Stir in confectioners sugar and vanilla; blend well (mixture will be dry and crumbly.)
Stir in evaporated milk.
Micro on High 1 minute; stir.
Micro an additional 1 minute or until mixture is hot.
Beat with wooden spoon until smooth; add pecan pieces.
Pour into prepared pan.
Cover; chill until firm.
Cut into squares.
Store covered in refrigerator.
Makes 4 dozen squares.

title: carolina meat pie
directions: Cut ham finely; cut veal into 1-inch cubes and sprinkle

generously with salt and pepper. Put in pot with butter or lard and when hot, add meat. Brown well; add onions and cook few minutes. Add carrots. Sprinkle with flour and when brown, add boiling water. Combine with ketchup and simmer for 1/2 hour or until meat is tender. Add potatoes and cook until they are tender and stew is rich and thick.

title: olive-pecan chicken slaw
directions: Melt butter in a wide frying pan over medium heat.
Add pecans and cook, stirring often, until nuts turn a darker brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Combine Mustard Cream Dressing, cabbage, chicken, apple, pimentos, olives and celery.
Season to taste with salt.
Sprinkle pecans over top of slaw.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice; cook broccoli just until tender.
Saute onion in margarine until tender.
Add Cheez Whiz
and soup and stir until blended.
Add broccoli and rice; pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cathedral window candy
directions: You will need waxed paper.

title: cranberry salad
directions: First wash berries.
Next grind them.
Spread sugar over berries.
Let stand while mixing other ingredients but do not stir.
Peel apples and grind.
Mix with pineapple.
Make jello with hot water.
Mix all the ingredients together and refrigerate for at least 24 hours.

title: chip bars
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle in graham cracker crumbs. Place coconut and chips on top of crumbs.
Drizzle milk over top.
Sprinkle on nuts.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Combine ingredients well.
Serve on lettuce leaf.
Yields 6 servings.

title: grandma austin's custard pie
directions: Pour into unbaked crust and bake until firm at 350°.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Place the beans in a large bowl or pot and cover with water by 2 inches. Let soak for 8 hours or overnight. Drain and set aside.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix the banana cream pudding mix as directed on box.
Add the condensed milk and mix well.
Stir in the Cool Whip.
Put a layer of the pudding mix in a large size dish followed by a layer of rolled wafers and then a layer of bananas.
Continue until mixture is gone, ending with pudding.
Refrigerate.
This will keep a week or more.

title: orange roughy italiano
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add onion, zucchini and oregano. Saute over medium-high heat, stirring often, for about 4 minutes. Place tomato and fish over vegetables in skillet.

Sprinkle fish with salt and pepper. Cover skillet, reduce heat and simmer until fish is opaque and flakes easily with a fork, about 1 1/2 minutes. Serve immediately. Top with grated cheese just before serving. Serves 4.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan in a 350° oven. Sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with remaining ingredients.
Press down firmly. Bake 25 to 30 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool before cutting.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: fried rice
directions: Preheat wok.
Heat oil.
Cook meat; add onion and eggs. Stir-fry.
Immediately add rice and mix.
Add other vegetables and sprouts.
Mix.
Add soy sauce, salt and m.s.g.
Stir quickly and serve.

title: congo squares
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Melt shortening. Add brown sugar and mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients, chocolate bits and nut meats.
Pour into greased pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: seafood enchiladas
directions: Bring a large pot of water to a boil over high heat and maintain at a boil.
Put the olive oil and garlic in a saute pan and cook over medium heat just until the garlic begins to brown. Remove the saute pan from the heat and pour in the wine.
Return it to the heat.
Cook for another 1 to 2 minutes until the wine has been reduced by half.
Stir in the lemon juice and tomato. Remove the pan from the heat.
tags: frozen crab flavored salad style fish

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, nuts, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs slightly.
Stir in oil, zucchini and lemon peel.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir until moistened.
Spread into 2 greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: turtle cake(keena's turtle cake)
directions: Grease and flour (use cocoa instead of flour) a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour half of batter into pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, melt caramels, milk and magarine together and stir into a caramel sauce.
When cake is finished, pour caramel mixture over cake (reserve 1/2 cup for top if desired).
Sprinkle with nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour remaining cake mix over top. Bake 20 more minutes at 350°.
Top with remaining caramel sauce and nuts, if desired.

title: four layer sabbath delight
directions: Blend together peanuts, flour and butter.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool 20 to 30 minutes.

title: imambayildi(the priest fainted)
directions: Remove the stems of the eggplants, leaving 2 cm.
Peel the eggplants, leaving lengthwise bands 2 cm. wide (to prevent the eggplant crumbling while cooking).
Fry in olive oil, turning them on all sides (they may be previously treated with salt to prevent them absorbing too much oil while cooking).
In a frying pan, brown the onion which has been cut into small pieces.
When the onion and garlic begin to turn brown, add the chopped parsley. Split the eggplants lengthwise, removing some of the seeds if necessary, spreading the two halves apart.
In the cavity, put the mixture of garlic, onion and cooked parsley.
Garnish each eggplant with a tomato ring, then place in a baking dish.
Place the water and remaining oil in the bottom of the dish, if none remains, make a sauce with 2 or 3 tomatoes.
Place in a warm oven for 30 minutes.
Serve cool.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and sugar together.
Flatten out in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 8 minutes at 400°.
Let cool.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potato and onion.
Melt butter.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually add milk; cook until thick.
Drain potatoes. Save water and mix with milk mixture.
Cook for 15 to 30 minutes.

title: spinach rockefeller
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Combine spinach with other ingredients in 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Saute the onion in a little margarine until tender.
Mash up the Swiss steaks and add them and their juice to the pan with the onion.
Add the seasonings, the cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and spaghetti sauce.
Heat until cheeses melt.
Let cool long enough so that the ingredients do not run out of the shells they they're stuffed.
Stuff the cooked shells.
Put a layer of spaghetti sauce in the bottom of a large 11 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Put a single layer of stuffed shells in.
Top the shells with more spaghetti sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pepperoni pinwheels
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles.
Firmly press perforation to seal.
Place 8 pepperoni slices on each rectangle. Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons cheese.
Starting at shortest side, tightly roll up each rectangle.
Pinch to seal. Slice each roll into 4 equal slices.
Pinch dough together on one side to seal.
Place sealed side down on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with warmed pizza sauce, if desired.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Bring to boil, white vinegar and sugar.
Cool.
Rinse and squeeze sauerkraut.
Add pimentos, water chestnuts, onion and celery to sauerkraut.
Pour cooled vinegar and sugar liquid marinade over sauerkraut ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Put in jars or etc.
Marinate 24 hours before serving.
Will keep long time refrigerated.

title: picante sauce
directions: In food processor, chop up all ingredients. Put in large pot. Boil 5 minutes. Turn heat down and simmer 30 to 45 minutes. Put in clean warm jars and seal with lids.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, cloves and nutmeg.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add tomato soup plus enough water to equal 2 cups. Add nuts and dates.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: salad dressing
directions: Beat slowly all but vinegar and oil.
Pour oil and vinegar very slowly.
Stir or shake.
Can be stored in refrigerator or not.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Prepare macaroni dinner as usual.
Combine remaining ingredients in a large bowl; mix well.
Stir in macaroni and cheese.
Spoon tuna mixture into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add crackers, cheese, milk, eggs, sugar, salt and pepper.
Bake uncovered for 25 minutes at 350°.
Top with crushed cracker crumbs for garnish before baking.

title: low-fat banana pudding
directions: Mix whipped topping according to directions.
Mix vanilla pudding with low-fat milk according to directions.
Mix together 1/2 of the whipped topping and the sour cream, then add this to the vanilla pudding.
Layer dish with vanilla wafers and bananas. Place a layer of wafers on top of pudding mixture, then spread the rest of the whipped topping over the wafers.
Chill for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: texas onion casserole
directions: Saute onion rings in saucepan in a little butter until almost transparent, then place in 2-quart casserole.
Put other ingredients into the same saucepan and heat, stirring until cheese melts.
Pour this mixture over the onions.
Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs or Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes. Very good with ham and pork dishes.

title: pork cutlets
directions: Dip pork cutlets in beaten egg and roll in cracker crumbs. Brown the cutlets in shortening in skillet.
Put into baking dish, adding a bit of the shortening and bake, covered, for 1 hour at 300° to 325°.

title: scotcharoos
directions: Bring Karo and sugar to a boil.
Take off burner.
Add peanut butter.
Mix with Rice Krispies.
Pour in 13 x 9-inch cake pan.

title: sicilian pizza
directions: Dissolve yeast packet from hot roll mix with 1 cup water.
Add flour, hot roll mix and eggs.
Let rise a minimum of 2 hours. Must be covered with Saran Wrap.
Spread dough into large (17 x 11 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch) greased pan.
Top with sauce, cheese and topping(s) of your choice.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before cutting.

title: squash oregano
directions: Slice small squash halfwise (long).
Pour melted butter over each half.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and oregano.
Bake at 350° until tender-crisp.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: texas trash
directions: Over low heat, melt butter in skillet.
Add Worcestershire sauce and salt.
After mixed, add other ingredients.
Stir until evenly coated.
Place in covered container and bake for 30 minutes at 350°, stir occasionally while baking.

title: president truman's buttermilk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar, one half cup at a time.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Combine flour and salt.
Add small amount at a time. Add buttermilk.
Batter should look like a cake mix that needs more flour.

title: down home pancakes
directions: Blend all dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop onto hot griddle.
Serve with syrup or jelly and hot coffee on Sunday morning.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Place first 5 ingredients into a bag and mix.
Place chops in and shake.
Brown chops in oil.
Add juice from pineapple chunks and add vinegar.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Cook at low heat at least 40 minutes.
Add pineapple and warm.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Brown sausage in a large skillet.
Do not drain.
Sprinkle in flour and stir over medium heat until all the whiteness is gone. Add the milk and stir constantly until thick, adding the salt and pepper as you stir.
Add more milk if it gets too thick.
Serve over hot biscuits.
Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni in large pot of boiling water until tender, but firm. Drain in colander. Rinse with cold water. In large bowl, combine macaroni, onions, tomato, green pepper and sliced olives. Toss lightly. Add enough fat-free salad dressing. Toss lightly; salt and pepper to taste! Place in refrigerator. Chill for 30 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in Dutch oven; bring to a boil. Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon, reserving 3 tablespoons grease.
