Crumble bacon; set aside.
Add flour to grease in skillet; stir until smooth.
Cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened and bubbly.
Gradually add milk mixture and bacon to potato mixture.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: In largest bowl of electric mixer, cream one cup of the butter with shortening and sugar until mixture is fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and stir in pineapple and juice.
Blend well.

title: war cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour an 8 x 4-inch baking pan.
Place brown sugar, water, raisins, oleo, cinnamon and cloves in a heavy-bottomed saucepan and bring to a boil.
Cook gently for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Let cool until mixture is warm to your finger.
Sift together the flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add them to the cooled sugar mixture, beating until no drifts of flour are visible and batter is smooth.
Stir in walnuts.
Spread evenly in baking pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes, or until cake tester comes out clean.
Let cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Turn onto rack to cool completely.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix lemon pie filling and Cool Whip.
Then add to the rest of the ingredients.
Add 1 c. of mini-marshmallows.
Mix well and chill.

title: chewy brownie cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream shortening, sugar, water and vanilla.
Beat in the eggs.
Combine flour, cocoa, salt and baking soda.
Gradually add to creamed mixture and beat just until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 9 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Yield: 3 dozen.

title: new orleans rice pudding
directions: Bring rice, milk and cream to a boil; cover and
cook until most of milk is absorbed and rice is tender.
Add all other ingredients, except egg yolks and whole eggs.
Stir some of the rice mixture into eggs and pour egg mixture into rice mixture and stir.
Pour into 2-quart buttered casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: yukova
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain grease.
Put cabbage on top and pour 1/2 c. of water over and sprinkle with soy sauce.
Cover and simmer 15-20 minutes.
Add crumbed noodles and flavoring and 1/2 c. water.
Sprinkle with soy sauce.
Stir.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes or until noodles are cooked.
Stir often.
I use more hamburger if I want leftovers.
Adjust cabbage quantity for your taste.
Quick and easy recipe.

title: homemade play dough
directions: Mix flour, salt and cream of tartar in heavy pan.
Add water, oil and food coloring, subject to color.
Heat for 3 minutes, then knead.
Store in airtight containers.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown ground beef, celery, onion and pepper.
In large boiler, combine remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Drain beef mixture and add to boiler.
Cook until potatoes are soft on low heat, approximately 1 hour.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Cook cabbage leaves in boiling water for 5 minutes and then drain.
Combine ground beef, bread crumbs, onion, eggs and seasonings.
Shape into rolls and wrap with cabbage leaves.
Pour soup into skillet and add cabbage rolls.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Simmer 35 minutes, spooning sauce over rolls occasionally.

title: baked chicken
directions: Grease 8 x 8 baking dish.
Put rice in bottom of dish. Sprinkle seasoning on top. Pour chicken broth over rice. Put chicken breasts on top of rice.
Cover with can of soup. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: indian stew
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add all other ingredients; cook slowly, stirring to prevent burning, about an hour or cook in crock-pot. Serve over rice.

title: seasoned oven fried potatoes
directions: Clean potatoes and quarter; cut into 1/4-inch thick.
Place potatoes in mixing bowl.
Add 3 tablespoons oil, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Toss potatoes and lay flat on jelly roll pan; sprinkle with cheese mixture.
Place in 400° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Flip occasionally with pancake turner to prevent sticking.
Serves 4.

title: spreciones(or egg cookies)
directions: Beat sugar, eggs, salt and lemon peel until mixture thickens. Add flour gradually until mixture is thick but not dry.
Roll into small balls, making a peak at the top of each cookie.
Brush with beaten egg and top with an almond sliver.
Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes.

title: rice-a-roni salad
directions: Cook and cool Rice-A-Roni according to package.
Add remaining ingredients; mix and enjoy.

title: cheese surprises
directions: Mix cheese, butter and flour with a fork.
Form into a ball. Flatten the ball and place an olive in the center and wrap the dough around it sealing the olive inside.
Freeze these cheese balls.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: watercress salad with ginger-lime dressing
directions: Add all ingredients and toss lightly.

title: pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease bottom only of loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inches. Beat all ingredients in large bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, 30 seconds. Beat on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally, 4 minutes. Spread in pan. Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, about 55 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Drain peaches and put in casserole. Combine sugar, flour, butter and salt.
Mix until flaky.
Put mixture over peaches.
Preheat oven to 375° and bake for 10 minutes, until golden brown.

title: calico beans
directions: Drain kidney and butter beans slightly.
Saute bacon; add beef and onion.
Fry until brown.
Drain off fat.
Mix with other ingredients.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 325° or cook in crock-pot early in the morning.

title: rhubarb cobbler
directions: Mix together in saucepan the sugar and tapioca.
Stir in water and rhubarb.
Bring to a boil 1 minute, stirring constantly. Place in baking dish.
Dot with butter and cinnamon.
Drop spoonfuls of biscuit dough onto hot fruit.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm with cream.

title: cheddar cheese cornbread
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Add onion and mix together. Add buttermilk and shortening. Mix together. But do not beat. Bake 30 minutes at 350° in an iron skillet.

title: hot fudge sauce(for cake or ice cream)
directions: Melt the chocolate with oleo.
Add sugar, milk and salt.
Cook until slightly thickened, then cool.

title: chicken bundles
directions: Mix all the above.
Separate crescent rolls.
Put some of chicken mixture in center of triangle of crescent roll and place another crescent roll on top and pinch together.
Place bundles on cookie sheet.
Melt 5 to 6 tablespoons of butter and spread over crescent rolls.
Crush 1/2 cup of corn flakes and spread over rolls.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until brown.
Heat the other 1/2 can of chicken soup with 1/4 cup water and serve over bundles.

title: open-faced hamburgers
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Using a fork, spread meat mixture on slices of bread or Subway buns or hamburger buns out to all edges.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake in oven at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes or until meat is done through.
(Bottom of bread will be toasted.)
Remove from oven and cover with slices of cheese. Return to oven for a minute or two until cheese melts.
Serve immediately.

title: fruit salad
directions: Clean and wash all fruit.
Cut fruit into bite size pieces. Add orange juice and toss.
In another bowl, mix raisins, nuts and cinnamon.
Spoon fruit salad into 10 small bowls.
Sprinkle one teaspoon of raisin nut mixture over each fruit salad.
Makes 10 servings.

title: homemade peach ice cream
directions: Add all ingredients except peaches in a saucepan.
Mix together with mixer.
Heat just until sugar dissolves over low-medium heat.
Let cool down to room temperature.
Add peaches; stir and freeze in 4-quart electric churn for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins in 2 cups water.
Drain and reserve liquid. Blend next 5 ingredients.
Stir into raisins.
Add remaining ingredients including raisin liquid.
Mix well and pour into a 9 x 9-inch pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean when inserted in top.
Makes 18 servings.
Each 1 bread, 1 fruit plus 2 fat exchanges.

title: cheese enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Mix together for the sauce the skim milk, cream soups, enchilada sauce and green chilies.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and cook over medium heat until thick. Remove from stove and add oleo or butter, coconut and vanilla flavoring.
Stir well, then pour into 8 or 9-inch baked pie shell (crust).
Top with beaten egg whites saved from egg yolks. Sprinkle coconut on top.
Brown in 350° oven.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, water, salt and butter.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Remove cover.
When mixture reaches soft ball stage, add peanuts.
Stir frequently to prevent scorching.
Cook to hard crack stage.

title: short and simple cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Mix lemon juice, cream cheese, condensed milk and vanilla at medium speed until well blended.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill for 3 to 6 hours.
Top with cherries.
Slice and serve.

title: swedish meatballs in micro
directions: Mix together the beef, crumbs, milk, egg, soup mix, salt and nutmeg.
Shape meat mixture into 40 balls.
Place 20 at a time in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave at High (10) for 7 to 9 minutes, rotating dish half turn after 4 minutes. Remove meatballs from dish; keep warm, reserving meat drippings. Repeat for other 20 meatballs.
To 1/4 cup drippings in dish, add flour, stirring until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk and brown Bouquet sauce.
Microwave at High (10) for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring every minute, until thickened.
Add sour cream; stir well.
Return meatballs to dish, mixing to coat evenly.
Microwave at High (10) for 1 to 2 minutes, until hot.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: no cook chocolate fudge
directions: Sift cocoa and sugar together.
Set aside.
Melt butter and cheese together (microwave is great).
Pour melted butter and cheese over sifted cocoa and sugar.
Mix well.
Add nuts and mix. Spray jellyroll pan with Pam.
Pat mixture in pan.
Place in refrigerator to set.
Cut into squares.

title: beat-n-eat frosting
directions: Bring the water to a boil and add it to all of the other ingredients.
Beat until it is very fluffy.

title: pineapple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Serve as dip for shrimp, crab or lobster.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Layer the asparagus, 1/2 chips and 1/2 cheese; repeat.
Put soup on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Bake pie shell at 450° for 10 minutes.
Cover raisins with boiling water; let stand 5 minutes; drain.
In mixing bowl, combine sugar, cinnamon, salt and cloves.
Stir in sour cream, eggs and lemon juice.
Stir in raisins last.

title: pumpkin gingersnap pie
directions: Pour milk and pie filling into large bowl; beat with wire whisk until well blended, about 1 minute.
Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: crunchy cauliflower salad
directions: Break cauliflower into small pieces.
Dice heart of cauliflower.
Cut broccoli bite size including heart.
Dice onion; chop pepper.

title: microwave potatoes
directions: Wash and scrub potatoes (amount is up to you; leave skins on). Prepare baking dish with Pam spray. Put first layer of potatoes in dish. Sprinkle with salts and pepper (amount depends on you). Layer more potatoes and sprinkle with salts and pepper. Place patties of margarine over top of potatoes. Lightly cover with plastic wrap, being sure to leave 1 end open for steam to escape. Microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes; stir. Microwave for 8 to 10 minutes more, until tender. Serve hot.

title: french toast
directions: Mix nutmeg, cinnamon, vanilla, eggs, milk and brown sugar together.
Dredge the bread through mixture.
Place on hot griddle.
Cook until brown.
Turn bread over and cook until brown.

title: no bake fruit and cereal bars
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In a large saucepan, stir together the brown sugar and honey.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Stir in peanut butter until smooth.
Set aside 1/3 cup dried fruit bits.
Stir in cereal and remaining mixed fruit bits until well coated.
Spread into prepared baking pan.
Press reserved 1/3 cup dried fruit bits onto surface.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Mix ingredients and heat on top of stove until hot.
Pour in casserole dish.

title: texas lime pie
directions: In a bowl, combine cracker crumbs, brown sugar and butter. Press onto the bottom and up the sides of 2 greased 9-inch pie plates.

title: chocolate peanut clusters
directions: Combine all but nuts in saucepan.
Bring to a full boil on high heat, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and boil 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add peanuts; beat until thickened.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Makes 15 to 20 pieces.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix as a pastry crust.
Mixture will be loose.
Put in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until light brown.

title: broccoli-cheese dip
directions: In medium bowl combine soup, broccoli, tomato, sour cream and mustard.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving. Serve with crackers and vegetables.

title: four-decker mocha dessert
directions: In mixing bowl cut butter into flour until crumbly; stir in 3/4 cup of the peanuts.
Press mixture evenly over bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes; cool.
In a small mixer bowl beat cream cheese on low speed of electric mixer until fluffy; beat in powdered sugar and half of the thawed whipped topping.
Spread over crust; chill.
In large mixer bowl combine both pudding mixes and milk, beat with rotary beater 2 minutes. Spoon a top of cream cheese layer in dish.
Chill or freeze until firm, several hours or overnight.
Top with remaining thawed whipped topping.
Sprinkle with grated chocolate and remaining chopped peanuts.
(If frozen, let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving.)

title: yum yum cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Bake in sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cinnamon baked apples
directions: Core apples.
Do not peel.
Make cuts down the sides of the apples to allow them to breathe.
Place in shallow baking dish. Place red candies into each apple.
Microwave on High until tender (4 to 6 minutes).
Serve in decorative dessert dish topped with ice cream.

title: orange liqueur
directions: With no white on the rind, blot dry with paper towels.
Put rind into a quart jar.
Add 2 cups of vodka, screw on top and store for 2 days in a cool, dark place.
Remove peel, add sugar and shake until sugar dissolves.
Add 1 cup vodka and stir.
Close jar and store again for 1 week at least.

title: apple-cranberry relish
directions: Put all fruit and peel through a grinder or food processor. Add sugar to taste.
Refrigerate several hours.
Serve as a sauce with ham, turkey or as a salad.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onions until tender; add salt and oleo. Cook 2 minutes.
Add milk.
Do not cook.

title: snicker cake
directions: Make cake according to directions. Put 1/2 the batter in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 25 minutes or until "just" done. Meanwhile, melt milk, caramels and oleo. Remove cake from oven and cool a little. Pour melted caramel mixture over cake. Top with chips and nuts. Dot remaining 1/2 of batter on top. Return to oven for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chili enchiladas
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain off fat.
Mix chili into meat mixture.
Line bottom of baking dish with flour tortillas.
Pour meat and chili mixture on top of tortillas; repeat layers until all gone.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tumbleweeds
directions: Combine white chocolate and peanut butter chips in a 2-quart glass bowl.
Microwave on 50% power for 4 minutes or until melted; mix well.
Stir in peanuts and potato sticks.

title: minestrone soup
directions: In large heavy pot, saute garlic and onion in oil.
Add all other ingredients except peas, macaroni and cheese.
Bring slowly to a boil, lower heat and simmer 1 hour, stirring often. When vegetables are tender, add peas, macaroni and cheese.
Remove from heat and let stand 20 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.
Freezes well.

title: cheese roll
directions: Soften cheese; grate the Cheddars or buy it already grated. Add ingredients to all cheese.
Mix with hands.
Roll into 2 large or 4 small rolls.
Refrigerate before cutting.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix together the condensed milk and undiluted lemonade.
Slowly stir in Cool Whip, then the juice from 1 lemon.
Blend well.
Spoon into pie shells.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: blender sweet potato pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender; mix well.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: stay up all night coffee cake
directions: Grease a Bundt pan; then sprinkle with the chopped nuts on bottom of pan.
Arrange rolls evenly over the nuts.
Sprinkle dry pudding over the rolls.
In a small bowl, combine sugar, melted margarine and cinnamon.
Cover rolls with the sugar mixture. Place in a cold oven to remain overnight.
In the morning, remove rolls from oven.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Return rolls to oven and bake for 25 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: fresh salsa dip
directions: Put all
ingredients
in food processor.
Process until chunky.
Keeps for	several weeks in refrigerator.	Serve with baked tortilla chips for great nonfat snack!

title: holly cookies
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows in a double boiler.
Blend in food color and vanilla.
Pour over cornflakes and mix very lightly with a fork (do not crush the corn flakes).
Drop by teaspoon, a small amount on a cookie sheet or plate.
Decorate with 3 red hots on each "holly leaf".

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Drain broccoli, combine ingredients, mix well.
Spoon into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs. Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: libby's pumpkin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, oats, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Cream butter.
Add sugars, beating until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Alternate additions of dry ingredients and pumpkin; mix well.
Stir in morsels.
Drop by spoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: buttermilk chess pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour in a large bowl.
Add eggs and buttermilk; stir until blended.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
Cool on wire rack.
Yield: one 9-inch pie.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Measure and sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream margarine; add sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; stir until thoroughly mixed.
Stir in mashed bananas.
Fold in dry ingredients and nuts. Place in a well-greased bread pan (2) or 4 small bread pans. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: skillet corn and tomatoes
directions: In a skillet, put tomatoes.
Add corn.
Stir.
Add pepper and salt, butter and oil.
Stir well.
If desired, you can add leftover chopped chicken and then add 1 tablespoon basil and 1 teaspoon nutmeg.
Stir well.
Add 1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese. Let cheese melt.
Stir well.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Grease cookie sheet.
Beat egg white until stiff; fold in brown sugar and pecans.
Mix, then spoon out on cookie sheet.
Put in oven at 450° for 1 minute.
Turn oven off.
Let set 12 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown onion, garlic and meat.
Add to next 7 ingredients; simmer 1 hour.
Cook lasagna noodles as package directs and drain. Put a little sauce in 9 x 13-inch pan and then layer noodles, sauce, sour cream, cheese, etc.
End with sauce and top with Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes.

title: egg custard
directions: Scald milk with margarine in pot (do not boil) or double boiler. Beat eggs, sugar and flavoring with electric mixer. Pour milk/margarine over this mixture and beat. Pour in pie shells. Bake 10 minutes at 450°; turn down and bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken-cheese enchiladas
directions: Combine soup, chilies and onion.
Cook on low 15 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add sour cream.
Fry tortillas.
Fill with mixture and a sprinkle of cheese.
Roll separately and put in oblong cake pan.
Pour remaining sauce over rolls and sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: brunswick soup
directions: Flour chicken.
Saut in oil until golden brown, add onions, tomatoes, water, seasoning and all other ingredients. Simmer until tender.

title: cherry cobbler bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 11 x 7-inch pan.
Mix flour and baking powder.
In a large bowl, beat butter and confectioners sugar with electric beater.
Beat in egg and lemon peel.
Mix on low and gradually add flour.
Remove 2/3 cup of dough.

title: emergency cake
directions: Cream eggs and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while warm.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, spread onion soup mix.
Spread 1 cup rice over top.
Over that place chicken.
Add mixed water and soups. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil and brown for about 20 minutes.

title: millionaire salad
directions: Combine cream cheese and sugar in mixing bowl; mix well.
Add pineapple, rice, pecans, salad dressing and marshmallows; mix well. Fold in whipped cream gently.
Yields 10 servings.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: After raisins are cooked down, add cream, then add sugar and flour, mixed.
Cook until partly thick and add vanilla and butter. Pour in baked shell and add meringue and bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: cherry scrap cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
After it cools, crumble up in large bowl.
Pour over cake your prepared instant pudding, then add pineapple, sliced bananas, nuts, cherries and top with Cool Whip.

title: southern style shredded pork(sauce)
directions: In large saucepan, combine all sauce ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour sauce over meat.
Turn to coat.
Cover; refrigerate 8 hours or overnight, turning occasionally.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Cube chocolate cake.
In a 3-quart size trifle bowl, layer half the cake cubes, 2 cups chocolate pudding, 1 cup whipped cream and half Heath bar pieces; repeat layers.

title: sour cream christmas cookies
directions: Bake at 355°.
Don't let them get brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix stuffing, butter and water lightly and put half in buttered 9 x 12-inch dish.
Mix next 5 ingredients and put in casserole over stuffing mixture.
Cover with remaining half of stuffing mix.
Beat eggs and milk; spread over casserole.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Take out 1 hour before baking.
Spread mushroom or mushroom-chicken soup over top.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes, uncovered.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and return to oven for 8 minutes.

title: zucchini saute
directions: Use a food processor or hand grater to grate the zucchini. Saute in the margarine and Creole seasoning.
Cover and let the zucchini set in its juices.
Umm delicious!

title: fudge pecan pie
directions: Combine all except pecans and beat.
Stir in nuts and pour into crust.
Place nut halves on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in large casserole.
Top with cheese and crushed potato chips.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken.
Dip each piece in melted margarine and coat with finely crushed potato chips.
Place in baking pan and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: meringue jewels
directions: Beat egg whites until foam is stiff.
Gradually add sugar. Continue until egg whites form stiff peaks.
Add vanilla, then nuts.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 40 minutes or until light or golden brown.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop on greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Yields 12 to 18 cookies.

title: awesome slow cooker pot roast
directions: In a slow cooker, mix cream of mushroom soup, dry onion soup mix, brown gravy mix and water. Place pot roast in slow cooker and coat with soup mixture. Cook on high setting for 3 to 4 hours or on low setting for 8 to 9 hours.

title: low calorie shake 'n bake
directions: Mix and use as substitute for original Shake 'n Bake.

title: chicken soup with potatoes
directions: In a large saucepan, saute onion in butter until tender. Stir in broth and potatoes; bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 15 minutes or so, until potatoes are tender. Stir in chicken, salt and pepper. Combine flour and milk until smooth. Stir into pan; add milk. Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened. Sprinkle with parsley and chives.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix above ingredients well and pour in pie shell. Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes.

title: steak and potato supper
directions: Dredge steak in flour. Brown well on both sides in hot fat. Place meat in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour off excess fat. Scrape up brown drippings left in pan and add to meat.
Sprinkle onion, parsley, salt and pepper over all. Add tomato sauce. Cover and bake in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Makes 4 generous servings.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix together. Pour in graham cracker pie crust and freeze.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs to mixture.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to butter mixture alternately with milk.
Add flavoring and mix well.
Place dough on floured board and knead to cutting consistency.
(Add up to 1/4 cup flour, if needed.)
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thick and cut as biscuits.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix all together, except the eggs. Let stand in fridge until chilled or overnight. Before serving, add chopped tomatoes, head of lettuce and eggs.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Prepare lemon Jell-O according to package directions.
Pour into 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Chill until set.
Drain fruit cocktail, reserving syrup.
Place syrup in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil; remove from heat.
Combine cold water and unflavored gelatin.
When gelatin is softened, add to hot syrup.
Stir until gelatin is completely dissolved.
Add cottage cheese.
Add drained fruit cocktail.
Mix well.
Spoon over chilled lemon gelatin. Chill until set.
Prepare strawberry gelatin according to directions.
Pour over cottage cheese mixture.
Chill until set. Unmold onto lettuce-lined serving platter.
Makes 8 servings.

title: crab seviche
directions: Mix all ingredients, cover with lemon juice and stir.
Heat until hot.
Serve with saltines or tortilla chips, hot or cold.

title: black forest chocolate fudge cake
directions: Prepare prune puree.
Set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat a 3 to 4-quart Bundt or other tube pan with a vegetable cooking spray.
Set aside.
Into a large bowl, sift together flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
In another bowl, whisk eggs with the prune puree, milk and vanilla.
Set aside.
Pour boiling water in measuring cup.
Stir in Espresso powder and soda.
Stir in eggs and water mixture into flour mixture.
Mix just until blended. Pour half the batter into prepared pan; sprinkle cherries and walnuts evenly over batter.
Evenly pour in remaining batter.
Bake in 350° oven for about 45 minutes until pick inserted into cake comes out clean.
Cool in pan on rack for 15 minutes; invert onto rack.
Remove pan and cool completely.
Dust with powdered sugar. Place on serving plate.
Fill cake center with additional cherries. Makes 16 servings.

title: mud pie
directions: Crush Oreos; cover bottom of pan with 1/2.
Mix pudding as directed.
Mix in cheese and Cool Whip.
Spread over crushed Oreos.
Sprinkle remaining cookies over top and refrigerate.

title: easy cran-orange relish
directions: Cut oranges into chunks, rind and pulp, removing all seeds. Wash and pick over berries.
Place oranges, cranberries and sugar in the bowl of a processor.
Process until coarsely chopped. Refrigerate until serving time.
Freezes well.

title: spinach stuffed peppers
directions: Chop and saute onions.
Add flour and cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add blended mix of milk.
Stir in spinach to desired consistency.
Steam peppers with tops cut off 5 to 7 minutes. Fill peppers with mixture.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: ruth's western barbecued beans
directions: Combine ground beef, salt, pepper and garlic.
Saute in cooking oil in large skillet over medium heat until lightly browned.
Add onion and brown a few minutes longer until onion is golden.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into bean pot or 9-inch square baking dish.
If desired, garnish top with onion rings and drizzle with a little catsup.
Bake in a slow 325° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: ham puffs
directions: Beat together flour, baking powder and eggs until well blended.
Mix in potatoes and ham.
Heat oil to 350° and drop batter by teaspoon into oil.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: cass county corn bread
directions: Heat oil in pan in oven while mixing other ingredients.
Mix all ingredients (except oil).
Add heated oil last.
Bake in 425° oven for about 20 minutes in 8 or 9-inch pan.
Serves 8.

title: jelly roll
directions: Beat egg whites and 1/2 cup sugar until they form fluffy peaks.
Beat egg yolks, 1/4 cup sugar and vanilla until light yellow.
Fold egg whites into egg yolks and add flour.
Pour onto cookie sheet which is greased and has wax paper in it.
Bake at 350° until done.
Remove from cookie sheet onto lightly powdered sugar towel and remove wax paper.
Roll up in towel and let cool for 5 minutes.
Unroll and put jelly on it.
Then roll it up again without the towel.
Place toothpicks in it to help hold it together.

title: mounds candy
directions: Mix sugar, coconut, milk and butter together.
Press into oblong pan and chill.
Cut into small squares.
Dip in coating mix.

title: aunt winnie's glazed lemon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: homemade chili
directions: Fry hamburger and onion together until done.
Drain off all grease.
Add remainder of ingredients and cook on medium heat 20-25 minutes.

title: hominy salad
directions: Rinse hominy and drain well.
Combine with remaining ingredients and chill well.
Serve on lettuce, garnished with tomato wedges and more mayonnaise, if desired.

title: tangy beef salad
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, wine, Worcestershire sauce, garlic and onion salt in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch microwave-safe baking dish. Partially freeze steak; slice diagonally across the grain into thin slices, and cut into 2-inch lengths.
Place steak in marinade; cover and marinate at least 2 hours in refrigerator. Cover with wax paper; microwave at Medium-high (70% power) 5 minutes; stir.
Microwave at Medium-high 3 to 5 additional minutes or to desired degree of doneness, stirring after 2 minutes. Remove from oven; let stand 5 minutes.
Drain steak; discard marinade.

title: grandma majernik's chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a bowl, combine first 3 ingredients with a wire whisk and set aside.
In another bowl, beat oleo and both sugars to a grainy paste.
Add egg and vanilla.
Then combine dry ingredients with oleo-sugar mixture.
When well mixed, add chocolate chips and nuts.

title: whipped cream pound cake
directions: Cream
butter,	sugar and eggs.
Add flour and whipping cream alternately.
Bake in large tube pan for 1 1/2 hours or until done at 325°.

title: shrimp scampi(microwave)
directions: Place butter in 2-quart casserole and microwave on High until melted.
Stir in parsley, lemon juice, garlic and salt.
Add shrimp and toss to coat.
Cover and microwave until shrimp is pink and tender (do not overcook or shrimp will be tough), about 4 to 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Sprinkle with paprika and serve.

title: chicken tamales
directions: Process cornmeal, oat bran, baking powder, salt, cumin, chili powder and margarine in food processor until blended.
With machine running, pour in broth; process until blended.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Combine chicken, tomato sauce and 2 tablespoons chilies in small bowl.

title: "taco pizza"
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Stir in tomato sauce and taco mix. Simmer 5 minutes.
Press dough on 12-inch ungreased pizza pan and prick bottom.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes, until golden brown. Fill with meat mixture.
Cover with cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.
Top with remaining ingredients and top with sour cream.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and spread in 13 x 9-inch ungreased pan.
Beat together remaining ingredients and spread onto cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: easy cherry pie
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix together sugar, flour and milk.
Pour batter over melted butter in pan.
Pour filling on top.
Bake until golden brown on top at 350°.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: pretzel dessert
directions: Mix pretzel crumbs, butter and sugar together and press in the bottom of square dish. Mix up 1 package of Dream Whip according to directions on the package.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar. Fold this mixture into the prepared Dream Whip.
Spread over the crumb mixture in the bottom of your dish.
Top with 1 can of cherry pie filling or your favorite fruit.
Sprinkle pretzel crumbs over the top and chill.

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook ziti according to package directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water and drain again.
In a mixing bowl, beat (with electric mixer), Ricotta, Mozzarella, Romano cheese, egg whites, parsley and pepper until fluffy.

title: poor man's filet mignon
directions: Combine first eight ingredients and 2 tablespoons barbecue sauce.
Form into 12 thick patties.
Wrap a bacon slice around the sides of each patty and secure with a toothpick.
Bake on a rack at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until desired doneness is reached. Baste frequently with remaining barbecue sauce the last 30 minutes.
Yields 12 servings.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
With rolling pin, crush vanilla wafers.
Add wafer flour alternately with milk.
Add coconut.
Fold in pecans.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Pour mixture into pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: maple sugar pumpkin pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except last 2.
Pour into the pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 45 minutes or until knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool to room temperature. Refrigerate.
Garnish with whipped cream, if desired.
Yields 8 servings.

title: three berry kuchen
directions: Spray 10-inch round spring-form pan with cooking spray. Combine in bowl 1 1/2 cups flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In large bowl, whisk egg whites, sugar, applesauce, yogurt and lemon zest until smooth.
Add flour mixture all at once to wet ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Place in prepared pan.
Place berries on top of batter.
In small bowl, combine remaining flour and brown sugar.
Cut in cold margarine and mix until evenly blended.
Put topping on batter.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes at 350°. Cool 20 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together; form into 1-inch balls.
May freeze at this point.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, if thawed; 30 minutes if frozen.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Add dressing and toss again.
Serve immediately.

title: dinosaur bone explorer
directions: Pretend chocolate chips are dinosaur bones.
Use the toothpick as your digging tool.
How many "bones" can you retrieve.
Brush off the cookie crumbs with the paintbrush.
For a party game, children can race against the clock to see who can find the most bones.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix in bowl the 3 cans of soup.
Take out 1 can of the mixed soup.
Add the uncooked rice to the cans of soup mix.
Put into a greased pan or casserole.
Lay chicken pieces on top of rice/soup mixture.
Pour 1 can of mixed soup over the chicken.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until chicken is tender, brown and crispy.

title: casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions until done.
Add barbecue sauce, brown sugar and beans.
When hot and bubbly, cut biscuits in halves.
Pour meat mixture into casserole dish.
Poke biscuit halves in mixture and cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 400° until biscuits are done and cheese is melted.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt. Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring 5 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in soda and vanilla.
Pour over popped corn, mixing well.
Turn into 2 large shallow pans (with sides) or roaster pans.
Bake in 250° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven; cool.
Break apart and store in tightly covered container.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Boil 5 minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon of vanilla.

title: cheese bites
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prepare pie crust as directed on box; add cheese to dry ingredients.
Shape mixture around olive, onion or nut.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet or shallow baking dish. Bake at 400° for about 45 minutes.

title: broccoli puffs
directions: Combine butter, water, salt and garlic powder in saucepan. Heat until water is boiling and butter is melted.
Add flour all at once.
Remove from heat and stir mixture quickly until dough comes away from sides of pan.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir broccoli into dough.
Chill 2 hours or overnight.
Pour oil into deep skillet and heat to 375°. Drop heaping teaspoonful of mixture into oil.
Brown on one side about 2 minutes, then turn and brown on other side.
Drain. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and serve hot.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, Parkay and Milnot.
Bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Continue to cook, boiling 5 minutes over medium heat.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: over night sticky buns
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients well. Spray bundt pan with Pam, sprinkle nuts or raisins on bottom of pan. Layer frozen buns on top of nuts or raisins. Sprinkle butterscotch pudding over rolls evenly. Pour oleo mix over rolls. Cover with a paper towel. Let stand at room temperature over night. Cover loosely with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Invert immediately on plate. Enjoy!!

title: refrigerator cake
directions: Mix first five ingredients and press into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix sugar, Cool Whip and cream cheese and spread over crust.
Mix pudding with 3 cups milk. Spread over cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: lazy day fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding mix and fruit cocktail.
Mix all together.

title: corn meal cookies
directions: Mix margarine and sugar in bowl.
Add egg and beat well.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Drop dough from teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until light brown.

title: *easy biscuits
directions: Combine flour, milk and mayonnaise in bowl; mix well.
Fill greased muffin cups.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 12 servings.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all together by hand.
Bake in greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: creamy italian pasta salad
directions: Can also add sliced artichoke hearts.

title: corn bread
directions: Grease an 8-inch pie pan.
Mix in this order.
Bake in 425° oven for 20 minutes or until light brown.

title: red skin potatoes
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam spray.
Wash potatoes and cut in half.
Coat potatoes with onion soup and oil by putting in a bag and shaking until all potatoes are coated.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
(Need not add any liquid.)

title: ripe tomato relish
directions: Chop or cut in small pieces.
Mix all ingredients and boil for about 2 hours, slowly, or until thick.
Stir often to keep from sticking.
Cook in porcelain pan.
Seal while hot.
Yields 6 to 7 pints.

title: ranch oyster crackers
directions: Mix Hidden Valley with oil, pour over crackers, stirring well to coat evenly. Bake 15-20 minutes at 250°. Stir halfway through baking. Use for snacks, with soups or party appetizers.

title: wassail
directions: Combine cider, brown sugar and fruit juices in large pot and add spices.
Bring to a boil, lower heat and simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Strain to remove spices.
